(4589, 332, 7, '<p>Es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de acetato de buserelina al 0,00042%, an&aacute;logo sint&eacute;tico del de GnRH hipotal&aacute;mica.&nbsp;Producto para el aparato reproductor y manejo de la reproducci&oacute;n en hembras bovinas y equinas.</p>\r\n'),
(4590, 332, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Acetato de buserelina 420 mcg, agua para inyectables, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4591, 332, 1, '<p>GONAXAL&reg; est&aacute; indicado para corregir trastornos en la reproducci&oacute;n sobre todo de origen ov&aacute;rico, para program&aacute;s de Inseminaci&oacute;n Artiicial, por su efecto sobre la ovulaci&oacute;n y mejoramiento de los par&aacute;metros de concepci&oacute;n. Aciclia, ovulaci&oacute;n retardada, atresia folicular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bovinos: Usos terap&eacute;uticos: Para el tratamiento del anestro por causas ov&aacute;ricas, al promover el desarrollo folicular y la consecuente ovulaci&oacute;n. Tratamiento de quistes ov&aacute;ricos persistentes, al promover su luteinizaci&oacute;n. Usos biotecnol&oacute;gicos: Para la sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo en program&aacute;s de inseminaci&oacute;n artiicial. Mejoramiento de los par&aacute;metros reproductivos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equinos: Usos terap&eacute;uticos: Celos prolongados o permanentes. Aciclia. Usos biotecnol&oacute;gicos: Promover la ovulaci&oacute;n de fol&iacute;culos maduros y predecir mejor el momento del servicio o Inseminaci&oacute;n artiicial. Aumento de los &iacute;ndices de concepci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4592, 332, 3, '<p>GONAXAL&reg; se administra preferentemente por v&iacute;a intramuscular profunda, pero pueden usarse como v&iacute;as alternativas, la endovenosa y la subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bovinos:<br />\r\nTratamiento del anestro por causas ov&aacute;ricas: Quiste folicular: Administrar 5 mL de GONAXAL&reg; (equivalente a 21mcg de buserel&iacute;na acetato). No es necesaria la revisaci&oacute;n ginecol&oacute;gica para la eliminaci&oacute;n del quiste. Se debe realizar una nueva revisaci&oacute;n entre 10 a 15 d&iacute;as de la primera, pudiendo repetirse el tratamiento en caso de no obtener una respuesta favorable.<br />\r\nAnestro: Administrar 5 mL de GONAXAL&reg; (equivalente a 21mcg de buserel&iacute;na acetato). En caso de no observar celo dentro de los 10 a 12 d&iacute;as de realizado el tratamiento, se aconseja la revisaci&oacute;n ginecol&oacute;gica para detectar ausencia de estructuras funcionales de los ovarios y falta de tono uterino. En estos casos se debe repetir el tratamiento.<br />\r\nOvulaciones retardadas: Administrar 2,5 mL de GONAXAL&reg; al momento del servicio a corral o inseminaci&oacute;n artiicial, como m&aacute;ximo 6 horas antes de los mismos. En este caso la ovulaci&oacute;n se producir&aacute; dentro de las 24 horas de realizado el tratamiento.<br />\r\nAlteraciones Tocol&oacute;gicas: Administrar 5 mL de GONAXAL&reg; en vacas que hayan sufrido partos dist&oacute;cicos, con retenciones placentarias, ya que pueden alargar el periodo de parto-concepci&oacute;n por tener quistes foliculares. Este tratamiento se debe realizar entre 10 y 14 d&iacute;as post-parto, sobre todo en hembras productoras de leche.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equinos:<br />\r\nEn las yeguas se utiliza en general para: Quistes ov&aacute;ricos: Administrar 10 mL de GONAXAL&reg;<br />\r\nAnestro: Administrar 5 mL de GONAXAL&reg; 2 veces con un intervalo entre ambos de 24 horas. De persistir la alteraci&oacute;n isiol&oacute;gica por 10 d&iacute;as, repetir el tratamiento los d&iacute;as 11&ordm; y 12&ordm;.<br />\r\nInducci&oacute;n de la ovulaci&oacute;n: Administrar 10 mL de GONAXAL&reg;. Se aconseja su uso 6 horas antes de realizar el servicio o la inseminaci&oacute;n artiicial, aplicando el producto por la ma&ntilde;ana y realizando el servicio por la tarde. Se aconseja un nuevo servicio a la ma&ntilde;ana siguiente. Si por revisaci&oacute;n ginecol&oacute;gica se diagnostica que la yegua no ha ovulado, se aconseja repetir el tratamiento.</p>\r\n'),
(4593, 332, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4594, 332, 6, '<p>Frascos por 50 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4595, 333, 7, '<p>Complejo vitam&iacute;nico inyectable para bovinos, equinos, ovinos y porcinos, de manifiesta acci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica que interviene regulando el metabolismo del Calcio y el F&oacute;sforo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>De esta manera se asegura la calciicaci&oacute;n de los huesos, activando las fosfatasas sangu&iacute;neas en los puntos de osiicaci&oacute;n del cart&iacute;lago y provocando mejor asimilaci&oacute;n de dichos factores nutricionales. Estimula el crecimiento, mantiene el estado normal de los epitelios, mejora el pelaje, favorece la reproducci&oacute;n y mejora el estado general de los animales. Las vitaminas A, D3 y E son las llamadas vitaminas liposolubles. En consecuencia, su formulaci&oacute;n en veh&iacute;culo oleoso resulta la m&aacute;s adecuada, pues mejora su estabilidad y su acci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica.</p>\r\n'),
(4596, 333, 2, '<p>Vitamina A 500.000 U.I.; Vitamina D3 75.000 U.I.; Vitamina E 50 U.I.; excipientes c.s.p. 1 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4597, 333, 1, '<p>Preventivo y curativo del raquitismo, osteomalacia e hipocalcemia. Para elevar el porcentaje de pre&ntilde;ez, mejorar el estado general de los reproductores y favorecer el engorde en la recr&iacute;a e invernada. Como adyuvante de tratamientos antiinfecciosos y antiparasitarios. Para ser administrado durante e inmediatamente despu&eacute;s de la gestaci&oacute;n. Como fuente vitam&iacute;nica en &eacute;pocas de sequ&iacute;a o alimentaci&oacute;n deiciente.</p>\r\n'),
(4598, 333, 3, '<p>Bovinos: Toros: 4-6 mL; Vacas: 2-4 mL; Terneros: 0,5-1 mL; Recr&iacute;a e invernada: 1-4 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equinos: Padrillos: 3-6 mL; Yeguas: 3-5 mL; Potrillos: 1-2 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: Carneros y ovejas: 1-2 mL; Corderos: 0,25-0,5 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: Machos y hembras adultas: 1-3 mL; Lechones: 0,25 &ndash; 0,5 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>V&iacute;a de administraci&oacute;n: subcut&aacute;nea o intramuscular.</p>\r\n'),
(4599, 333, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4600, 333, 6, '<p>Frascos por 100 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4601, 334, 7, '<p>Suplemento mineral inyectable para bovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4602, 334, 2, '<p>Cobre (como edetato )1,0 g; Zinc (como edetato ) 4,0 g; Manganeso (como edetato ) 1,0 g; Selenio (como selenito de sodio) 0,5 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4603, 334, 1, '<p>ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de microelementos que est&aacute; indicada para la prevenci&oacute;n y control del estr&eacute;s oxidativo en terneros al destete, al inicio de un plan de inmunizaci&oacute;n y al ingreso de animales al feedlot; as&iacute; como otras situaciones que pudiesen generar la formaci&oacute;n de radicales super&oacute;xido, como por ejemplo el transporte. ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN tambi&eacute;n est&aacute; indicado para la prevenci&oacute;n y tratamiento de las carencias de los microelementos que &eacute;sta soluci&oacute;n contiene (Cobre, Zinc, Selenio y Manganeso). Los microelementos de ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN y las vitaminas de ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT representan en forma conjunta o aislada factores esenciales para la defensa antioxidante del organismo.</p>\r\n'),
(4604, 334, 3, '<p>La dosis aconsejada de ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN, es de 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. El intervalo entre dosis no debe ser inferior a 30 d&iacute;as. Animales j&oacute;venes (terneros/as) hasta 200 kg: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. Animales en recr&iacute;a (novillos y vaquillonas): 4 mL por animal como dosis total. Animales Adultos: Vacas: 5 mL por animal como dosis total. Toros: 6 mL por animal como dosis total.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con agujas 12 x 18. Se recomienda generar reserva hep&aacute;tica fetal tratando a las vacas con ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN en el &uacute;ltimo tercio de la gestaci&oacute;n, evitando de esa forma las deiciencias de Cu y Zn en el ternero al pie de corta edad, al ser dif&iacute;cil el tratamiento en esta categor&iacute;a.</p>\r\n'),
(4605, 334, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4606, 334, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kit compuesto por 1 frasco de ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN por 500 mL y 1 frasco de ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4607, 335, 7, '<p>Suplemento Vitam&iacute;nico inyectable para bovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4608, 335, 2, '<p>Vitamina A palmitato 3,5 g; Vitamina E acetato 5,0 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(4609, 335, 1, '<p>ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de vitaminas A y E, indicada para ser utilizada s&oacute;la o en forma conjunta con ADAPTADOR&reg;MIN, para que ambos intervengan impidiendo fundamentalmente los procesos oxidativos que se producen en los animales ante cualquier situaci&oacute;n de estr&eacute;s. Situaciones como castraciones, destetes, ingreso a feedlot, situaciones ambientales extrem&aacute;s (sequ&iacute;a &ndash; inundaci&oacute;n). Las vitaminas junto a los microelementos, macroelementos y la energ&iacute;a aportada por la dieta (forrajes y granos), son requerimientos diarios que necesita el animal y aunque &eacute;stos var&iacute;an en sus aportes desde miligramos a kilogramos, todos tienen el mismo valor y un desbalance entre los mismos provocar&aacute; deiciencias que afectan al animal. Los microelementos de ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN y las vitaminas de ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT, son en forma conjunta o aislada factores esenciales para la defensa antioxidante del organismo.</p>\r\n'),
(4610, 335, 3, '<p>Terneros: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v., desde la primera semana de vida hasta el destete.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Novillos: 4 mL al comienzo del per&iacute;odo de engorde, 1 aplicaci&oacute;n cada 3 meses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vaquillonas: 4 mL durante la recr&iacute;a cada 3 meses, y antes del servicio. Vacas: 5 mL, 1 a 2 meses antes del servicio y 1 a 2 meses antes de la parici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Toros: 6 mL, 1 a 2 meses antes de comenzar el servicio, y durante el mismo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con agujas 12 x 18.</p>\r\n'),
(4611, 335, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4612, 335, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kit compuesto por 1 frasco de ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN por 500 mL y 1 frasco de ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4613, 336, 7, '<p>Calcificante. Soluci&oacute;n inyectable para bovinos, equinos, ovinos y porcinos. Con refuerzo energ&eacute;tico y cardiot&oacute;nico.</p>\r\n'),
(4614, 336, 2, '<p>Borogluconato de Calcio 9,25 g; Gluconato de Calcio 2,25 g; Sacarato de Calcio 0,5 g; Hipofosito de Magnesio 1 g; Cloruro de magnesio, 9 g; Cafe&iacute;na 0,1 g; Glucosa 12 g; Fenol 0,5 g; Agua para inyectables, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4615, 336, 1, '<p>Hipocalcemias. Hipomagnesemias. Fiebre Vitular. Acetonemia. Estados parapl&eacute;jicos del pre y post parto. Eclampsia. Tetanias. Enfermedades del transporte. Raquitismo. Osteomalacia. Colapso o Paresia Puerperal.</p>\r\n'),
(4616, 336, 3, '<p>Bovinos y Equinos adultos: 250-700 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros, potrillos, ovinos y porcinos: 100 a 200 mL. Corderos y lechones: 5 a 20 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Es muy efectiva la administraci&oacute;n de mitad de la dosis por inyecci&oacute;n endovenosa y la otra mitad por inyecci&oacute;n intramuscular.</p>\r\n'),
(4617, 336, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4618, 336, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4619, 337, 7, '<p>Es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de Cobre (Cu) y Zinc (Zn), para corregir y evitar las deiciencias de estos microelementos que se maniiestan en los bovinos en vastas zonas del pa&iacute;s. Su formulaci&oacute;n especial permite alcanzar los niveles isiol&oacute;gicos y mantenerlos para evitar las deiciencias provocadas por las carencias en suelos, aguas de bebida y forrajes.</p>\r\n'),
(4620, 337, 2, '<p>Cobre (como Edetato), 1,5 g; Zinc (como Edetato), 5 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4621, 337, 1, '<p>Prevenci&oacute;n y tratamiento de las deficiencias de Cu y Zn, que incluyen fallas en la pigmentaci&oacute;n del pelo (acromotriquia), anemia, diarreas, deformaciones articulares, fracturas espont&aacute;neas en terneros, p&eacute;rdida de la condici&oacute;n corporal y prevenci&oacute;n de la muerte s&uacute;bita por falla card&iacute;aca en animales adultos.</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `tbl_producto_contenido` (`id`, `producto_id`, `parte`, `text`) VALUES
(4622, 337, 3, '<p>Animales j&oacute;venes: Terneros/as hasta 200 kg., 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales en recr&iacute;a: Novillos y vaquillonas, 4 mL por animal como dosis &uacute;nica y total.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales adultos: Vacas, 5 mL, toros, 6 mL, dosis &uacute;nica y total. Se recomienda generar reserva hep&aacute;tica fetal administrando SUPLENUT&reg; a las vacas en el &uacute;ltimo tercio de la gestaci&oacute;n, evitando de esa forma las deiciencias de Cu y Zn en el ternero al pie de corta edad, al ser dif&iacute;cil el tratamiento en &eacute;sta categor&iacute;a.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con agujas 12/18, manteniendo buenas condiciones de asepsia en todo el instrumental.</p>\r\n'),
(4623, 337, 9, '<p>Prestar singular atenci&oacute;n a las dosis a administrar, ya que dosis superiores a las aconsejadas pueden llegar a provocar necrosis hep&aacute;ticas agudas y crisis hemol&iacute;ticas</p>\r\n'),
(4624, 337, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4625, 337, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4626, 339, 7, '<p>Anab&oacute;lico, implante subcut&aacute;neo para bovinos y ovinos</p>\r\n'),
(4627, 339, 2, '<p>Cada implante contiene: 12 mg de Zeranol.</p>\r\n'),
(4628, 339, 1, '<p>Para mantener el promedio de ganancia de peso y mejorar la conversi&oacute;n alimenticia en bovinos (terneros al pie de la madre, terneros de recr&iacute;a, novillitos, novillos, vaquillas para engorde y vacas descarte) y ovinos (corderos, borregos, capones y ovejas descarte). El implante es compatible con otras actividades simult&aacute;neas (vacunaciones, desparasitaciones, etc.).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No aumenta el consumo de alimentos, por lo cual no hay que incrementar el &aacute;rea de pastoreo. No retiene l&iacute;quidos, disminuyendo las mermas por oreo en la res.</p>\r\n'),
(4629, 339, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 3 implantes por animal (equivalente a 36 mg de zeranol/animal).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: 1 implante por animal (equivalente a 12 mg de zeranol/animal).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Para utilizar el producto en bovinos, colocar el cartucho en la pistola dosiicadora, quitando previamente la faja de seguridad, la cual debe encontrarse intacta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Para utilizar el producto en ovinos, desarmar el cartucho, extraer 2 implantes de cada compartimento, volver a armar el cartucho y colocarlo en la pistola dosiicadora. Para utilizar las 72 dosis ovinas, esta acci&oacute;n debe repetirse dos veces m&aacute;s, dejando siempre 1 s&oacute;lo implante en cada compartimento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perforar la piel con la aguja en forma subcut&aacute;nea, en el pliegue que hace la oreja con la cabeza, cerca del borde inferior, penetrar 2,5 cm y oprimir suavemente el gatillo colocando el implante entre la piel y el cart&iacute;lago.</p>\r\n'),
(4630, 339, 8, '<p>Bovinos: 65 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: 40 d&iacute;as</p>\r\n'),
(4631, 339, 6, '<p>Caja dispensadora conteniendo 14 cartuchos con 24 dosis cada uno (336 dosis en total)</p>\r\n'),
(4632, 338, 7, '<p>Antidiarr&eacute;ico, antis&eacute;ptico, carminativo, normalizador de la flora intestinal para equinos, bovinos, ovinos, caprinos, porcinos, caninos y felinos. Suspensi&oacute;n para uso oral.</p>\r\n'),
(4633, 338, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Ftalilsulfatiazol 2,5 g; Estreptomicina Sulfato 0,5 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4634, 338, 1, '<p>Estreptocarbocaftiazol, est&aacute; indicado para ser usado en diarreas polimicrobianas de terneros, potrillos y lechones. Colibacilosis, enteritis y gastroenteritis en general de todas las especies. Infecciones alimentarias.</p>\r\n'),
(4635, 338, 3, '<p>En todas las especies 1 mL/kg p.v. por v&iacute;a oral, directamente en la boca o mezclado con el alimento.</p>\r\n'),
(4636, 338, 8, '<p>No faenar animales para consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n hasta transcurridos 12 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento. Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la utilizaci&oacute;n de la leche para consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n deben transcurrir 72 horas.</p>\r\n'),
(4637, 338, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL y 1 L.</p>\r\n'),
(4644, 340, 7, '<p>Antis&eacute;ptico, desinfectante y germicida de superficie.</p>\r\n'),
(4645, 340, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Trimetilacetilamonio bromuro, 5 g; Dimetilbencilalquilamonio Cloruro 10 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4646, 340, 1, '<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n de instrumental quir&uacute;rgico, campo quir&uacute;rgico, lesiones externas de animales y ubres en el tambo, bebederos; instalaciones, m&aacute;quinas, utensilios y supericies contra el virus de inluenza tipo A H1N1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n de materiales, dispositivos y &aacute;reas genitales en sistem&aacute;s de Inseminaci&oacute;n Artiicial, eliminando virus, bacterias y protozoarios que afectan la reproducci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4647, 340, 3, '<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n externa prequir&uacute;rgica: 1: 2.000 (1 mL en 2 L). Desinfecci&oacute;n de instrumental quir&uacute;rgico: 1: 200 (5 mL en 1 L) Desinfecci&oacute;n externa de animales y ubres en el tambo: 1: 2.000 (1 mL en 2 L). Desinfecci&oacute;n de bebederos: 1: 10.000 (1mL en 10 L) Desinfecci&oacute;n de instalaciones, m&aacute;quinas, utensilios y supericies contra el virus de inluenza tipo A H1N1: 1: 200 (5 mL en 1 L o 50 mL en 10 L). Desinfecci&oacute;n de materiales, dispositivos y &aacute;reas genitales en sistem&aacute;s de Inseminaci&oacute;n Artiicial: 1: 200 (5 mL en 1 L o 50 mL en 10 L).</p>\r\n'),
(4648, 340, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL y bidones por 5 L.</p>\r\n'),
(4649, 341, 7, '<p>Desinfectante biodegradable de amplio espectro a base de un sistema de m&uacute;ltiples componentes que act&uacute;a como oxidante de materia org&aacute;nica, para su uso en supericies, instalaciones y equipos. Activo frente a m&uacute;ltiples agentes infecciosos, incluidos bacterias Gram positivas y Gram negativas (Aerobias, anaerobias y esporas), hongos (mohos y levaduras) y virus.</p>\r\n'),
(4650, 341, 2, '<p>Cada 100 g contiene (p/p): Potasio peroximonosulfato, 54,45%; Sodio hexametafosfato, 21,05%; Potasio persulfato, 1,36%; excipientes, c.s.p 100 g.</p>\r\n'),
(4651, 341, 1, '<p>Para su uso en supericies inertes en establecimientos habilitados por SENASA. Posteriormente al uso enjuagar con abundante agua potable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bacterias: Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae, Bordetella avium, B. bronchiseptica, Burkholderia mallei, Campylobacter pyloridis, Clostridium perfringens, Dermatophilus congolensis, Escherichia coli, Histophilus somni, Klebsiella pneumonia, Moraxella bovis, Mycobacterium bovis, Mycoplasma gallisepticum, M. mycoides, Pasteurella multocida, Proteus vulgaris, Pseudomona aeruginosa, Salmonella ent&eacute;rica, Serpulina hyodysenteriae, Staphylococcus aureus, S. epidermidis, Streptococcus equi, S. pyogenes, S. suis, Taylorella equigenitalis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hongos: Aspergillus fumigatus, Candida albicans, Fusarium moniliforme, Microsporum canis, Trichopyton spp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Virus: Adenovirus bovino tipo 4, Adenovirus canino, Adenovirus del pato, Calicivirus felino, Circovirus porcino, Coronavirus canino, Herpesvirus felino, Herpesvirus del pavo, Herpesvirus equino tipo 1, Papilomavirus equino, Parvovirus canino, Parvovirus porcino, PCPV (Pseudocowpox virus), Poliomavirus bovino, Rotavirus bovino Virus de la anemia infecciosa del pollo, Virus de la anemia infecciosa del salmon, Virus de la anemia infecciosa equina, Virus de la arteritis viral equina, Virus de la Bronquitis infecciosa aviar, Virus de la diarrea viral bovina, Virus de la enfermedad de Aujeszky, Virus de la enfermedad de Gumboro, Virus de la enfermedad de Marek, Virus de la enfermedad de Newcastle, Virus de la enteritis viral del pato, Virus de la estomatitis vesicular, Virus de la iebre aftosa, Virus de la hepatitis infecciosa canina, Virus de la inluenza (gripe) aviar, Virus de la inluenza (gripe) porcina (tipo A H1N1), Virus de la inluenza (gripe) equina (tipo A), Virus de la laringotraqueitis infecciosa aviar, Virus de la necropsia pancre&aacute;tica infecciosa, Virus de la panleucopenia felina, Virus de la parainluenza canina, Virus de la peritonitis infecciosa felina, Virus de la peste equina africana, Virus de la peste porcina africana, Virus de la peste porcina cl&aacute;sica, Virus de la rinotraqueitis del pavo, Virus de la rinotraqueitis felina, Virus de la rinotraqueitis infecciosa bovina, Virus del exantema coital equino (herpesvirus equino tipo 3), Virus del moquillo (distemper) canino, Virus del s&iacute;ndrome de baja postura (adenovirus), Virus del s&iacute;ndrome reproductivo y respiratorio del cerdo (PRRSV), Virus Maedi-Visna.</p>\r\n'),
(4652, 341, 3, '<p>Preparaci&oacute;n de una soluci&oacute;n al 0,5-1,0%: Para el volumen de soluci&oacute;n a preparar, adicionar la cantidad correspondiente (seg&uacute;n tabla orientativa), y revolver hasta su completa disoluci&oacute;n, hasta obtener una soluci&oacute;n l&iacute;mpida rojiza anaranjada.</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th rowspan="2" scope="col">Agua</th>\r\n			<th colspan="2" scope="col">Soluci&oacute;n</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">0,5%</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">1%</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>5 L</td>\r\n			<td>---</td>\r\n			<td>50 g</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>10 L</td>\r\n			<td>50 g</td>\r\n			<td>100 g</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>20 L</td>\r\n			<td>100 g</td>\r\n			<td>200 g</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th rowspan="2" scope="col">Agua</th>\r\n			<th colspan="2" scope="col">Soluci&oacute;n</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">0,5%</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">1%</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>100 L</td>\r\n			<td>1 Kg</td>\r\n			<td>2 Kg</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>500 L</td>\r\n			<td>2,5 Kg</td>\r\n			<td>5 Kg</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1000 L</td>\r\n			<td>5 Kg</td>\r\n			<td>10 Kg</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Supericies: Saturar las supericies con una soluci&oacute;n al 1%, dejar actuar durante 10 minutos. A modo orientativo, se deber&aacute; utilizar 1 L de soluci&oacute;n cada 3 m2. El producto es aplicable sobre supericies de: acero inoxidable, porcelana, pl&aacute;stico, poliuretano, polipropileno, azulejos, lin&oacute;leo, vinilo, cemento, asfalto, madera, concreto, vidrio; en diversas instalaciones: granjas av&iacute;colas, granjas porcinas, haras e hip&oacute;dromos, caba&ntilde;as ovinas, plantas de incubaci&oacute;n, criaderos en general, pensiones caninas y felinas, parques zool&oacute;gicos, acuarios y piscifactor&iacute;as, cl&iacute;nicas veterinarias, salas de inseminaci&oacute;n, laboratorios. Ej: paredes, pisos y techos, mangas y corrales ganaderos, comederos y bebederos, veh&iacute;culos de transporte, incubadoras, jaulas, camillas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instrumental quir&uacute;rgico: Sumergir completamente en una soluci&oacute;n al 1% durante 10 minutos. No exceder el tiempo de contacto indicado.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ambientes: Aspersora de mochila: pulverizar una soluci&oacute;n al 0,5%. Nebulizadores o microdifusores: pulverizar una soluci&oacute;n al 1%. Aplicar aproximadamente 1L de soluci&oacute;n cada 10 m2 de supericie. Vent&iacute;lese adecuadamente por tres horas antes de reingresar al recinto. No apto para su uso por aspersi&oacute;n, nebulizaci&oacute;n y microdifusi&oacute;n en mataderos, frigor&iacute;icos y plantas procesadoras.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tanques y sistemas de distribuci&oacute;n de agua: Vaciar y aislar el sistema. Llenar el tanque con una soluci&oacute;n al 0,5% y dejar actuar por 10 minutos. Abrir la entrada al sistema y dejar que la soluci&oacute;n permanezca en las tuber&iacute;as por 30 minutos antes de drenarla.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pediluvios y rodaluvios: Saturar con una soluci&oacute;n al 1%. Reponer cada 4 d&iacute;as la soluci&oacute;n preparada o cuando la soluci&oacute;n contenga gran densidad de restos de suelo.</p>\r\n'),
(4653, 341, 16, '<p>Duraci&oacute;n m&aacute;xima de uso de la soluci&oacute;n luego de preparada: 7 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Almacenar en contenedores de pl&aacute;stico o vidrio cerrados, a temperatura ambiente y al resguardo de la luz directa.</p>\r\n'),
(4654, 220, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de la leptospirosis en bovinos&nbsp;y porcinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4655, 220, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n acuosa inactivada de serovares&nbsp;de Leptospira interrogans: Canicola canicola,&nbsp;Icterohaemorrhagiae copenhageni, Grippotyphosa&nbsp;grippotyphosa, Pomona pomona, Sejroe hardjo,&nbsp;Australis bratislava y Tarassovi tarassovi.</p>\r\n'),
(4656, 220, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 5 mL v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea por delante&nbsp;o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.&nbsp;Porcinos: 3 mL v&iacute;a intramuscular profunda en el pescuezo&nbsp;detr&aacute;s de la oreja.</p>\r\n'),
(4657, 220, 4, '<p>Bovinos: Terneros: Primera dosis: 4 meses de vida.&nbsp;Segunda dosis: 5 meses de vida. Se sugiere revacunar<br />\r\n6 meses posteriores a la &uacute;ltima aplicaci&oacute;n.&nbsp;Vacas-Vaquillonas y toros sin vacunaci&oacute;n previa:&nbsp;Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as previos al servicio. Segunda dosis:&nbsp;30 d&iacute;as previos al servicio. Otras categor&iacute;as: 1 dosis&nbsp;de refuerzo anual. Se sugiere aplicar una dosis de refuerzo&nbsp;a las hembras pre&ntilde;adas al momento del tacto.<br />\r\nPorcinos: Cachorras al primer servicio: Primera dosis:&nbsp;60 d&iacute;as antes del servicio. Segunda dosis: 30 d&iacute;as antes<br />\r\ndel servicio. Cerdas madres (revacunaci&oacute;n): 10 a 15 d&iacute;as&nbsp;del inicio de la lactancia. Padrillos sin vacunaci&oacute;n previa:&nbsp;Dos dosis con 30 d&iacute;as de intervalo.&nbsp;Padrillos (revacunaci&oacute;n): 1 dosis cada 6 meses.</p>\r\n'),
(4658, 220, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.&nbsp;No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4659, 220, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4660, 222, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de cuadros de Mancha,&nbsp;Gangrena y Enterotoxemia en bovinos, ovinos y caprinos,&nbsp;producidos por los microorganismos incluidos&nbsp;en la composici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4661, 222, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n de bacterinas y toxoides de Clostridium&nbsp;chauvoei, Clostridium septicum y toxoide de Clostridium&nbsp;perfringens tipo D en veh&iacute;culo acuoso.</p>\r\n'),
(4662, 222, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 2 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la tabla&nbsp;del cuello o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.&nbsp;Ovinos y caprinos: 2 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea,&nbsp;en la axila o en el pliegue inguinal.</p>\r\n'),
(4663, 222, 4, '<p>Primovacunaci&oacute;n (cualquier categor&iacute;a que recibe&nbsp;esta vacuna por primera vez): 2 dosis con intervalo&nbsp;de 21 a 35 d&iacute;as. Terneros de madres vacunadas:&nbsp;Primera dosis a los 2 meses de vida. Segunda dosis&nbsp;a los 3 meses de vida. Revacunar al destete.&nbsp;Revacunaci&oacute;n: una dosis anual; se sugiere en zonas&nbsp;de alta incidencia vacunar cada 6 meses.&nbsp;Corderos/cabritos de madres vacunadas:&nbsp;Primera dosis a los 2 meses de vida. Segunda dosis&nbsp;a los 3 meses de vida. Revacunaci&oacute;n: una dosis anual;&nbsp;se sugiere en zonas de alta incidencia vacunar cada<br />\r\n6 meses. Terneros/corderos/cabritos de madres&nbsp;no vacunadas: Primera dosis a las 4 semanas de vida.<br />\r\nSegunda dosis a las 7 semanas de vida. Revacunar&nbsp;al destete. Revacunaci&oacute;n: una dosis anual; se sugiere<br />\r\nen zonas de alta incidencia vacunar cada 6 meses.&nbsp;Majada general (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis&nbsp;a los 45 d&iacute;as previos al descole, castraci&oacute;n y/o esquila.&nbsp;Segunda dosis a los 15 d&iacute;as previos al descole, castraci&oacute;n&nbsp;y/o esquila. Animales que cambian su alimentaci&oacute;n&nbsp;(Revacunaci&oacute;n): 15 d&iacute;as previos al cambio.</p>\r\n'),
(4664, 222, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.&nbsp;No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4665, 222, 6, '<p>Frascos de 120 y 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4666, 223, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de cuadros de Mancha&nbsp;y Gangrena gaseosa producidas por Clostridium chauvoei<br />\r\ny C. septicum, y Enterotoxemias producidas por C.&nbsp;perfringens tipos C y D. Contribuye a la prevenci&oacute;n&nbsp;de cuadros ent&eacute;ricos o sist&eacute;micos producidos por toxinas&nbsp;de bacterias Gram negativas. Para bovinos, ovinos&nbsp;y caprinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4667, 223, 2, '<p>Cepas de Clostridium chauvoei, Clostridium septicum,&nbsp;Clostridium perfringens tipos C y D y Escherichia coli&nbsp;J5 inactivadas con formaldeh&iacute;do y absorbidas en hidr&oacute;xido&nbsp;de aluminio.</p>\r\n'),
(4668, 223, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 5 mL v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la tabla del cuello&nbsp;o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.&nbsp;Ovinos y caprinos: 2 mL v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la axila&nbsp;o en el pliegue inguinal.</p>\r\n'),
(4669, 223, 4, '<p>Bovinos: Terneros/as: primera dosis a los 2 meses&nbsp;de vida. Segunda dosis a los 3 meses de vida (antes&nbsp;de la marcaci&oacute;n). Invernada: 15 d&iacute;as antes del destete&nbsp;y antes de la &eacute;poca de incidencia (oto&ntilde;o y primavera).&nbsp;Transportes (remates, ferias): 15 d&iacute;as antes&nbsp;del transporte. Vacas y vaquillonas: primera dosis,&nbsp;3 meses antes del parto. Segunda dosis, 2 meses&nbsp;antes del parto.&nbsp;Ovinos y caprinos: Corderos/as y chivitos/as: 15 d&iacute;as&nbsp;antes del descole, se&ntilde;alada, castraci&oacute;n, esquila. Borregas,&nbsp;ovejas y cabras pre&ntilde;adas: 1 mes antes del parto. Majada&nbsp;general y carneros, chivos/castrones: 15 a 30 d&iacute;as antes&nbsp;de la esquila. En animales&nbsp;ya inmunizados se recomienda aplicar una dosis anual&nbsp;de refuerzo.</p>\r\n'),
(4670, 223, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.&nbsp;No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4671, 223, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4672, 225, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n del S&iacute;ndrome Respiratorio&nbsp;en bovinos (Complejo de enfermedades respiratorias/&nbsp;Fiebre del Transporte/ Neumon&iacute;a) y cuadros reproductivos,&nbsp;neurol&oacute;gicos y ent&eacute;ricos asociados a la acci&oacute;n individual&nbsp;o combinada de los virus y bacterias presentes&nbsp;en la composici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4673, 225, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n acuosa inactivada de Herpesvirus Bovino&nbsp;(BoHV) tipos 1 y 5, virus de la Diarrea Viral Bovina (BVDV)<br />\r\ntipos 1 y 2, virus de Parainfluenza 3 (PI3), Pasteurella&nbsp;multocida, Mannheimia haemolytica&nbsp;e Histophilus somni.</p>\r\n'),
(4674, 225, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 5 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(4675, 225, 4, '<p>Primovacunaci&oacute;n (cualquier categor&iacute;a que recibe&nbsp;esta vacuna por primera vez): 2 dosis con intervalo de&nbsp;21 a 35 d&iacute;as. Terneros de madres vacunadas: Primera&nbsp;dosis: 3 meses de edad. Segunda dosis: 4 meses&nbsp;de edad. Revacunar 15 d&iacute;a previos al destete. Continuar&nbsp;con una dosis anual de refuerzo.&nbsp;Animales transportados (primovacunaci&oacute;n):&nbsp;Primera dosis: 45 d&iacute;as antes del transporte. Segunda&nbsp;dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.<br />\r\nAnimales transportados (revacunaci&oacute;n):&nbsp;15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.&nbsp;Animales que ingresan a invernada o feedlot:&nbsp;Vacunar al ingreso; sin antecedentes de vacunaci&oacute;n&nbsp;previa revacunar a los 15-21 d&iacute;as.&nbsp;Vacas y vaquillonas gestantes:&nbsp;Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as antes del parto. Segunda dosis:&nbsp;30 d&iacute;as antes del parto.</p>\r\n'),
(4676, 225, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.&nbsp;No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4677, 225, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4683, 238, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n del Carbunclo Bacteridiano&nbsp;en bovinos, ovinos, porcinos, caprinos y equinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4684, 238, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: 900 millones de esporos&nbsp;no capsulados avirulentos de Bacillus anthracis,&nbsp;cepa 34 F2 Sterne, excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4685, 238, 3, '<p>Bovinos y equinos: 2 mL&nbsp;Porcinos, ovinos y caprinos: 1mL&nbsp;V&iacute;a: subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(4686, 238, 19, '<p>Primovacunaci&oacute;n: Se debe vacunar a todo bovino&nbsp;mayor de 3 meses de vida. La vacunaci&oacute;n&nbsp;de ovinos, caprinos y porcinos debe ser considerada&nbsp;al convivir con los rodeos de bovinos donde se manifiestan&nbsp;los casos de carbunclo, vacunando s&oacute;lo a los adultos.&nbsp;Vacunaciones siguientes: Revacunar a los 6 (seis)&nbsp;meses o 12 (doce) meses seg&uacute;n la prevalencia&nbsp;de la enfermedad en el establecimiento. Para casos&nbsp;de los llamados &ldquo;campos malditos&rdquo; (alta infecci&oacute;n tel&uacute;rica),&nbsp;la revacunaci&oacute;n debe ser repetida a los 6 meses.&nbsp;La fecha de vacunaci&oacute;n debe ser estrat&eacute;gica en relaci&oacute;n&nbsp;a la mayor casu&iacute;stica que ocurre en verano; se recomienda&nbsp;por ende la vacunaci&oacute;n en primavera.</p>\r\n'),
(4687, 238, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.&nbsp;No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4688, 238, 6, '<p>Frascos de 100 y 200 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4689, 240, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo en soluci&oacute;n oral para&nbsp;bovinos y ovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4690, 240, 2, '<p>Closantel (N-[5-cloro-4 (4 clorofenil) cianometil-2&nbsp;metilfenil]-2 hidroxi-3,5 diiodobenzamida), 7,5 g; agentes&nbsp;de formulaci&oacute;n, c.s.p. 100 ml.</p>\r\n'),
(4691, 240, 1, '<p>Haemonchus spp, Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum&nbsp;spp, Chabertia ovina, Gaigeria pachyscelis, Oestrus&nbsp;ovis (gusano de la nariz), Fasciola hep&aacute;tica, Dermatobia&nbsp;hominis, Cochliomyia hominivorax, C. macellaria, C.&nbsp;bezziana, Lucilia spp, Haematopinus eurysternus,&nbsp;Linognathus vituli y Solenopotes capillatus.</p>\r\n'),
(4692, 240, 3, '<p>Administrar por v&iacute;a oral.&nbsp;Lombrices gastrointestinales (Haemonchus spp,&nbsp;Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Chabertia&nbsp;ovina y Gaigeria pachyscelis): 1 ml / 7,5 kg p.v.&nbsp;(10 mg/kg). Saguayp&eacute; (Fasciola hep&aacute;tica):&nbsp;1 ml / 5 kg p.v. (15 mg/kg). Gusano de la nariz (Oestrus&nbsp;ovis): 1 ml / 5 kg p.v. (15 mg/kg). Miasis (Gusaneras)<br />\r\n(Cochliomyia hominivorax): Preventiva: 1 ml / 7,5 kg p.v.&nbsp;(10 mg/kg). Curativa: 1 ml / 5 kg p.v. (15 mg/kg) Ura<br />\r\n(Dermatobia hominis): 1 ml / 7,5 kg p.v. (10 mg/kg). Para&nbsp;controlar la URA en &eacute;pocas de incidencia (primavera hasta&nbsp;oto&ntilde;o), se aconseja repetir el tratamiento cada 30 - 45&nbsp;d&iacute;as. En infestaciones severas de piojos y/o miasis, repetir&nbsp;la dosis cada 21 d&iacute;as. Piojos chupadores:&nbsp;1 ml / 7,5 kg p.v. (10 mg / kg).</p>\r\n'),
(4693, 240, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena, deben transcurrir 30&nbsp;d&iacute;as. No usar en animales en orde&ntilde;e, cuyo destino sea el&nbsp;consumo o industrializaci&oacute;n de la leche.</p>\r\n'),
(4694, 240, 6, '<p>Frascos por 1 L.</p>\r\n'),
(4701, 243, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno de uso oral para bovinos, ovinos,&nbsp;caprinos y equinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4702, 243, 2, '<p>Fenbendazol, 10 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4703, 243, 1, '<p>Antiparasitario interno de amplio espectro adulticida,&nbsp;larvicida y ovicida indicado para el tratamiento&nbsp;de la helmintiasis de los rumiantes (bovinos, ovinos&nbsp;y caprinos) causada por vermes pertenecientes&nbsp;a los g&eacute;neros: Chabertia spp, Haemonchus spp,&nbsp;Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) spp, Trichostrongylus spp,&nbsp;Strongyloides spp, Cooperia spp, Nematodirus spp,&nbsp;Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Capilaria spp,&nbsp;Trichuris spp, Dictyocaulus spp, Moniezias spp y de los&nbsp;equinos: estrongilidios (grandes y peque&ntilde;os), Parascaris&nbsp;spp, Oxyuris spp y Strongyloides spp.</p>\r\n'),
(4704, 243, 3, '<p>V&iacute;a oral.&nbsp;Bovinos y equinos: 1 mL cada 20 kg de p.v.&nbsp;(5 mg/Kg p.v.).&nbsp;En casos de ostertagiasis inhibida: 1,5 mL cada 20 kg&nbsp;de p.v. (7,5 mg /Kg p.v.).&nbsp;En casos de teniasis: 2 mL cada 20 kg de p.v.&nbsp;Ovinos y caprinos: 1 mL cada 20 kg de p.v.&nbsp;En casos de teniasis: 2 mL cada 20 kg de p.v.</p>\r\n'),
(4705, 243, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo&nbsp;deben transcurrir 8 d&iacute;as. No usar en equinos cuando&nbsp;la carne se destine a consumo humano.&nbsp;Leche: sin restricciones.</p>\r\n'),
(4706, 243, 6, '<p>Bidones por 5 L.</p>\r\n'),
(4713, 246, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario externo pour-on para bovinos,&nbsp;ovinos y caprinos. Sus caracter&iacute;sticas son: gran poder&nbsp;de volteo, persistencia de acci&oacute;n antiparasitaria&nbsp;y repelencia, lo que otorga un alto poder residual.</p>\r\n'),
(4714, 246, 2, '<p>Cipermetrina, 5 g; Clorpirif&oacute;s, 2,5 g; But&oacute;xido&nbsp;de piperonilo (PBX), 1 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4715, 246, 1, '<p>Control y tratamiento de piojos chupadores&nbsp;(Haematopinus eurysternus; Linognathus vituli, ovillus&nbsp;y pedalis), piojos m&aacute;sticadores (Bovicola bovis&nbsp;y Damalinia ovis) y mosca de los cuernos (Haematobia&nbsp;irritans), en bovinos, ovinos y caprinos.&nbsp;Tambi&eacute;n est&aacute; indicado para combatir otros insectos&nbsp;hemat&oacute;fagos perjudiciales (mosquitos, t&aacute;banos, mosca&nbsp;brava, etc.).</p>\r\n'),
(4716, 246, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 10 mL hasta 400 kg de p.v. y 20 mL&nbsp;para animales de m&aacute;s de 400 kg de p.v. Las dosis&nbsp;se pueden modificar seg&uacute;n criterio profesional.&nbsp;Ovinos y caprinos: 1 mL cada 10 kg de p.v.&nbsp;Aplicar por derrame cut&aacute;neo dorsal (pour-on)&nbsp;con c&aacute;nula lluvia desde el encuentro al anca&nbsp;y en los flancos. Piojos: el tiempo necesario para&nbsp;la eliminaci&oacute;n parasitaria es de 4 a 6 semanas.&nbsp;En ovinos adultos, los tratamientos deben realizarse&nbsp;dentro de los 45 d&iacute;as post-esquila. Los corderos&nbsp;pueden tratarse en cualquier momento.</p>\r\n'),
(4717, 246, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo deben&nbsp;transcurrir 35 d&iacute;as. Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento&nbsp;y el orde&ntilde;e para consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n de&nbsp;la leche deben transcurrir 12 hs.</p>\r\n'),
(4718, 246, 6, '<p>Bidones dosificadores por 1 L.<br />\r\nBidones mochila por 2,5 L</p>\r\n'),
(4725, 249, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario externo formulado a base de Cipermetrina&nbsp;y Clorpirif&oacute;s. Esta combinaci&oacute;n potencia mutuamente&nbsp;el efecto de ambos principios activos dado el sinergismo&nbsp;que producen entre s&iacute; los piretroides y &oacute;rganofosforados.&nbsp;Su formulaci&oacute;n especial para aspersi&oacute;n facilita un correcto&nbsp;mojado y la adherencia de los principios activos&nbsp;a la piel de los animales. Antis&aacute;rnico, piojicida, insecticida&nbsp;y mosquicida bovino. Melofaguicida ovino.</p>\r\n'),
(4726, 249, 2, '<p>Cipermetrina, 20 g; Clorpirif&oacute;s, 50 g; excipientes, c.s.p.&nbsp;100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4727, 249, 1, '<p>Control y tratamiento de infestaciones provocadas por:&nbsp;&aacute;caros de la sarna bovina (Psoroptes communis var. bovis),&nbsp;piojos chupadores (Linognathus spp), piojos masticadores&nbsp;(Damalinia spp; Bovicola spp), mel&oacute;fagos (Melophagus&nbsp;ovinus), y una amplia gama de insectos hemat&oacute;fagos,&nbsp;moscas, t&aacute;banos, mosquitos y especialmente la mosca&nbsp;de los cuernos (Haematobia irritans).</p>\r\n'),
(4728, 249, 3, '<p>ASPERSIN&reg; se aplica en ba&ntilde;os de aspersi&oacute;n con&nbsp;bombas mec&aacute;nicas o manuales, las cuales deben&nbsp;asegurar una presi&oacute;n adecuada para permitir el correcto&nbsp;asperjado de los animales. Insecticida, mosquicida&nbsp;y melofaguicida: Se dosifica a raz&oacute;n de 1 L de&nbsp;ASPERSIN&reg; en 1200 litros de agua, equivalente al&nbsp;contenido de una tapa de ASPERSIN&reg; en 25 litros de&nbsp;agua. En caso de disponer de un sistema recuperador de&nbsp;l&iacute;quido, el&nbsp;refuerzo debe ser de 2 (dos) litros cada 1200&nbsp;litros de agua. Antis&aacute;rnico bovino: Se dosifica a raz&oacute;n&nbsp;de 1 litro de ASPERSIN&reg; en 1333 litros de agua,&nbsp;equivalente al contenido de un frasco de 250 mL en 333&nbsp;litros de agua.&nbsp;Los animales deben ser perfectamente&nbsp;mojados en toda la superficie corporal, prestando&nbsp;especial&nbsp;atenci&oacute;n a las lesiones y los pliegues de la piel.&nbsp;Se recomienda remover las costras de las lesiones&nbsp;sarnosas mediante frotaci&oacute;n con cepillo antes&nbsp;de proceder al ba&ntilde;o.Se deben aplicar dos ba&ntilde;os&nbsp;con 10 a 12 d&iacute;as de intervalo entre ambos con el objeto&nbsp;de cortar el ciclo de la enfermedad.</p>\r\n'),
(4729, 249, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo&nbsp;deben transcurrir 48 horas.&nbsp;Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y el orde&ntilde;e para consumo&nbsp;humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n de la leche deben transcurrir&nbsp;48 horas.</p>\r\n'),
(4730, 249, 6, '<p>Frascos por 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4748, 255, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario inyectable endectocida a base de Ivermectina al 3,15% p/v formulada especialmente con veh&iacute;culos que permiten obtener una acci&oacute;n sostenida y eicaz en el ganado bovino. La presencia de tres vitaminas liposolubles indispensables para el crecimiento, desarrollo y reproducci&oacute;n sumado a la larga acci&oacute;n del producto, facilita el manejo de los animales, reduciendo los movimientos del ganado, al alargar el per&iacute;odo entre un tratamiento y el siguiente</p>\r\n'),
(4749, 255, 2, '<p>Soluci&oacute;n inyectable conteniendo cada 100 mL: Ivermectina, 3,15 g; vitamina A (Palmitato), 8,85 g; vitamina D3, 0,06 g; vitamina E, 1,5 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4750, 255, 1, '<p>Tratamiento y control de parasitosis internas (gastrointestinales y pulmonares, en estad&iacute;os juveniles - adultos - estad&iacute;os inhibidos) y externas (sarna- piojos - garrapatas - ura - miasis) de los bovinos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: (Estad&iacute;os inmaduros y adultos) - Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) ostertagi (incluyendo estad&iacute;os inhibidos) - Ostertagia lyrata - Haemonchus placei - Mecistocirrus digitatus (adultos) - Trichostrongylus axei - Trichostrongylus colubriformis - Cooperia spp (inmaduros) Oesophagostomum radiatum - Nematodirus helvetianus - Nematodirus spathiger - Strongyloides papillosus - Bunostomum phlebotomum - Toxocara vitulorum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: (Estad&iacute;os inmaduros, inhibidos y adultos) - Dictyocaulus viviparus</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Miasis cut&aacute;neas: (Estad&iacute;os parasitarios) Dermatobia hominis (Ura - T&oacute;rsalo - Nuche) - Cochliomyia hominivorax (&ldquo;bichera&rdquo; &oacute; &ldquo;gusanera&rdquo;) - Hypoderma spp - Chrysomya bezziana Moscas hemat&oacute;fagas - Haematobia irritans (Ayuda en el control del ciclo biol&oacute;gico)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Piojos Chupadores: Linognathus vitulli - Haematopinus eurysternus - Solenopotes capillatus Garrapatas: Rhipicephalus microplus (Garrapata com&uacute;n del vacuno)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&Aacute;caros de la sarna: Psoroptes communis var. bovis Sarcoptes scabiei var. Bovis</p>\r\n'),
(4751, 255, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. (630 mcg/kg p.v.).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(4752, 255, 8, '<p>No sacriicar animales bovinos para consumo humano hasta haber transcurrido 122 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No utilizar en vacas cuya leche se destine a consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4753, 255, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4761, 342, 1, '<p>Inactivated vaccine indicated for prevention of Foot-and-Mouth Disease.</p>\r\n'),
(4762, 342, 2, '<p>Oil emulsion vaccine containing Foot and Mouth Disease virus typesO1 Campos, A24 Cruzeiro, A 2001, and C3 Indaial, replicated in BHK suspension cell culture and inactivated with B.E.I. Dosage and route of administration</p>\r\n'),
(4763, 342, 3, '<p>2 mL given in deep intramuscular tissue or subcutaneous tissue. Suggested vaccination schedule It must be administered according to the national Plan to Eradicate FMDV designed by SENASA</p>\r\n'),
(4764, 342, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light. Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4765, 342, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 60 and 125 doses of 2 mL</p>\r\n'),
(4766, 343, 1, '<p>Vaccine intended for the prevention of Infectious Bovine Keratoconjunctivitis caused by the individual or combined action of Bovine Herpes Virus, Moraxella bovis and Branhamella ovis.</p>\r\n'),
(4767, 343, 2, '<p>Bacterin of local strains of pileated Moraxella bovis and bacterial toxoids, bacterin of Branhamella ovis inactivated with formaldehyde and Bovine Herpes Virus (BoHV) type 1 inactivated with B.E.I in an oil suspension.</p>\r\n'),
(4768, 343, 3, '<p>3 mL in subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue.</p>\r\n'),
(4769, 343, 4, '<p>Calves: First dose: 60 days before weaning; Second dose: 30 days before weaning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other categories: First dose: 60 days before the season of IBK outbreaks; Second dose: 30 days before the season of IBK outbreaks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An annual booster dose is recommended for vaccinated animals</p>\r\n'),
(4770, 343, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light. Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4771, 343, 6, '<p>Bottles of 120 and 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4786, 344, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of bovine respiratory syndrome (respiratory disease complex/shipping fever/Pneumonia) and reproductive, nervous and enteric conditions associated to the individual or combined action of the virus and bacteria present in the composition.</p>\r\n'),
(4787, 344, 2, '<p>Inactivated aqueous suspension of Bovine Herpesvirus (BoHV) types 1 y 5, Bovine Viral Diarrhea Virus (BVDV) types 1 y 2, Parainluenza 3 virus (PI3), Pasteurella multocida, Mannheimia haemolytica and Histophilus somni.</p>\r\n'),
(4788, 344, 3, '<p>Cattle: 5 mL in subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suggested vaccination plan Primary vaccination (any category receiving this vaccine for the irst time): 2 doses at an interval of 21 to 35 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Calves born from vaccinated cows:<br />\r\nFirst dose: 3 months of age; Second dose: 4 months of age. Revaccinate 15 days before weaning. Subsequently continue with an annual booster dose.<br />\r\nTransported animals (primary vaccination): First dose: 45 days before shipment; second dose: 15 days before shipment. Transported animals (revaccination): 15 days before shipment.<br />\r\nAnimals entering pens or feedlot: Vaccination upon entering; if there is no record of prior vaccination, revaccinate after 15-21 days.<br />\r\nPregnant heifers and cows: First dose: 60 days before calving; Second dose: 30 days before calving.</p>\r\n'),
(4789, 344, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light. Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4790, 344, 6, '<p>Bottles of 125 and 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4803, 264, 7, '<p>Antibi&oacute;tico y antiinflamatorio. Soluci&oacute;n inyectable para Bovinos. Es una asociaci&oacute;n de un antibi&oacute;tico de amplio espectro (Tilmicosina) con un antiinflamatorio no esteroide (Ketoprofeno); donde la Tilmicosina act&uacute;a como un quimioter&aacute;pico, al mismo tiempo que el Ketoprofeno reduce el dolor, la inflamaci&oacute;n y la fiebre.</p>\r\n'),
(4804, 264, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Tilmicosina, 30 g; Ketoprofeno, 9 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4805, 264, 1, '<p>La acci&oacute;n combinada de los dos principios activos de la formulaci&oacute;n de MAXITYL PLATINUM permite por un lado, el tratamiento de la enfermedad respiratoria en bovinos, fundamentalmente asociada a la Fiebre del Embarque provocada por Mannheimia (Pasteurella) haemolytica, tratamiento de Piet&iacute;n (pododermatitis infecciosa), Neumon&iacute;a en terneros y el S&iacute;ndrome de QIB (Queratoconjuntivitis Infecciosa Bovina) por accion de la Tilmicosina; mientras que el aporte de Ketoprofeno alivia el dolor, reduce la fiebre y la inflamacion asociada a cualquier proceso infeccioso, mejorando el estado general del animal y recuperando el apetito.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Los agentes etiol&oacute;gicos susceptibles a MAXITYL PLATINUM son: Mannheimia (Pasterurella) haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida, Histophilus somni (Haemophilus somnus), Mycoplasma dispar, Mycoplasma bovis, Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus agalactiae, Actinomyces pyogenes, Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae, Moraxella bovis, Clostridium perfringens, Fusobacterium necrophorum.</p>\r\n'),
(4806, 264, 3, '<p>1 mL cada 30 o 60 kg de p.v., seg&uacute;n criterio del profesional actuante, equivalente a 5 a 10 mg/kg de Tilmicosina y 1,5 a 3 mg/kg de Ketoprofeno.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En general se utilizan dosis &uacute;nicas. En caso de no notar mejor&iacute;a a las 48 horas reevaluar el diagn&oacute;stico. Neumon&iacute;a: 1 mL/30 kg de p.v. Piet&iacute;n: 1 mL/60 kg de p.v.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Queratoconjuntivitis: 1 mL/60 kg de p.v. Se administra por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea en la regi&oacute;n del cuello o por detr&aacute;s de la paleta, con jeringas comunes y agujas 12/18. No utilizar jeringas autom&aacute;ticas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NO ADMINISTRAR POR V&Iacute;A ENDOVENOSA, PUES PUEDE SER FATAL</p>\r\n'),
(4807, 264, 9, '<p>Utilizar s&oacute;lo en bovinos. El uso en otras especies puede ser fatal. Manipular con precauci&oacute;n, la inyecci&oacute;n accidental puede resultar fatal para el hombre.</p>\r\n'),
(4808, 264, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo deben transcurrir 28 d&iacute;as. No usar en vacas en orde&ntilde;e cuya leche se destine a consumo y/o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4809, 264, 6, '<p>Frascos por 20 mL y 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4822, 259, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario inyectable endectocida a base de Ivermectina 3,15% p/v formulada especialmente con veh&iacute;culos que permiten obtener una acci&oacute;n sostenida y eficaz en el ganado bovino.</p>\r\n'),
(4823, 259, 2, '<p>Ivermectina, 3,15 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4824, 259, 1, '<p>Tratamiento y control de parasitosis internas (gastrointestinales y pulmonares, en estad&iacute;os juveniles - adultos - estad&iacute;os inhibidos) y externas (sarna- piojos chupadores - garrapatas - ura - miasis) de los bovinos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: Bunostomum phlebotomum (adultos, L3 y L4); Cooperia oncophora (adultos y L4); C. pectinata (adultos y L4); C. punctata (adultos y L4); Cooperia spp (adultos y L3); Haemonchus placei (adultos, L3 y L4); Mecistocirrus digitatus (adultos); Nematodirus helvetianus (adultos); N. spathiger (adultos); Oesophagostomum radiatum (adultos, L3 y L4); Ostertagia ostertagi (adultos, L3 y L4, incluyendo larvas inhibidas); O. Iyrata (adultos y L4); Strongyloides papillosus (adultos), Trichostrongylus axei (adultos y L4); T. colubriformis (adultos y L4); Toxocara vitulorum (adultos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Dictyocaulus viviparus (adultos, L4 y estad&iacute;os inhibidos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Sarna: Acariosis cut&aacute;nea producida por: Psoroptes communis var. bovis, Sarcoptes scabiei var. bovis, Chorioptes bovis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Piojos chupadores: Haematopinus eurysternus, Linognathus vituli, Solenopotes capillatus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Miasis forunculosa (ura, nuche o t&oacute;rsalo): Dermatobia hominis, Hypoderma bovis, Hypoderma lineatum. Garrapatas: Garrapata com&uacute;n del ganado bovino: Rhipicephalus microplus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Otros par&aacute;sitos donde la Ivermectina ha mostrado actividad: Parailaria bovicola (adultos); Thelazia spp (adultos); Chrisomyia bezziana.</p>\r\n'),
(4825, 259, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. (equivalente a 630 mcg/kg p.v.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En animales de m&aacute;s de 600 kg p.v. administrar a raz&oacute;n de 1 mL / 50 kg. Administrar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Para el control de la miasis: Miasis de ombligo: Aplicar una dosis en las primeras 24 hs de nacimiento. Miasis de castraci&oacute;n: Aplicar una dosis simult&aacute;neamente con la castraci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4826, 259, 8, '<p>Carne: No sacrificar animales para consumo humano hasta haber transcurrido 50 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leche: No administrar a hembras en lactancia cuya leche se destine a consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4827, 259, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4828, 267, 7, '<p>Agente luteol&iacute;tico a base de D-Cloprostenol, enanti&oacute;mero dextr&oacute;giro sint&eacute;tico de la prostaglandina F2 alfa, en soluci&oacute;n inyectable listo para usar para bovinos y porcinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4829, 267, 2, '<p>D-Cloprostenol, 7,5 mg; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4830, 267, 1, '<p>Biot&eacute;cnicas: Sincronizaci&oacute;n e inducci&oacute;n del celo en vacas y vaquillonas. Sincronizaci&oacute;n del ciclo estral en donantes y receptores de programas de transferencia embrionaria. Inducci&oacute;n al parto en cerdas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terap&eacute;uticas: Des&oacute;rdenes funcionales de los ovarios. Celos silenciosos por anestros post-servicio o post-parto. Ciclos irregulares o anovulatorios. Cuerpo l&uacute;teo persistente. Quistes l&uacute;teos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enfermedades puerperales: endometritis, pi&oacute;metras, etc. Abortos terap&eacute;uticos en el primer tercio de gestaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4831, 267, 3, '<p>La dosis a administrar se debe aplicar por v&iacute;a intramuscular a raz&oacute;n de 2 mL en bovinos y 1 mL en porcinos. En bovinos, el punto de aplicaci&oacute;n es en la tabla del cuello o el cuarto posterior, en porcinos se utiliza la tabla del cuello por detr&aacute;s de la oreja.</p>\r\n'),
(4832, 267, 8, '<p>No sacrificar animales bovinos y porcinos para consumo humano hasta haber transcurrido 24 horas del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y el destino de la leche para consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n deben transcurrir 4 horas.</p>\r\n'),
(4833, 267, 6, '<p>Frascos por 20 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4840, 260, 7, '<p>Soluci&oacute;n antibi&oacute;tica inyectable de amplio espectro para bovinos y porcinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4841, 260, 2, '<p>Ceftiofur base (como Clorhidrato), 5 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.,</p>\r\n'),
(4842, 260, 1, '<p>Control de las infecciones bacterianas m&aacute;s comunes causadas por bacterias gram negativas y positivas. Indicado para uso en bovinos de cualquier edad y tipo de producci&oacute;n, incluyendo vaquillonas y vacas en producci&oacute;n l&aacute;ctea; y en porcinos: en lechones y cerdos de engorde y cr&iacute;a.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bovinos: Tratamiento de la Enfermedad Respiratoria Bovina (BRD), Fiebre del Embarque o Neumon&iacute;a Bovina, asociada a Mannheimia (Pasteurella) haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida e Histophilus somni. Tratamiento de la necrobacilosis interdigital aguda (piet&iacute;n, &ldquo;foot-rot&rdquo; o pododermatitis) asociada a Fusobacterium necrophorum y Bacteroides melaninogenicus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: Tratamiento y control de la Enfermedad Bacteriana de los cerdos (neumon&iacute;a) asociada con Pasteurella multocida, Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae y Streptococcus suis Tipo 2. Eicaz frente a infecciones por Escherichia coli, Salmonella typhimurium, Haemophilus pleuropneumoniae, Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus agalactiae, S. dysgalactiae, S. uberis y S. bovis.</p>\r\n'),
(4843, 260, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 1 a 2 mL cada 50 kg de p.v por v&iacute;a intramuscular o subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: 0,5 a 1 mL cada 10 kg de p.v por v&iacute;a intramuscular profunda exclusivamente.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En ambas especies se debe repetir la dosis cada 24 horas durante 3 d&iacute;as como m&iacute;nimo. Queda a criterio del profesional actuante prolongar los tratamientos.</p>\r\n'),
(4844, 260, 8, '<p>No posee per&iacute;odo de retiro para faena o consumo de leche.</p>\r\n'),
(4845, 260, 6, '<p>Frascos por 30 y 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4846, 262, 2, '<p>Florfenicol, 30 g; Excipientes no acuosos, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4847, 262, 7, '<p>Antibi&oacute;tico sint&eacute;tico en soluci&oacute;n inyectable lista para usar, activo contra bacterias Gram positivas y negativas. Est&aacute; indicado para ser utilizado en bovinos y porcinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4848, 262, 1, '<p>Bovinos: Enfermedad Respiratoria Bovina (Fiebre del Embarque): Mannheimia haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida e Histophilus somni, Diarreas de los terneros (S&iacute;ndrome diarreico), Escherichia coli ET y cuadros neumoent&eacute;ricos: Corynebacterium pyogenes, Salmonella spp, Streptococcus spp, Staphilococcus spp, Klebsiella spp. Pododermatitis (Piet&iacute;n): Fusobacterium necrophorum, Bacteroides nodosus, Bacteroides melaninogenicus. Queratoconjuntivitis Infecciosa Bovina, incluyendo Moraxella spp. Infecciones del aparato genital (metritis, pi&oacute;metras y endometritis) e Infecciones en general. Porcinos: Enfermedades del tracto respiratorio (Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae), Neumon&iacute;a Enzo&oacute;tica (Haemophilus inluenzae). Rinitis Atr&oacute;ica (Pasteurella multocida, Bordetella bronchiseptica). Diarreas causadas por Escherichia coli, Salmonella spp. Infecciones del aparato genital (metritis, pi&oacute;metras) y S&iacute;ndrome de Metritis, Mastitis, Agalactia (M.M.A.).</p>\r\n'),
(4849, 262, 3, '<p>Bovinos: V&iacute;a intramuscular: 20 mg/kg de p.v. (1mL/15 kg), repetir a las 48 hs.</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Cantidad (en mL)</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Peso (en kg)</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>hasta 50</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>7</td>\r\n			<td>de 51 a 100</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>10</td>\r\n			<td>de 101 a 150</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>15</td>\r\n			<td>de 151 a 250</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n			<td>de 251 a 350</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>25</td>\r\n			<td>de 351 a 450</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>(Animales adultos, utilizar entre 30 y 40 mL; no aplicar m&aacute;s de 10 mL en cada punto de inyecci&oacute;n; repetir la dosis a las 48 hs.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>V&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea: 40 mg/kg de p.v. (2mL/15 kg), &uacute;nica dosis. No aplicar m&aacute;s de 10 mL en cada sitio de inyecci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Cantidad (en mL)</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Peso (en kg)</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>6</td>\r\n			<td>hasta 50</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>14</td>\r\n			<td>de 51 a 100</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n			<td>de 101 a 150</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>30</td>\r\n			<td>de 151 a 250</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>40</td>\r\n			<td>de 251 a 350</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>50</td>\r\n			<td>de 351 a 450</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: V&iacute;a intramuscular: 10 mg/kg de p.v. (1 mL/30 kg). Se recomienda aplicar 3 inyecciones con 24 horas de intervalo entre cada una o 15 mg/kg de p.v. (1,5 mL/30 kg p.v.), por v&iacute;a intramuscular. Aplicar dos inyecciones con intervalo de 48 horas entre cada una.</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan="2" rowspan="1" scope="col">Dosis: 10 mg/kg</th>\r\n			<th colspan="2" rowspan="1" scope="col">Dosis: 15 mg/kg</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cantidad (en mL)</td>\r\n			<td>Peso (en kg)</td>\r\n			<td>Cantidad (en mL)</td>\r\n			<td>Peso (en kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>0,5</td>\r\n			<td>15</td>\r\n			<td>0,5</td>\r\n			<td>10</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>30</td>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>60</td>\r\n			<td>1,5</td>\r\n			<td>30</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>90</td>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>60</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>120</td>\r\n			<td>6</td>\r\n			<td>120</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(4850, 262, 14, '<p>Preferentemente en la tabla del cuello, en ambas especies, cuando se aplica por v&iacute;a intramuscular. Por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea en bovinos por delante o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.</p>\r\n'),
(4851, 262, 8, '<p>Carne: Bovinos y Porcinos: 28 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leche: No utilizar en hembras lecheras en lactancia cuya leche sea destinada a consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4852, 262, 6, '<p>Se presenta en frascos de 20 y 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4853, 262, 5, '<p>Entre 4&ordm;C y 25&ordm;C.</p>\r\n'),
(4854, 345, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of bovine respiratory syndrome (respiratory disease complex/shipping fever/Pneumonia) and reproductive, nervous and enteric conditions caused by the individual or combined action of the virus and bacteria present in the composition.</p>\r\n'),
(4855, 345, 2, '<p>Oil emulsion vaccine containing strains of Bovine Herpesvirus (BoHV) types 1 and 5, Bovine Viral Diarrhea virus (BVDV) types 1 and 2, Parainluenza 3 virus (PI3) and Bovine Respiratory Syncytial Virus (BRSV) inactivated with BEI and bacterial strains of Mannheimia haemolytica (Pasteurella haemolytica), Pasteurella multocida and Histophilus somni (Haemophilus somnus) inactivated with formaldehyde.</p>\r\n'),
(4856, 345, 3, '<p>3 mL in subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue in the side of the neck or behind the shoulder blade.</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `tbl_producto_contenido` (`id`, `producto_id`, `parte`, `text`) VALUES
(4857, 345, 4, '<p>Suckling calves: First dose: 3 months of age; Second dose: 4 months of age.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Calves at the time of conventional weaning (Primary vaccination): First dose: 45 days before weaning; Second dose: 15 days before weaning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early weaning calves: First dose: 30 days before weaning. Second dose: 15 days before weaning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transported animals (primary vaccination): First dose: 30 days before shipment; second dose: 15 days before shipment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transported animals (revaccination): 15 days before shipment. Animals entering pens or feedlot (Primary vaccination): First dose: Upon entering; Second dose: 21 days after.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cows and heifers (beef herd): First dose: during the seventh month of pregnancy; Second dose: during the eighth month of pregnancy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cows and heifers (dairy herd): First dose: At dry off; Second dose: At prepartum.</p>\r\n'),
(4858, 345, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4859, 345, 6, '<p>Bottles of 120 and 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4866, 346, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of Bovine Bacillary Hemoglobinuria.</p>\r\n'),
(4867, 346, 2, '<p>Aqueous suspension of inactivated bacterin and toxoid of Clostridium haemolyticum.</p>\r\n'),
(4868, 346, 3, '<p>3 mL administered in subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n'),
(4869, 346, 4, '<p>Vaccination at 6 months. Primary immunisation: two doses with a 20 to 30 day interval between the irst and second application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Revaccination recommended every 4 months.</p>\r\n'),
(4870, 346, 5, '<p>Store between 2&deg;C and 8&deg;C, away from light. Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4871, 346, 6, '<p>Bottles of 120 and 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4872, 347, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of Blackleg, Gangrene and Enterotoxemia in cattle, sheep and goats caused by the microorganism present in its composition.</p>\r\n'),
(4873, 347, 2, '<p>Suspension of Clostridium chauvoei and Clostridium Septicum bacterins and toxoids and Clostridium perfringens type D toxoids in an aqueous carrier.</p>\r\n'),
(4874, 347, 3, '<p>Cattle: 2 mL in subcutaneous tissue, at the side of the neck or behind the shoulder blade.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep and goats: 2 mL in subcutaneous tissue in the axilla or inguinal fold.</p>\r\n'),
(4875, 347, 4, '<p>Primary immunization (for any animal category receiving this vaccine for the irst time): 2 doses at an interval of 21 to 35 days. Calves born from vaccinated cows: First dose at 2 months of age. Second dose at three months of age. Revaccinate at weaning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Revaccination: one dose per year. In areas with high incidence of clostridial diseases, vaccination every 6 months is suggested. Lambs/kids born from vaccinated ewes/does: First dose at 2 months of age; second dose at 3 months of age. Revaccination: one dose per year. In areas with high incidence of clostridial diseases, vaccination every 6 months is suggested. Calves/lambs/kids born from non-vaccinated cows/ewes/does: First dose at 4 weeks of age; second dose at 7 weeks of age. Revaccinate at weaning. Revaccination: one dose per year; In areas with high incidence of clostridial diseases, vaccination every 6 months is suggested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whole lock (irst vaccination): First dose 45 days prior to tail docking, castration and/or shearing. Second dose at 15 days prior to tail docking, castration and/or shearing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animals changing their diet (Revaccination): 15 days before changing diet.</p>\r\n'),
(4876, 347, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4877, 347, 6, '<p>Bottles of 120 and 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4887, 348, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of blackleg and gas gangrene caused by Clostridium chauvoei and C. septicum, and enterotoxemias caused by C. perfringens types C and D. It contributes to the prevention of enteric or systemic symptoms caused by toxins of gram negative bacteria. For cattle, sheep and goats.</p>\r\n'),
(4888, 348, 2, '<p>Strains of Clostridium chauvoei, Clostridium septicum, Clostridium perfringens types C and D and Escherichia coli J5, inactivated with formaldehyde and absorbed in aluminum hydroxide.</p>\r\n'),
(4889, 348, 3, '<p>Cattle: 5 mL in subcutaneous tissue, at the side of the neck or behind the shoulder blade. Sheep and goats: 2 mL in subcutaneous tissue, at the axilla or inguinal fold.</p>\r\n'),
(4890, 348, 4, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Calves: First dose at 2 months of age. Second dose at three months of age (before branding).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Feedlot: 15 days before weaning and before the season of highest incidence (autumn and spring).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animals to be transported (auctions, fairs): 15 days before transportation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cows and heifers: First dose, 3 months before calving. Second dose, 2 months before calving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep and goats: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lambs and kids: 15 days before tail docking, branding, castration and shearing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pregnant ewe lambs, ewes and does: 1 month before delivery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General herd and rams and bucks/wethers: 15 to 30 days before shearing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is recommended to apply an annual booster dose to immunized animals</p>\r\n'),
(4891, 348, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4892, 348, 6, '<p>Bottles of 125 and 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4902, 272, 7, '<p>Suplemento Vitam&iacute;nico inyectable para bovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4903, 272, 2, '<p>Vitamina A palmitato 3,5 g; Vitamina E acetato 5,0 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(4904, 272, 1, '<p>ADAPTADOR VIT es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de vitaminas A y E, indicada para ser utilizada sola o en forma conjunta con ADAPTADOR MIN, para que ambos intervengan impidiendo fundamentalmente los procesos oxidativos que se producen en los animales ante cualquier situaci&oacute;n de estr&eacute;s. Situaciones como castraciones, destetes, ingreso a feedlot, situaciones ambientales extremas (sequ&iacute;a &ndash; inundaci&oacute;n). Las vitaminas junto a los microelementos, macroelementos y la energ&iacute;a aportada por la dieta (forrajes y granos), son requerimientos diarios que necesita el animal y aunque &eacute;stos var&iacute;an en sus aportes desde miligramos a kilogramos, todos tienen el mismo valor y un desbalance entre los mismos provocar&aacute; deficiencias que afectan al animal. Los microelementos de ADAPTADOR MIN y las vitaminas de ADAPTADOR VIT, son en forma conjunta o aislada factores esenciales para la defensa antioxidante del organismo.</p>\r\n'),
(4905, 272, 3, '<p>Terneros: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v., desde la primera semana de vida hasta el destete. Novillos: 4 mL al comienzo del per&iacute;odo de engorde, 1 aplicaci&oacute;n cada 3 meses. Vaquillonas: 4 mL durante la recr&iacute;a cada 3 meses, y antes del servicio. Vacas: 5 mL, 1 a 2 meses antes del servicio y 1 a 2 meses antes de la parici&oacute;n. Toros: 6 mL, 1 a 2 meses antes de comenzar el servicio, y durante el mismo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con agujas 12 x 18.</p>\r\n'),
(4906, 272, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(4907, 272, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kit compuesto por 1 frasco de ADAPTADOR MIN por 500 mL y 1 frasco de ADAPTADOR VIT por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4920, 349, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of the following diseases in cattle and sheep caused by Clostridium: blackleg, gas gangrene, enterotoxemia, infectious necrotic hepatitis, bacillary hemoglobinuria and sudden death. Prevention of endotoxemia symptoms produced by Gram negative bacteria.</p>\r\n'),
(4921, 349, 2, '<p>Inactivated aqueous suspension of bacterins and toxoids of Clostridium chauvoei, Clostridium septicum, Clostridium sordelli, Clostridium perfringens types C and D, Clostridium novyi and Clostridium haemolyticum combined with Escherichia coli J5 bacterin. The combination of toxoids of Clostridium perfringens type C and toxoid of Clostridium perfringens type D afford protection against Clostridium perfringens type B.</p>\r\n'),
(4922, 349, 3, '<p>Cattle: 5 mL in subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep: 3 mL in subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n'),
(4923, 349, 4, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suckling calves: First dose: at 2 months of age. Second dose: at 3 months of age. Calves before weaning (primary vaccination): First dose: 45 days before weaning. Second dose: 15 days before weaning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animals to be transported (shows, auctions, fairs): 15 days before transportation. Animals changing their diet (Feedlot or pens): 15 days before entering the pens.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lambs: First dose: 2 months of age, Second dose: 3 months of age.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ewe lambs and ewes: 30 days before delivery. General herd: 15 days before tail docking, castration and/ or shearing. Changes in diet, going to fresh pasture. An annual booster dose is recommended for vaccinated adult animals. Vaccination every 6 months is recommended for areas with high incidence of Clostridium novyi and Clostridium haemolyticum. Revaccination is recommended in the event of infestation of gastrointestinal parasites.</p>\r\n'),
(4924, 349, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light. Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4925, 349, 6, '<p>Bottles of 125 and 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4944, 350, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of Leptospirosis in cattle and swine.</p>\r\n'),
(4945, 350, 2, '<p>Inactivated aqueous suspension containing Leptospira interrogans serovars: Canicola canicola, Icterohaemorrhagiae copenhageni, Grippotyphosa grippotyphosa, Pomona pomona, Sejroe hardjo, Australis bratislava and Tarassovi tarassovi.</p>\r\n'),
(4946, 350, 3, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>5 mL in subcutaneous tissue in front of or behind the shoulder blade. 3 mL in deep intramuscular tissue in the neck behind the ear. Suggested vaccination plan Cattle:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Calves: First dose to be applied at 4 months of age. Second dose to be applied at 5 months of age. It is suggested to revaccinate 6 months after last application.</li>\r\n	<li>Cows-Heifers and bulls: primary vaccination: First dose: 60 days before mating; Second dose: 30 days before mating.</li>\r\n	<li>Other categories: 1 booster dose per year. A booster dose for pregnant cows and heifers at the time of rectal examination is suggested.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Swine: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gilts at irst mating: First dose: 60 days before mating; second dose: 30 days before mating.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sows (revaccination): 10 to 15 days before commencing lactation. oars (primary vaccination): Two doses at a 30-day interval.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Boars (revaccination): 1 dose every 6 months.</p>\r\n'),
(4947, 350, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4948, 350, 6, '<p>Bottles of 125 and 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4949, 278, 7, '<p>Antidiarr&eacute;ico, antis&eacute;ptico, carminativo, normalizador de la flora intestinal para equinos, bovinos, ovinos, caprinos, porcinos, caninos y felinos. Suspensi&oacute;n para uso oral.</p>\r\n'),
(4950, 278, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Ftalilsulfatiazol 2,5 g; Estreptomicina Sulfato 0,5 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4951, 278, 1, '<p>Estreptocarbocaftiazol, est&aacute; indicado para ser usado en diarreas polimicrobianas de terneros, potrillos y lechones. Colibacilosis, enteritis y gastroenteritis en general de todas las especies. Infecciones alimentarias.</p>\r\n'),
(4952, 278, 3, '<p>En todas las especies 1 mL/kg p.v. por v&iacute;a oral, directamente en la boca o mezclado con el alimento.</p>\r\n'),
(4953, 278, 8, '<p>No faenar animales para consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n hasta transcurridos 12 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento. Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la utilizaci&oacute;n de la leche para consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n deben transcurrir 72 horas.</p>\r\n'),
(4954, 278, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL y 1 L.</p>\r\n'),
(4955, 280, 7, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de la queratoconjuntivitis infecciosa bovina producida por la acci&oacute;n individual o combinada de Herpesvirus bovino, Moraxella bovis y Branhamella ovis.</p>\r\n'),
(4956, 280, 2, '<p>Bacterina de cepas aut&oacute;ctonas de Moraxella bovis piliadas y toxoide bacteriano, bacterina de Branhamella ovis inactivadas con formaldeh&iacute;do, y Herpesvirus bovino (BoHV) tipo 1 inactivado con B.E.I. en veh&iacute;culo oleoso.</p>\r\n'),
(4957, 280, 3, '<p>3 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea o intramuscular.</p>\r\n'),
(4958, 280, 4, '<p>Terneros:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as previos al destete;</li>\r\n	<li>Segunda dosis: 30 d&iacute;as previos al destete.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Otras categor&iacute;as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as previos a la presentaci&oacute;n habitual de los cuadros de Queratoconjuntivitis;</li>\r\n	<li>Segunda dosis: 30 d&iacute;as previos a la presentaci&oacute;n habitual de los cuadros de Queratoconjuntivitis.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>En animales inmunizados, se recomienda aplicar una dosis anual de refuerzo.</p>\r\n'),
(4959, 280, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz. No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4960, 280, 6, '<p>Frascos de 120 y 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4961, 351, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of infertility and abortions in cattle caused by the microorganisms present in its composition.</p>\r\n'),
(4962, 351, 2, '<p>Inactivated aqueous suspension of Bovine Herpesvirus (BoHV) type-1, Bovine Viral Diarrhea Virus (BVDV) types 1 and 2 and bacterial strains of Campylobacter fetus fetus, Campylobacter fetus venerealis, Histophilus somni and Leptospira interrogans Pomona pomona.</p>\r\n'),
(4963, 351, 3, '<p>5 mL in subcutaneous tissue at the side of the neck or behind the shoulder blade.</p>\r\n'),
(4964, 351, 4, '<p>Primary vaccination (any category receiving this vaccine for the irst time): 2 doses at an interval of 21 to 35 days. Beef cattle: Bulls and heifers: First dose: 60 days before mating or artiicial insemination (A.I.); Second dose: 30 days before mating or artiicial insemination (A.I.). Cows (revaccination): 30 days before mating or artiicial insemination (A.I.). Dairy cattle: Heifers: First dose: 60 days before mating or Artiicial Insemination (A.I.); Second dose: 30 days before mating or artiicial insemination (A.I.). Cows and bulls: one dose every 6 months. In the case of cows and heifers in beef and dairy herds with high losses during the period between rectal examination and calving, it is suggested to apply one dose at the time of rectal examination.</p>\r\n'),
(4965, 351, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4966, 351, 6, '<p>Bottles of 125 and 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4967, 281, 7, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n del S&iacute;ndrome Respiratorio en bovinos (Complejo de enfermedades respiratorias/ Fiebre del Transporte/ Neumon&iacute;a) y cuadros reproductivos, neurol&oacute;gicos y ent&eacute;ricos asociados a la acci&oacute;n individual o combinada de los virus y bacterias presentes en la composici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4968, 281, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n acuosa inactivada de Herpesvirus Bovino (BoHV) tipos 1 y 5, virus de la Diarrea Viral Bovina (BVDV) tipos 1 y 2, virus de Parainluenza 3 (PI3), Pasteurella multocida, Mannheimia haemolytica e Histophilus somni.</p>\r\n'),
(4969, 281, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 5 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(4970, 281, 4, '<p>Primovacunaci&oacute;n (cualquier categor&iacute;a que recibe esta vacuna por primera vez): 2 dosis con intervalo de 21 a 35 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros de madres vacunadas: Primera dosis: 3 meses de edad; Segunda dosis: 4 meses de edad. Revacunar 15 d&iacute;a previos al destete. Continuar con una dosis anual de refuerzo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales transportados (primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis: 45 d&iacute;as antes del transporte; segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales transportados (revacunaci&oacute;n): 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales que ingresan a invernada o feedlot: Vacunar al ingreso; sin antecedentes de vacunaci&oacute;n previa revacunar a los 15-21 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vacas y vaquillonas gestantes: Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as antes del parto; Segunda dosis: 30 d&iacute;as antes del parto.</p>\r\n'),
(4971, 281, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz. No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4972, 281, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4973, 352, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of neonatal Calf Diarrhea syndrome caused by Bovine Rotavirus and Gram negative bacteria; endotoxemias secondary to Gram Negative Bacterial infections and coliform mastitis in dairy cattle</p>\r\n'),
(4974, 352, 2, '<p>Inactivated oil emulsion of Bovine Rotavirus (serotypes 6 and 10) and Escherichia coli J5.</p>\r\n'),
(4975, 352, 3, '<p>3 mL in subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue in the neck or behind the shoulder blade.</p>\r\n'),
(4976, 352, 4, '<p>Primary vaccination (any category receiving this vaccine for the irst time): 2 doses at an interval of 21-35 days. Beef herds: Cows and heifers (primary vaccination): First dose: 7th month of pregnancy; Second dose: 8th month of pregnancy. Cows and heifers (revaccination): Administer one dose during the 8th month of pregnancy. In areas with high incidence of diarrhea outbreaks it is suggested to revaccinate with a third dose to late calving cows. Dairy cattle: Cows and heifers (primary vaccination): First dose: 7th month of pregnancy; Second dose: 8th month of pregnancy. Cows and heifers (revaccination): First dose: at dry off; Second dose: prepartum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the prevention of coliform mastitis it is recommended to administer a third dose at calving.</p>\r\n'),
(4977, 352, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light. Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(4978, 352, 6, '<p>Bottles of 120 and 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4979, 282, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n del s&iacute;ndrome respiratorio de los bovinos (Complejo de enfermedades respiratorias/ Fiebre del transporte/Neumon&iacute;a) y cuadros reproductivos, nerviosos y ent&eacute;ricos provocados por la acci&oacute;n individual o combinada de los virus y bacterias presentes en la composici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4980, 282, 2, '<p>Cepas de Herpesvirus Bovino (BoHV) tipos 1 y 5, virus de la Diarrea Viral Bovina (BVDV) tipos 1 y 2, virus de Parainluenza 3 (PI3) y virus Sincicial Respiratorio Bovino (BRSV) inactivados con BEI y cepas bacterianas de Mannheimia haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida e Histophilus somni inactivadas con formaldeh&iacute;do y emulsionadas en adyuvante oleoso.</p>\r\n'),
(4981, 282, 3, '<p>3 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea o intramuscular en la tabla del cuello o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.</p>\r\n'),
(4982, 282, 4, '<p>Terneros al pie: Primera dosis: 3 meses de edad; Segunda dosis: 4 meses de edad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros de destete convencional (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis: 45 d&iacute;as antes del destete; Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del destete.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros de destete precoz: Primera dosis: 30 d&iacute;as antes del destete. Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del destete.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales transportados (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis: 30 d&iacute;as antes del transporte; Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales transportados (Revacunaci&oacute;n): 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales que ingresan a invernada o feedlot (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis: Al ingreso; Segunda dosis: 21 d&iacute;as despu&eacute;s.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vacas y vaquillonas (rodeo de cr&iacute;a): Primera dosis: s&eacute;ptimo mes de pre&ntilde;ez; Segunda dosis: octavo mes de pre&ntilde;ez.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vacas y vaquillonas (tambo): Primera dosis: Al secado; Segunda dosis: Al preparto.</p>\r\n'),
(4983, 282, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4984, 282, 6, '<p>Frascos de 120 y 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4985, 283, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de la Hemoglobinuria Bacilar en bovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4986, 283, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n acuosa inactivada de bacterina y toxoide de Clostridium haemolyticum.</p>\r\n'),
(4987, 283, 3, '<p>3 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(4988, 283, 4, '<p>Vacunar a partir de los 6 meses de edad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Primovacunaci&oacute;n: dos dosis con 20 a 30 d&iacute;as de intervalo entre la primera y la segunda aplicaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Se recomienda la revacunaci&oacute;n cada 4 meses.</p>\r\n'),
(4989, 283, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2&deg;C y 8&deg;C, al resguardo de la luz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4990, 283, 6, '<p>Frascos de 120 y 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4991, 284, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de cuadros de Mancha, Gangrena y Enterotoxemia en bovinos, ovinos y caprinos, producidos por los microorganismos incluidos en la composici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(4992, 284, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n de bacterinas y toxoides de Clostridium chauvoei, Clostridium septicum; toxoide de Clostridium perfringens tipo D en veh&iacute;culo acuoso.</p>\r\n'),
(4993, 284, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 2 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la tabla del cuello o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos y caprinos: 2 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la axila o en el pliegue inguinal.</p>\r\n'),
(4994, 284, 4, '<p>Primovacunaci&oacute;n (cualquier categor&iacute;a que recibe esta vacuna por primera vez): 2 dosis con intervalo de 21 a 35 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros de madres vacunadas: Primera dosis a los 2 meses de vida. Segunda dosis a los 3 meses de vida. Revacunar al destete. Revacunaci&oacute;n: una dosis anual; se sugiere en zonas de alta incidencia vacunar cada 6 meses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Corderos/cabritos de madres vacunadas: Primera dosis a los 2 meses de vida; segunda dosis a los 3 meses de vida. Revacunaci&oacute;n: una dosis anual; se sugiere en zonas de alta incidencia vacunar cada 6 meses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros/corderos/cabritos de madres no vacunadas: Primera dosis a las 4 semanas de vida; segunda dosis a las 7 semanas de vida. Revacunar al destete. Revacunaci&oacute;n: una dosis anual; se sugiere en zonas de alta incidencia vacunar cada 6 meses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Majada general (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis a los 45 d&iacute;as previos al descole, castraci&oacute;n y/o esquila. Segunda dosis a los 15 d&iacute;as previos al descole, castraci&oacute;n y/o esquila.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales que cambian su alimentaci&oacute;n (Revacunaci&oacute;n): 15 d&iacute;as previos al cambio.</p>\r\n'),
(4995, 284, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(4996, 284, 6, '<p>Frascos de 120 y 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(4997, 285, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de cuadros de mancha y gangrena gaseosa producidas por Clostridium chauvoei y C. septicum, y enterotoxemias producidas por C. perfringens tipos C y D. Contribuye a la prevenci&oacute;n de cuadros ent&eacute;ricos o sist&eacute;micos producidos por toxinas de bacterias Gram negativas. Para bovinos, ovinos y caprinos.</p>\r\n'),
(4998, 285, 2, '<p>Cepas de Clostridium chauvoei, Clostridium septicum; Clostridium perfringens tipos C y D, y Escherichia coli J5 inactivadas con formaldeh&iacute;do y absorbidas en hidr&oacute;xido de aluminio.</p>\r\n'),
(4999, 285, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 5 mL v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la tabla del cuello o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos y caprinos: 2 mL v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la axila o en el pliegue inguinal.</p>\r\n'),
(5000, 285, 4, '<p>Bovinos: Terneros/as: primera dosis a los 2 meses de vida. Segunda dosis a los 3 meses de vida (antes de la marcaci&oacute;n).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Invernada: 15 d&iacute;as antes del destete y antes de la &eacute;poca de incidencia (oto&ntilde;o y primavera).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Transportes (remates, ferias): 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vacas y vaquillonas: primera dosis, 3 meses antes del parto. Segunda dosis, 2 meses antes del parto.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos y caprinos: Corderos/as y chivitos/as: 15 d&iacute;as antes del descole, se&ntilde;alada, castraci&oacute;n, esquila.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Borregas, ovejas y cabras pre&ntilde;adas: 1 mes antes del parto. Majada general y carneros, chivos/ castrones: 15 a 30 d&iacute;as antes de la esquila.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En animales ya inmunizados se recomienda aplicar una dosis anual de refuerzo.</p>\r\n'),
(5001, 285, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(5002, 285, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5003, 353, 1, '<p>Vaccine for the prevention of bacterial Carbuncle in cattle, sheep, swine, goats and horses.</p>\r\n'),
(5004, 353, 2, '<p>Every 100 mL contains: 900 million of avirulent, non-encapsulated spores of Bacillus anthracis, Sterne strain 34 F2, excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5005, 353, 3, '<p>Cattle and horses: 2 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Swine, sheep and goats: 1mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Route: Subcutaneous injection.</p>\r\n'),
(5006, 353, 4, '<p>Primary vaccination: All animals older than 3 (three) months must be vaccinated. Vaccination of sheep, goats and swine exposed to cattle presenting carbuncle must be considered; vaccinating only adult animals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Following vaccinations: Revaccinate at 6 (six) month or 12 (twelve) month intervals according to disease prevalence on the premises. For the so-called &ldquo;accursed ields&rdquo; (high telluric contamination), revaccination must be repeated at 6 month intervals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vaccination must be strategically timed with the season of highest incidence of outbreaks, which is summer; therefore, vaccination should be in spring.</p>\r\n'),
(5007, 353, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(5008, 353, 6, '<p>Bottles of 100 and 200 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5009, 286, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de las siguientes enfermedades en bovinos y ovinos causadas por Clostridios: mancha, gangrena gaseosa, enterotoxemia, hepatitis necr&oacute;tica infecciosa, hemoglobinuria bacilar y muerte s&uacute;bita. Prevenci&oacute;n de cuadros de endotoxemia producidos por bacterias Gram negativas.</p>\r\n'),
(5010, 286, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n acuosa inactivada de bacterinas y toxoides de Clostridium chauvoei, Clostridium septicum, Clostridium sordelli; Clostridium perfringens tipo C y D, Clostridium novyi y Clostridium haemolyticum combinados con bacterina de Escherichia coli J5. La combinaci&oacute;n de toxoide de Clostridium perfringens tipo C y Toxoide de Clostridium perfringens tipo D, coniere protecci&oacute;n contra Clostridium perfringens tipo B.</p>\r\n'),
(5011, 286, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 5 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: 3 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(5012, 286, 4, '<p>Bovinos: Terneros/as al pie de la madre: Primera dosis: 2 meses de edad. Segunda dosis: 3 meses de edad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros pre-destete (primovacunaci&oacute;n): Primera dosis: 45 d&iacute;as previos al destete. Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as previos al destete.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales transportados (Exposiciones, remates, ferias): 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Animales que cambian su alimentaci&oacute;n (Feedlot o corrales): 15 d&iacute;as antes del ingreso a corrales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: Corderos: Primera dosis: 2 meses de edad, Segunda dosis: 3 meses de edad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Borregas y ovejas: 30 d&iacute;as antes del parto.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Majada general: 15 d&iacute;as previos al descole, castraci&oacute;n y/o esquila.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ingreso a verdeos o cambios de alimentaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En animales adultos vacunados se recomienda una dosis anual de refuerzo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En zonas de alta incidencia de Clostridium novyi y Clostridium haemolyticum se recomienda la vacunaci&oacute;n cada 6 meses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Se aconseja la revacunaci&oacute;n ante cuadros de parasitosis gastrointestinales.</p>\r\n'),
(5013, 286, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(5014, 286, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5015, 354, 1, '<p>Inactivated vaccine for the prevention of paralytic rabies in cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5016, 354, 2, '<p>Inactivated suspension of rabies virus produced in BHK cells, in aluminum hydroxide adjuvant.</p>\r\n'),
(5017, 354, 3, '<p>2 mL in subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue, regardless of animal weight or age. If animals are vaccinated before 6 months of age, it is recommended to revaccinate 6 months thereafter. Revaccinate annually.</p>\r\n'),
(5018, 354, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(5019, 354, 6, '<p>Bottles of 50 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5020, 245, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario externo pour-on a base de Cipermetrina&nbsp;para bovinos, equinos, ovinos y porcinos.&nbsp;Su caracter&iacute;stica m&aacute;s importante es la persistencia&nbsp;de su acci&oacute;n antiparasitaria y repelente,&nbsp;lo que le otorga un prolongado poder residual.</p>\r\n'),
(5021, 245, 2, '<p>Cipermetrina, 6 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5022, 245, 1, '<p>Control y tratamiento de ectopar&aacute;sitos: piojos&nbsp;chupadores y masticadores, mosca de los cuernos,&nbsp;en bovinos, ovinos, equinos y porcinos.&nbsp;Piojos: el tiempo necesario para la eliminaci&oacute;n&nbsp;parasitaria es de 4 a 6 semanas. En ovinos adultos,&nbsp;los tratamientos deben realizarse dentro de los 45 d&iacute;as&nbsp;post-esquila. Los corderos pueden tratarse&nbsp;en cualquier momento.</p>\r\n'),
(5023, 245, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 10 mL hasta 400 kg de p.v. y 20 mL&nbsp;para animales de m&aacute;s de 400 kg de p.v. Las dosis&nbsp;se pueden modificar seg&uacute;n criterio profesional.&nbsp;Ovinos y Porcinos: 5 mL por animal.&nbsp;Equinos: 20 mL, repartidos de la siguiente forma: 5 mL&nbsp;en la tabla del cuello y pecho y 5 mL en cada flanco&nbsp;e ijar.&nbsp;Aplicar por derrame cut&aacute;neo dorsal (pour-on).</p>\r\n'),
(5024, 245, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo&nbsp;deben transcurrir 6 d&iacute;as.&nbsp;Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y el orde&ntilde;e para&nbsp;el consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n de la leche&nbsp;deben transcurrir 6 hs.</p>\r\n'),
(5025, 245, 6, '<p>Bidones dosificadores por 1 L.<br />\r\nBidones mochila por 5 L.</p>\r\n'),
(5026, 355, 1, '<p>Inactivated vaccine for the prevention of rabies in dogs and cats.</p>\r\n'),
(5027, 355, 2, '<p>Inactivated suspension of rabies virus produced in BHK cells</p>\r\n'),
(5028, 355, 3, '<p>1 mL in subcutaneous tissue as of 3 months of age.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Revaccinate annually.</p>\r\n'),
(5029, 355, 5, '<p>Store between 2 &ordm;C and 8 &ordm;C, away from light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not freeze.</p>\r\n'),
(5030, 355, 6, '<p>Package containing 12 monodose vials of 1 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Multidose bottles of 25 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5031, 247, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario externo pour-on. Piojicida y Mosquicida&nbsp;para bovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(5032, 247, 2, '<p>Cipermetrina, R-S-(Cis-Trans) 3-(2,2 diclorovinil)&nbsp;2,2 dimetilciclo propancarboxilato de alfa-ciano-3-&nbsp;fenoxibencilo (IUPAC), 4 g; imidacloprid, 1-(6-cloro-&nbsp;3-piridilmetil)-N-nitro-imidazolidin-2-ilideamina, 4 g;&nbsp;but&oacute;xido de piperonilo, 4 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5033, 247, 1, '<p>Piojos m&aacute;sticadores: Damalinia (Bovicola) bovis.&nbsp;Mosca de los Cuernos: Haematobia irritans.&nbsp;Miasis: Dermatobia hominis (Ura), ayuda en el control&nbsp;de Cochliomyia hominivorax.&nbsp;Insectos hemat&oacute;fagos: (Mosca brava) Stomoxis calcitrans.&nbsp;T&aacute;banos: Tabanidae spp.&nbsp;Mosquitos: Mosquitoes spp.</p>\r\n'),
(5034, 247, 3, '<p>Animales de 80 kg hasta 150 kg p.v. (terneros/as), aplicar&nbsp;10 mL. Animales de 150 kg hasta 350 kg p.v.&nbsp;(novillos y vaquillonas), aplicar 15 mL. Animales de m&aacute;s&nbsp;de 350 kg p.v. (Vacas / toros / novillos pesados): 20 mL.&nbsp;Aplicar por derrame cut&aacute;neo dorsal (pour on)&nbsp;con una jeringa con c&aacute;nula dosificadora, o similar.&nbsp;El producto se presenta listo&nbsp;para usar, no necesitando&nbsp;ninguna preparaci&oacute;n previa especial.</p>\r\n'),
(5035, 247, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y el sacrificio de los animales&nbsp;para consumo humano deben transcurrir 10 d&iacute;as.&nbsp;Puede utilizarse en vacas lecheras en per&iacute;odo&nbsp;de lactaci&oacute;n, con un per&iacute;odo de retiro preorde&ntilde;e&nbsp;de 12 horas a partir de la &uacute;ltima aplicaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5036, 247, 6, '<p>Bidones por 2,5 y 5 L.</p>\r\n'),
(5042, 256, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo para bovinos, ovino y porcinos. Antis&aacute;rnico y garrapaticida.</p>\r\n'),
(5043, 256, 2, '<p>Ivermectina, 1 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5044, 256, 1, '<p>BOVIFORT&reg; es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de Ivermectina 1% lista para usar. Sus caracter&iacute;sticas farmacocin&eacute;ticas hacen que el producto se metabolice lentamente por lo cual su acci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica es m&aacute;s prolongada que las formulaciones cl&aacute;sicas de Ivermectina inyectable. Administrando las dosis indicadas en bovinos, ovinos y porcinos, es altamente efectivo para el control y tratamiento de los par&aacute;sitos, tanto internos como externos.</p>\r\n'),
(5045, 256, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea exclusivamente. El punto de inoculaci&oacute;n sugerido es delante o detr&aacute;s de la paleta, utilizando jeringas adecuadas con agujas 15 x 15. Como cualquier inyectable, deben mantenerse las norm&aacute;s de asepsia, para evitar lesiones posteriores en el punto de inoculaci&oacute;n (abscesos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: La dosis para par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales, pulmonares y externos (d&iacute;pteros, piojos y miasis), es de 0,5 mL cada 25 kg de p.v.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En el caso de sarna las alternativas de tratamiento son: A) &Uacute;NICA dosis de 1 mL cada 30 kg de p.v. B) DOS dosis con un intervalo de 7 d&iacute;as, de 0,5 mL cada 25 kg de p.v.<br />\r\nDebe administrarse por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea exclusivamente. El punto de inoculaci&oacute;n sugerido es en la entrepierna, utilizando agujas 12/8 (o 12/10 en climas fr&iacute;os).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: 1 mL cada 33 kg de p.v., en una dosis &uacute;nica. Debe administrarse por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea exclusivamente. El punto de inoculaci&oacute;n sugerido es por detr&aacute;s de la oreja, utilizando agujas 12/6.</p>\r\n'),
(5046, 256, 9, '<p>Administrar s&oacute;lo por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n'),
(5047, 256, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo deben transcurrir:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bovinos: 49 d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n	<li>Ovinos: 49 d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n	<li>Porcinos: 28 d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>No administrar a animales en lactancia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No administrar a bovinos 28 d&iacute;as previos al parto cuando la leche se destine a consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5048, 256, 6, '<p>Frascos por 50 y 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5049, 254, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario inyectable endectocida a base de Ivermectina al 1% formulada especialmente con veh&iacute;culos de nueva generaci&oacute;n. Su acci&oacute;n antiparasitaria se complementa con una balanceada composici&oacute;n de tres vitaminas liposolubles indispensables para el crecimiento, desarrollo y reproducci&oacute;n del ganado bovino, ovino y porcino.</p>\r\n'),
(5050, 254, 2, '<p>Ivermectina, 1 g; Vitamina A (Palmitato), 8,85 g (150.000 UI/mL); Vitamina D3, 0,06 g (24.000 UI/mL); Vitamina E, 1,5 g (15 mg/mL), excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5051, 254, 1, '<p>Tratamiento y control de parasitosis internas (gastrointestinales y pulmonares, en estadios juveniles, adultos, e inhibidos) y externas (garrapata, sarna, piojos masticadores y chupadores, miasis cut&aacute;nea forunculosa(*)) de los bovinos, ovinos y porcinos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Al ser un producto vitam&iacute;nico combinado es de excelente aplicaci&oacute;n en animales en crecimiento, en la b&uacute;squeda de mejor respuesta inmunitaria de las vacunaciones, para evitar p&eacute;rdida de peso en destetes o movimientos de hacienda y lograr mejores &iacute;ndices de fertilidad y de engorde. La dosificaci&oacute;n vitam&iacute;nica aplicada cubre en m&aacute;s los requerimientos de las diferentes categor&iacute;as, facilitando el manejo y reduciendo los movimientos del ganado.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(*) (tupe, gusano del monte, t&oacute;rsalo, mirunta, maranguin, moyo cuil, nuche, berne, ura)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bovinos: Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: Bunostomum phlebotomum (adultos, L3 y L4) - Cooperia oncophora (adultos y L4) - C. pectinata (adultos y L4) - C. punctata (adultos y L4) - Cooperia spp (adultos y L3) - Haemonchus placei (adultos, L3 y L4) - Mecistocirrus digitatus (adultos) - Nematodirus helvetianus (adultos) - N. spathiger (adultos) - Oesophagostomum radiatum (adultos, L3 y L4) - Ostertagia ostertagi (adultos, L3 y L4, incluyendo larvas inhibidas) - O. Iyrata (adultos y L4) - Strongyloides papillosus (adultos) - Trichostrongylus axei (adultos y L4) - T. colubriformis (adultos y L4) - Toxocara vitulorum (adultos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Dictyocaulus viviparus (adultos, L4 y estados inhibidos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Sarna: Acariosis cut&aacute;nea producida por: Psoroptes bovis (syn. Psoroptes communis var. bovis) - Sarcoptes scabiei var. bovis - Chorioptes bovis Garrapata com&uacute;n del bovino: Rhipicephalus microplus (Boophilus microplus)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pediculosis - Piojos chupadores: Haematopinus eurystermus - Linognathus vituli - Solenopotes capillatus. Ura: Dermatobia hominis - Hypoderma bovis - Hypoderma lineatum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Como tratamiento coadyuvante en el control de: Pediculosis - Piojos masticadores: Damalinia bovis. Otros par&aacute;sitos donde la Ivermectina ha mostrado actividad: Parailaria bovicola (adultos), Thelazia spp (adultos), Chrisomyia bezziana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: Haemonchus contortus (adultos, L3 y L4) - Ostertagia circumcincta (adultos, L3 y L4)- Ostertagia trifurcata (adultos y L4) - Trichostrongylus axei (adultos) - Trichostrongylus vitrinus (adultos) - Trichostrongylus colubriformis (adultos, L3 y L4) - Nematodirus spathiger (L3 y L4) - Nematodirus il&iacute;collis - Cooperia curticei (adultos, L3 y L4)- Oesophagostomum venulosum (adultos), Oesophagostomum columbianum (adultos, L3 y L4) - Chabertia ovina (adultos, L3 y L4)- Trichuris ovis (adultos) - Strongyloides papillosus (L3 y L4) - Gaigeria pachyscellis (adultos, L3 y L4).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Protostrongylus rufescens (adultos) - Dictyocaulus ilaria (adultos). Gusano de la nariz: Oestrus ovis (todos los estados larvales).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Acaros de la sarna: Psoroptes (Psoroptes communis var. ovis) - Sarcoptes scabiei var. ovis - Psorergates spp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: Ascaris suum (adultos y L4) - Hyostrongylus rubidus (adultos y L4) - Oesophagostomum spp (adultos y L4) - Strongyloides ransomi (adultos) - Trichuris suis (adultos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Metastrongylus spp (adultos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos del Ri&ntilde;&oacute;n: Stephanurus dentatus (adultos y L4).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Par&aacute;sitos externos: Piojos: Haematopinus suis - Acaros: Sarcoptes scabiei var. suis.</p>\r\n'),
(5052, 254, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. (200 mcg/kg). Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con aguja 10/18.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: 0,5 mL cada 25 kg de p.v. (200 mcg/kg). Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con aguja 10/15, en la piel floja detr&aacute;s de la paleta o en la ingle, en la cara interna del muslo</p>\r\n'),
(5053, 254, 8, '<p>Bovinos y Ovinos: Carne: No sacrificar animales para consumo humano hasta haber transcurrido 48 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leche: No aplicar en animales en lactaci&oacute;n ni dentro de los 38 d&iacute;as antes del parto, cuando la leche se destine para consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: No sacrificar animales para consumo humano hasta haber transcurrido 28 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n'),
(5054, 254, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5055, 253, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo para equinos. Soluci&oacute;n gelificada de Ivermectina al 1% para ser administrada por v&iacute;a oral, de excelente palatabilidad y facilidad de aplicaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5056, 253, 2, '<p>Ivermectina, 1g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5057, 253, 1, '<p>BAGOMECTINA EQUINA gel multidosis est&aacute; indicado para combatir los siguientes par&aacute;sitos, tanto en sus formas adultas como inmaduras.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grandes estr&oacute;ngilos: Strongylus vulgaris (adultos y estadios larvales arteriales), Strongylus edentatus (adultos y estadios tisulares), Strongylus equinus (adultos) y Triodontophorus spp (adultos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peque&ntilde;os estr&oacute;ngilos: Cyathostominae (adultos y L-4) de las siguientes especies: Cyathostomum spp, Cylicocyclus spp, Cylicostephanus spp, Cylicodontophorus spp, Gyalocephalus spp y Poteriostomum spp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Otros par&aacute;sitos internos: Parascaris equorum (adultos, L-3 y L-4), Trichostrongylus axei (adultos), Strongyloides westeri (adultos), Habronema muscae (adultos), Habronema majus (adultos) y Oxyuris equi (adultos y L -4). Par&aacute;sitos del cuajo: Gasterophilus nasalis (L-2 y L-3). Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Dictyocaulus arnieldi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Habronemosis cut&aacute;nea: (llagas de verano) causadas por: Habronema muscae, Habronema majus y Draschias spp en sus estadios larvales cut&aacute;neos L-3. Dermatitis causadas por Fil&aacute;ridos (microilariae): Onchocerca cervicalis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garrapatas: Ayuda en el control de Amblyomma cajennense y Dermacentor nitens.</p>\r\n'),
(5058, 253, 3, '<p>1 g cada 50 kg de p.v. (200 mcg de Ivermectina por kg de peso vivo). Administrar exclusivamente por v&iacute;a oral. Destapar el frasco, colocar el inserto con boquilla para jeringa en la boca del mismo y cargar la jeringa dosiicadora con la cantidad adecuada de producto ajustada al peso del animal a tratar. No retirar el inserto una vez colocado.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrar el producto en la parte posterior de la boca elevando luego la cabeza del animal para asegurarse que el producto sea ingerido. Evitar la administraci&oacute;n en forma en&eacute;rgica, para disminuir la posibilidad de falsa v&iacute;a.</p>\r\n'),
(5059, 253, 6, '<p>Jeringas monodosis de 12 g y frascos multidosis de 240 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5060, 252, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo para bovinos, ovinos y porcinos, que combate los par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales, pulmonares, sarna, piojos, ura y miasis. Soluci&oacute;n inyectable de Ivermectina al 1%.</p>\r\n'),
(5061, 252, 2, '<p>Ivermectina, 1 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5062, 252, 1, '<p>Bovinos<br />\r\nPar&aacute;sitos internos: Par&aacute;sitos Gastrointestinales: Bunostomum phlebotomum (adultos, L3 y L4); Cooperia oncophora (adultos y L4); Cooperia pectinata (adultos y L4); Cooperia punctata (adultos y L4); Cooperia spp (adultos y L3); Haemonchus placei (adultos, L3 y L4); Mecistocirrus digitatus (adultos); Nematodirus helvetianus (adultos); Nematodirus spathiger (adultos); Oesophagostomum radiatum (adultos, L3 y L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) lyrata (adultos y L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) ostertagi (adultos, L3 y L4 incluyendo larvas inhibidas); Strongyloides papillosus (adultos); Trichostrongylus axei (adultos y L4); Trichostrongylus colubriformis (adultos y L4); Toxocara vitulorum (adultos). Par&aacute;sitos Pulmonares: Dictyocaulus viviparus (adultos, L4 y estados inhibidos). Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Sarna: Acariosis cut&aacute;nea producida por: Psoroptes communis var. bovis; Sarcoptes scabiei var. bovis; Chorioptes bovis. Piojos Chupadores: Haematopinus eurysternus; Linognathus vituli; Solenopotes capillatus. Miasis: Dermatobia hominis (Ura); Hypoderma bovis; Hypoderma lineatum. Como tratamiento coadyuvante en el control de piojos m&aacute;sticadores (Damalinia bovis). Otros par&aacute;sitos donde la Ivermectina ha mostrado actividad: Parailaria bovicola (adultos); Thelazia spp (adultos); Chrysomyia bezziana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos<br />\r\nPar&aacute;sitos internos: Par&aacute;sitos Gastrointestinales: Haemonchus contortus (adultos, L3 y L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) circumcincta (adultos, L3 y L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) trifurcata (adultos y L4); Trichostrongylus axei (adultos); Trichostrongylus vitrinus (adultos); Trichostrongylus colubriformis (adultos, L3 y L4); Nematodirus spathiger (L3 y L4); Nematodirus ilicollis; Cooperia curticei (adultos, L3 y L4);Oesophagostomum venulosum (adultos); Oesophagostomum columbianum (adultos, L3 y L4); Chabertia ovina (adultos, L3 y L4); Thichuris ovis (adultos); Strongyloides papillosus (L3 y L4); Gaigeria pachyscelis (adultos, L3 y L4). Par&aacute;sitos Pulmonares: Dictyocaulus ilaria (adultos); Protostrongylus rufescens (adultos). Gusano de la cabeza: Oestrus ovis (todos los estad&iacute;os larvales). Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Acaros de la Sarna: Psoroptes communis var. ovis; Sarcoptes scabiei var. ovis; Psorergates ovis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos<br />\r\nPar&aacute;sitos internos: Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: Ascaris suum (adultos y L4); Hyostrongylus rubidus (adultos y L4); Oesophagostomum spp (adultos y L4); Strongyloides ransomi (adultos); Trichuris suis (adultos). Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Metastrongylus spp (adultos). Par&aacute;sitos del ri&ntilde;&oacute;n: Stephanurus dentatus (adultos y L4). Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Piojos: Haematopinus suis; Acaros: Sarcoptes scabiei var suis.</p>\r\n'),
(5063, 252, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. (200 mcg/kg) por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con aguja 10/18. Ovinos: 0,5 mL cada 25 kg de p.v. (200 mcg/kg) por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con aguja 40/15, en la piel loja detr&aacute;s de la paleta o en la ingle, en la cara interna del muslo. Porcinos: 1 mL cada 33 kg de p.v. (300 mcg/kg) por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la piel laxa detr&aacute;s de la oreja o en la ingle (cara interna del muslo).</p>\r\n'),
(5064, 252, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo deben transcurrir:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bovinos: 35 d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n	<li>Ovinos: 35 d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n	<li>Porcinos: 18 d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>No aplicar en vacas lecheras en lactaci&oacute;n ni dentro de los 28 d&iacute;as previos al parto cuando la leche se destine a consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n. No utilizar en ovejas en lactaci&oacute;n cuando la leche se destine a consumo humano o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5065, 252, 6, '<p>Frascos por 50 y 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5066, 356, 7, '<p>Wide spectrum injectable endoparasiticide for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5067, 356, 2, '<p>L-Tetramisole phosphate, 22.3 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5068, 356, 1, '<p>Endoparasiticide effective against gastrointestinal and pulmonary parasites in cattle</p>\r\n'),
(5069, 356, 3, '<p>1 ml per 22.5 kg live weight (8 mg/kg live weight), in subcutaneous (SC), intramuscular (IM), intraruminal (IR) or intraperitoneal (IP) tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Subcutaneous injection: Administer in the neck or behind the shoulder blade with a 10/18 gauge needle, pinching the skin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Intramuscular injection: It can be administered in the neck or rump with a 20/20 gauge needle according to animal size.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Intraruminal or intraperitoneal injection: Administer in the left lank with a 20/20 gauge needle according to animal size. IR and IP routes are speciically indicated for use during the summer season so as to avoid possible local reactions. Inoculation in the left lank in animals with underdeveloped rumen has no contraindications, since the IP route can be used.</p>\r\n'),
(5070, 356, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter is 7 days. Withdrawal time from last treatment for milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5071, 356, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 500 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5072, 257, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo altamente efectivo para el control y tratamiento de los par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales y pulmonares, sarna, miasis y garrapatas de bovinos y ovinos. Soluci&oacute;n inyectable de Doramectina al 1,1% listo para usar.</p>\r\n'),
(5073, 257, 2, '<p>Doramectina 1,1 g; excipientes, c.s.p 100 mL.</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `tbl_producto_contenido` (`id`, `producto_id`, `parte`, `text`) VALUES
(5074, 257, 1, '<p>Bovinos: Par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales: Ostertagia ostertagi (adultos); O. ostertagi inhibidos (L4); O. lyrata (adultos e inmaduros); Haemonchus placei (adultos e inmaduros); Mecistocirrus digitatus (adultos); Trichostrongylus axei (adultos e inmaduros); T. colubriformis (adultos e inmaduros); Cooperia punctata (adultos e inmaduros); C. pectinata (adultos e inmaduros); C. oncophora (adultos e inmaduros); Cooperia spp (adultos e inmaduros); Oesophagostomum radiatum (adultos e inmaduros); Nematodirus helvetianus (adultos); N. spathiger (adultos); Strongyloides papillosus (adultos); Bunostomum phlebotomum (adultos e inmaduros); Toxocara vitulorum (adultos). Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Dictyocaulus viviparus (adultos, inmaduros e inhibidos). Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Miasis cut&aacute;neas: Dermatobia hominis (ura, berne, nuche o t&oacute;rsalo) (estad&iacute;os larvarios); Hypoderma bovis (&ldquo;heel lies&rdquo;) (estad&iacute;os larvarios); Hypoderma lineatum (estad&iacute;os larvarios); Cochliomyia hominivorax (bichera o gusanera) (estad&iacute;os larvarios); Chrysomya bezziana (estad&iacute;os larvarios).Garrapatas: Rhipicephalus microplus. Aprobado como garrapaticida con una eicacia del 99,47% y un poder residual absoluto de 11 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: Par&aacute;sitos Gastrointestinales: Haemonchus contortus (adultos, L3 y L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) circumcincta (adultos, L3 y L4); Mecistocirrus digitatus (adultos e inmaduros); O. (Teladorsagia) trifurcata (adultos y L4); Trichostrongylus vitrinus (adultos); Nematodirus ilicollis; Nematodirus spathiger (adultos y L4); Cooperia curticei (adultos y L4); Oesophagostomum columbianum (adultos, L3 y L4); Oesophagostomum venulosum (adultos); Trichuris ovis (adultos); Strongyloides papillosus (L3 y L4); Gaigeria pachyscelis (adultos, L3 y L4); Chabertia ovina (adultos, L3 y L4). Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Dictyocaulus ilaria (adultos); Protostrongylus rufescens (adultos). Ectopar&aacute;sitos: Miasis: Cochliomyia hominivorax, (estad&iacute;os larvarios); C. macellaria, (estad&iacute;os larvarios); Lucilia spp, (estad&iacute;os larvarios); Oestrus ovis, (estad&iacute;os larvarios). &Aacute;caros de la sarna: Psoroptes communis var. ovis; Sarcoptes scabiei</p>\r\n'),
(5075, 257, 3, '<p>Bovinos: Usar a raz&oacute;n de 1 mL/50 kg de peso vivo (equivalente a 220 mcg de Doramectina), en dosis &uacute;nica. Por inyecci&oacute;n subcut&aacute;nea, aplicada en la mitad posterior de la tabla del cuello por delante de la paleta, o por detr&aacute;s de &eacute;sta, en la parte superior de la regi&oacute;n del costillar. Usar una jeringa multidosis, con una aguja 15/15, y de igual manera que para cualquier inyectable, mantener las normas de asepsia, para evitar as&iacute; lesiones posteriores. La jeringa y las agujas deben ser esterilizadas previo a su uso.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: La dosis para par&aacute;sitos gastrointestinales y pulmonares y par&aacute;sitos externos (miasis) es de 0,5 mL/25 kg de peso vivo. Para el tratamiento de la sarna ovina administrar 1 mL/25 Kg de peso vivo. FLOK debe usarse por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea exclusivamente, en dosis &uacute;nica. El punto de aplicaci&oacute;n sugerido es en la entrepierna, utilizando agujas 12/8 o 12/10 y jeringa autom&aacute;tica, aplicar el producto con el animal sentado. Al igual que para todo inyectable deben mantenerse las normas de asepsia.</p>\r\n'),
(5076, 257, 8, '<p>No sacrificar animales bovinos y ovinos para consumo humano hasta haber transcurrido 44 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No administrar a hembras en lactancia cuya leche se destine a consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n. la correspondiente Prueba Oicial (Resoluci&oacute;n (SAyG) N&ordm; 270/84).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Este producto debe aplicarse bajo prescripci&oacute;n y control del M&eacute;dico Veterinario.</p>\r\n'),
(5077, 257, 6, '<p>Frascos por 50 mL y 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5078, 251, 7, '<p>Larvicida externo, pomada antimi&aacute;sica para bovinos,&nbsp;ovinos, caprinos, equinos y porcinos.</p>\r\n'),
(5079, 251, 2, '<p>Cipermetrina, 2 g; Diclorv&oacute;s, 1 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5080, 251, 1, '<p>Indicado especialmente para combatir las miasis&nbsp;producidas por Cochliomyia hominivorax, Lucilia cuprina&nbsp;y L. sericata en bovinos, ovinos, caprinos, equinos&nbsp;y porcinos. Tiene acci&oacute;n residual por 12 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n'),
(5081, 251, 3, '<p>Para el tratamiento de las miasis se debe proceder a&nbsp;cubrir bien las cavidades y superficies de las heridas, y&nbsp;as&iacute; poder eliminar las larvas, activando y facilitando la&nbsp;cicatrizaci&oacute;n. Como preventivo, recomendamos&nbsp;GALMETRIN PLUS POMADA en las heridas ocasionadas&nbsp;por: esquila, se&ntilde;alada, descole, descorne, castraci&oacute;n, etc.&nbsp;El efecto residual de GALMETRIN PLUS POMADA es&nbsp;prolongado, no obstante, en &eacute;pocas de mucha incidencia&nbsp;de moscas, conviene repetir el tratamiento con intervalos&nbsp;de 12 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n'),
(5082, 251, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo&nbsp;humano deben transcurrir 48 horas. Entre el &uacute;ltimo&nbsp;tratamiento y el orde&ntilde;e para consumo humano y/o&nbsp;industrializaci&oacute;n de la leche deben transcurrir&nbsp;48 horas.</p>\r\n'),
(5083, 251, 6, '<p>Potes por 1 kg.</p>\r\n'),
(5084, 258, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo para equinos. Gel de amplio espectro que combina Ivermectina al 1% y Praziquantel para ser administrado por v&iacute;a oral. De excelente palatabilidad y facilidad de aplicaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5085, 258, 2, '<p>Ivermectina, 1 g ; Praziquantel, 7,5 g; excipientes c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5086, 258, 1, '<p>FORTIUM est&aacute; indicado para combatir los siguientes par&aacute;sitos tanto en sus form&aacute;s adultas e inmaduras: Grandes estr&oacute;ngilos: Strongylus vulgaris (adultos y estad&iacute;os larvales arteriales);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Strongylus edentatus (adultos y estad&iacute;os tisulares); Strongylus equinus (adultos); Triodontophorus spp (adultos).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peque&ntilde;os estr&oacute;ngilos: Cyathostominae (Adultos y L4) de las siguientes especies: Cyathostomum spp; Cylicocyclus spp; Cylicostephanus spp; Cylicodontophorus spp; Gyalocephalus spp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Poteriostomum spp. Otros par&aacute;sitos internos: Parascaris equorum (adultos, L3 y L4); Oxyuris equi (adultos y L4); Trichostrongylus axei (adultos); Strongyloides westeri (adultos); Habronema muscae (adultos);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Habronema majus (adultos); Anoplocephala perfoliata; Anoplocephala magna; Paranoplocephala mamillana. Par&aacute;sitos del cuajo: Gasterophilus nasalis (L2 y L3). Par&aacute;sitos pulmonares: Dictyocaulus arnieldi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Habronemosis cut&aacute;nea (llagas de verano) causadas por: Habronema muscae; Habronema majus; Draschias spp en sus estad&iacute;os larvales cut&aacute;neos L3. Dermatitis causadas por Fil&aacute;ridos (microilariae): Onchocerca cervicalis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Garrapatas: Ayuda en el control de: Amblyomma cajenense; Dermacentor nitens.</p>\r\n'),
(5087, 258, 3, '<p>1 g cada 50 kg de p.v. (200 mcg de Ivermectina/ kg p.v. y 1,5 mg/kg p.v. de Praziquantel).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrar exclusivamente por v&iacute;a oral. Para una correcta administraci&oacute;n del producto, calibrar la jeringa dosificadora de acuerdo al peso del animal a tratar</p>\r\n'),
(5088, 258, 16, '<p>Abrir la boca colocando los dedos sobre el morro y el pulgar sobre el paladar, ejerciendo una suave presi&oacute;n. Retirar la tapa de la c&aacute;nula e introducir la jeringa en la boca buscando dejar la c&aacute;nula sobre la base de la lengua, apretando luego el &eacute;mbolo suavemente. El equino saborear&aacute; la esencia y deglutir&aacute; el gel. Evitar la administraci&oacute;n en forma en&eacute;rgica para disminuir la posibilidad de falsa v&iacute;a.</p>\r\n'),
(5089, 258, 17, '<p>A la dosis indicada puede ser administrado en equinos de todas las edades, inclusive en yeguas en cualquier etapa del estado de pre&ntilde;ez.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La fertilidad y calidad del semen de los padrillos no son afectados. No tiene efecto teratog&eacute;nico.</p>\r\n'),
(5090, 258, 8, '<p>No destinar los animales tratados al consumo humano hasta transcurridos 14 d&iacute;as del &uacute;ltimo tratamiento.</p>\r\n'),
(5091, 258, 6, '<p>Jeringas monodosis de 12 g y Frascos multidosis por 240 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5092, 261, 7, '<p>Antibi&oacute;tico inyectable de amplio espectro &ndash; antit&eacute;rmico. Para bovinos y equinos. Asociaci&oacute;n sin&eacute;rgica bif&aacute;sica de Penicilina y Estreptomicina con Dipirona y Vitamina C.</p>\r\n'),
(5093, 261, 2, '<p>Cada frasco con polvo contiene: Penicilina s&oacute;dica, 2.500.000 UI; Penicilina benzat&iacute;nica, 2.500.000 UI; Estreptomicina (como sulfato), 2000 mg; Dipirona, 1000 mg.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cada ampolla con solvente contiene: Vitamina C, 1100 mg; Clorhidrato de Lidoca&iacute;na, 60 mg; excipientes, c.s.p. 16 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5094, 261, 1, '<p>Neumon&iacute;as, bronconeumon&iacute;as, neumoenteritis, nefritis, pielonefritis, cistitis, metritis, hepatitis, mastitis, septicemias, adenitis equina, absceso interdigital, actinomicosis, carbunclo, t&eacute;tanos, leptospirosis. En todos los casos de infecciones provocadas por g&eacute;rmenes sensibles a la penicilina o estreptomicina.</p>\r\n'),
(5095, 261, 3, '<p>10.000 a 20.000 UI de penicilina/kg p.v., por v&iacute;a intramuscular profunda que equivalen aproximadamente a 3,2 mL del producto reconstitu&iacute;do cada 100 kg de p.v., seg&uacute;n la gravedad de la afecci&oacute;n. Por lo general una sola inyecci&oacute;n es suficiente. Si persistieran los s&iacute;ntom&aacute;s puede ser repetida la aplicaci&oacute;n a las 24-48 horas.</p>\r\n'),
(5096, 261, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo deben transcurrir 30 d&iacute;as. Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la utilizaci&oacute;n de la leche para consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n deben transcurrir 4 d&iacute;as (8 orde&ntilde;es).</p>\r\n'),
(5097, 261, 6, '<p>Cajas con 12 estuches. Cada estuche contiene una ampolla con polvo y una ampolla con el solvente.</p>\r\n'),
(5098, 263, 7, '<p>Soluci&oacute;n antibi&oacute;tica inyectable de amplio espectro y acci&oacute;n prolongada para bovinos, porcinos, ovinos y caprinos. La naturaleza del excipiente de &eacute;sta preparaci&oacute;n permite:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtener tasas plasm&aacute;ticas y en tejidos elevadas e inmediatamente eficaces.</li>\r\n	<li>Mantener estas tasas durante tres a cinco d&iacute;as.</li>\r\n	<li>Tratar infecciones con una sola administraci&oacute;n a&uacute;n cuando se trate de procesos agudos.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>El espectro de acci&oacute;n de MAXIBIOTIC L.A. es muy amplio, abarcando g&eacute;rmenes Gram (+) y Gram (-); Micoplasmas, Protozoarios, Rickettsias, Clamidias y Actinomicetos.</p>\r\n'),
(5099, 263, 2, '<p>Oxitetraciclina base, 20 gr; excipiente de acci&oacute;n prolongada, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5100, 263, 1, '<p>Bovinos: Neumopat&iacute;as y gastroenteritis infecciosas, abortos de origen infeccioso, infecciones articulares, pododermitis, artritis, queratoconjuntivitis infecciosa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: Neumopat&iacute;as y gastroenteritis infecciosas, metritis, mastitis, agalactia, abortos de origen infeccioso, rinitis atr&oacute;ica.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos y caprinos: Piet&iacute;n, abortos provocados por Clamidias y Salmonellas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Otras indicaciones: Neumon&iacute;a del transporte, anaplasmosis, piroplasmosis, leptospirosis y carbunclo sintom&aacute;tico.</p>\r\n'),
(5101, 263, 3, '<p>1 mL cada 10 kg de p.v. (20mg/kg p.v.) por v&iacute;a intramuscular profunda en bovinos, ovinos, caprinos y porcinos; y por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea en lechones menores de 10 kg de p.v. En caso de infecciones graves, puede aplicarse otra dosis a los tres d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n'),
(5102, 263, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo deben transcurrir 28 d&iacute;as. No usar en animales en orde&ntilde;e cuya leche se destine a consumo y/o industrializaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5103, 263, 6, '<p>Frascos por 100 mL y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5104, 357, 7, '<p>Injectable endoparasiticide with ovicide effect for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5105, 357, 2, '<p>Ricobendazole 10 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5106, 357, 1, '<p>For the treatment and control of lung and gastrointestinal parasitosis in cattle caused by: Haemonchus spp, Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) spp (including hypobiotic forms), Trichostrongylus spp, Cooperia spp, Nematodirus spp, Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Dictyocaulus spp. PARAXANE&reg; INYECTABLE is more than 99% effective against adult parasites and more than 94% effective against inhibited forms of parasites.</p>\r\n'),
(5107, 357, 3, '<p>Administer in subcutaneous tissue only, in front of or behind the shoulder blade. Use a dose of 2.5 to 8 mg/kg of body weight. The following dosage is recommended: 1 mL per 40 kg of body weight up to 1 mL per 12.5 kg of body weight, taking into account parasite cycle and according to the professional judgment of the attending veterinarian.</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Dosage</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">100Kg</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">200Kg</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">300Kg</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">400Kg</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Adult Parasites</td>\r\n			<td>2,5mL</td>\r\n			<td>5mL</td>\r\n			<td>7,5mL</td>\r\n			<td>10mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Hypobiotic Larve</td>\r\n			<td>8mL</td>\r\n			<td>16mL</td>\r\n			<td>24mL</td>\r\n			<td>32mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(5108, 357, 8, '<p>Due to its long-acting formula and its persistence in tissues, animals cannot be slaughtered until 49 days after the last treatment. Withdrawal time from last treatment of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 120 hours (10 milkings).</p>\r\n'),
(5109, 357, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 1 L.</p>\r\n'),
(5110, 265, 7, '<p>Producto hormonal para el manejo del ciclo estral y de la reproducci&oacute;n en bovinos, ovinos, equinos, porcinos, caninos y felinos.</p>\r\n'),
(5111, 265, 2, '<p>Benzoato de estradiol, 100 mg; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5112, 265, 1, '<p>Terap&eacute;uticas: BIOESTROGEN es un producto hormonal con efecto estrog&eacute;nico, indicado como coadyuvante en el tratamiento de afecciones tocoginecol&oacute;gicas tales como partos dist&oacute;cicos, retenciones placentarias, abortos, metritis y pi&oacute;metras en equinos, bovinos, ovinos, porcinos, caninos y felinos y para el tratamiento de la pseudopre&ntilde;ez en caninos. BIOESTROGEN est&aacute; indicado tambi&eacute;n como coadyuvante en el tratamiento del anestro en &eacute;stas especies. Manejo reproductivo: BIOESTROGEN est&aacute; indicado para ser utilizado dentro de diferentes Programas Reproductivos en equinos, bovinos, ovinos, porcinos, caninos y felinos, para la sincronizaci&oacute;n de la ovulaci&oacute;n en esquemas de inseminaci&oacute;n artificial a tiempo fijo o servicio natural.</p>\r\n'),
(5113, 265, 3, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Bovinos: 0,5 a 10 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Equinos: 2 a 10 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Ovinos: 0,5 a 3 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Porcinos: 1 a 4 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Caninos y Felinos: 0,01 a 0,1 mL /kg p.v.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>La v&iacute;a de administraci&oacute;n en todas las especies es intramuscular profunda.</p>\r\n'),
(5114, 265, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena o la utilizaci&oacute;n de la leche para consumo humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n, deben transcurrir 30 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n'),
(5115, 265, 6, '<p>Frascos por 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5116, 266, 7, '<p>Dispositivo intravaginal para la regulaci&oacute;n del ciclo estral en hembras bovinas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Luego de colocado el dispositivo en la vagina comienza r&aacute;pidamente a liberar progesterona, logrando niveles s&eacute;ricos elevados de &eacute;sta hormona en forma inmediata. Estos niveles elevados de progesterona producen un efecto importante sobre la din&aacute;mica folicular ov&aacute;rica, al actuar como un cuerpo l&uacute;teo artificial. En particular provocan la regresi&oacute;n del fol&iacute;culo dominante y aceleran el recambio de las ondas foliculares, con el consecuente cese de secreci&oacute;n de estr&oacute;genos e inhibinas. La ca&iacute;da de los niveles de estas dos hormonas desde el ovario, conducen a un aumento de la secreci&oacute;n de GnRH y FSH desde el eje hipot&aacute;lamo &ndash; hip&oacute;fisis. Esta &uacute;ltima ser&aacute; la responsable de la maduraci&oacute;n de la siguiente onda folicular. Luego, al retirar el dispositivo de la vagina, se provoca la ca&iacute;da abrupta de los niveles s&eacute;ricos de progesterona, lo cual lleva a aumentar la frecuencia puls&aacute;til en la liberaci&oacute;n de LH, responsable de la ovulaci&oacute;n y maduraci&oacute;n del cuerpo l&uacute;teo, y aumenta tambi&eacute;n la secreci&oacute;n del estradiol del ovario, responsable de las manifestaciones del celo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El concepto de inducci&oacute;n del celo implica desencadenamiento de una fase folicular que, asociado al comportamiento estral, culmine con la ovulaci&oacute;n. La sincronizaci&oacute;n de celo, por su parte, refiere a la simultaneidad de dichos eventos inducidos en un conjunto de animales tratados.</p>\r\n'),
(5117, 266, 2, '<p>Cada camisa contiene: progesterona (hormona esteroide de origen vegetal), 186 mg; Silicona inerte, c.s.p. 5,6 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5118, 266, 1, '<p>Control del ciclo estral en vaquillonas y vacas. Inseminaci&oacute;n artificial a tiempo fijo (IATF) y sistem&aacute;tica (IAS). Acortamiento del per&iacute;odo parto-concepci&oacute;n y del ciclo estral de la estaci&oacute;n reproductiva. Preparaci&oacute;n de donantes y receptoras para programas de transplantes de embriones. Tratamientos reproductivos para vaquillonas de corta edad. Todas estas indicaciones van acompa&ntilde;adas del uso de hormonas que juegan roles important&iacute;simos en el control del eje Hipot&aacute;lamo &ndash; Hip&oacute;fisis &ndash; Ov&aacute;rico.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LOS PROGRAMAS DE TRATAMIENTO DEBEN SER DIRIGIDOS POR ESTRICTA INTERVENCI&Oacute;N PROFESIONAL.</p>\r\n'),
(5119, 266, 3, '<p>V&iacute;a Intravaginal</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Para la manipulaci&oacute;n de los dispositivos y camisas se recomienda el uso de guantes.</li>\r\n	<li>El equipo de aplicaci&oacute;n se debe desinfectar antes de su uso.</li>\r\n	<li>Colocar el dispositivo dentro del aplicador con la cola de extracci&oacute;n hacia el interior, rebatiendo sus ramas.</li>\r\n	<li>Desinfectar la vulva del animal a tratar.</li>\r\n	<li>Introducir el aplicador en la vagina previa desinfecci&oacute;n con iodopovidona o amonios cuaternarios y lubricaci&oacute;n, hasta el fondo del saco vaginal (situaci&oacute;n fundamental para su correcto anclaje). Una vez colocado el dispositivo, retirar el aplicador.</li>\r\n	<li>Para facilitar la aplicaci&oacute;n en animales que se resisten a la misma, utilizar los m&eacute;todos de sujeci&oacute;n apropiados.</li>\r\n	<li>En los casos que no puede introducirse el aplicador con facilidad, revisar el estado genital de la hembra en cuesti&oacute;n, pues puede presentar anomal&iacute;as de origen cong&eacute;nito o adquirido.</li>\r\n	<li>Seg&uacute;n el momento indicado en el protocolo de sincronizaci&oacute;n de celo utilizado, retirar el dispositivo de la vagina, tirando de la cola de extracci&oacute;n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(5120, 266, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(5121, 266, 6, '<p>Bolsa conteniendo 20 perchas pl&aacute;sticas inertes. Cada percha tiene montadas 3 camisas medicadas y 1 camisa de silicona inerte como sost&eacute;n. Las 3 camisas montadas en las perchas pl&aacute;sticas inertes proveen en total 558 mg de progesterona. Se utiliza una percha por animal en hembras bovinas por &uacute;nica vez.</p>\r\n'),
(5122, 268, 7, '<p>Dispositivo intravaginal para la regulaci&oacute;n del ciclo estral en hembras bovinas. CRONIPRES TRES USOS es un dispositivo intravaginal de silicona inerte y progesterona (P4) utilizado para la sincronizaci&oacute;n del ciclo estral de bovinos. Esto permite mejorar el desarrollo de la Inseminaci&oacute;n Artiicial (IA), ya sea en forma sistem&aacute;tica (IAS) o a tiempo fijo (IATF) y las condiciones de manejo de los sistemas productivos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El dispositivo CRONIPRES TRES USOS puede ser utilizado dos veces en su forma de presentaci&oacute;n original y una tercera vez con el uso complementario de las Camisas. Deben montarse 3 Camisas por dispositivo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Luego de colocado el dispositivo en la vagina comienza r&aacute;pidamente a liberar progesterona, logrando niveles s&eacute;ricos elevados de esta hormona en forma inmediata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Estos niveles elevados de progesterona producen un efecto importante sobre la din&aacute;mica folicular ov&aacute;rica, al actuar como un cuerpo l&uacute;teo artiicial. En particular, provocan la regresi&oacute;n del fol&iacute;culo dominante y aceleran el recambio de las ondas foliculares, con el consecuente cese de secreci&oacute;n de estr&oacute;genos e inhibinas. La ca&iacute;da de los niveles de estas dos hormonas desde el ovario, conducen a un aumento de la secreci&oacute;n de GnRH y FSH desde el eje hipot&aacute;lamo &ndash; hip&oacute;fisis. Esta &uacute;ltima ser&aacute; la responsable de la maduraci&oacute;n de la siguiente onda folicular. Luego, al retirar el dispositivo de la vagina, se provoca la ca&iacute;da abrupta de los niveles s&eacute;ricos de progesterona, lo cual lleva a aumentar la frecuencia puls&aacute;til en la liberaci&oacute;n de LH, responsable de la ovulaci&oacute;n y maduraci&oacute;n del cuerpo luteo, y aumenta tambi&eacute;n la secreci&oacute;n del estradiol del ovario, responsable de las manifestaciones del celo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El concepto de inducci&oacute;n del celo implica desencadenamiento de una fase folicular que, asociado al comportamiento estral, culmine con la ovulaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La sincronizaci&oacute;n de celo, por su parte, refiere a la simultaneidad de dichos eventos inducidos en un conjunto de animales tratados.</p>\r\n'),
(5123, 268, 2, '<p>Cada dispositivo contiene:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progesterona* .............................1,00 g</li>\r\n	<li>Silicona inerte, c.s.p......................29,0 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>* Hormona esteroide de origen vegetal.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cada Camisa contiene:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progesterona *...........................100 mg</li>\r\n	<li>Silicona inerte, c.s.p..................... 2,90 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>* Hormona esteroide de origen vegetal.</sub></p>\r\n'),
(5124, 268, 1, '<p>Control del ciclo estral en vaquillonas y vacas. Inseminaci&oacute;n artificial a tiempo fijo (IATF) y sistem&aacute;tica (IAS). Acortamiento del periodo parto-concepci&oacute;n y del ciclo estral de la estaci&oacute;n reproductiva. Preparaci&oacute;n de donantes y receptoras para programas de transplantes de embriones. Tratamientos reproductivos para vaquillonas de corta edad. Todas estas indicaciones van acompa&ntilde;adas del uso de hormonas que juegan roles important&iacute;simos en el control del eje Hipot&aacute;lamo &ndash; Hip&oacute;fisis &ndash; Ov&aacute;rico.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LOS PROGRAMAS DE TRATAMIENTO DEBEN SER DIRIGIDOS POR ESTRICTA INTERVENCI&Oacute;N PROFESIONAL.</p>\r\n'),
(5125, 268, 3, '<p>V&iacute;a intravaginal</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Para la manipulaci&oacute;n de los dispositivos y camisas se recomienda la utilizaci&oacute;n de guantes.</li>\r\n	<li>El equipo de aplicaci&oacute;n debe desinfectarse antes de su uso.</li>\r\n	<li>Colocar el dispositivo dentro del aplicador con la cola de extracci&oacute;n hacia el interior, rebatiendo sus ramas.</li>\r\n	<li>Introducir el aplicador en la vagina, previa desinfecci&oacute;n y lubricaci&oacute;n, hasta el fondo del saco vaginal (situaci&oacute;n fundamental para su correcto anclaje). Luego retirar hacia atr&aacute;s el aplicador.</li>\r\n	<li>Una vez comprobado el correcto anclaje del dispositivo, retirar el aplicador.</li>\r\n	<li>Para facilitar la aplicaci&oacute;n en animales que se resisten a la misma, utilizar m&eacute;todos de sujeci&oacute;n apropiados.</li>\r\n	<li>Seg&uacute;n el momento indicado en el protocolo de sincronizaci&oacute;n de celo utilizado, retirar el dispositivo de la vagina tirando de la cola de extracci&oacute;n.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(5126, 268, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(5127, 268, 6, '<p>Bolsas conteniendo 10 dispositivos intravaginales y 30 camisas.</p>\r\n'),
(5128, 358, 7, '<p>Oral endoparasiticide for cattle, sheep, goats and horses.</p>\r\n'),
(5129, 358, 2, '<p>Fenbendazole 10 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5130, 358, 1, '<p>Wide spectrum parasiticide, adulticide, larvicide and ovicide indicated for the treatment of helminthiasis caused by the main genus of vermin in ruminants: Chabertia spp, Haemonchus spp, Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) spp, Trichostrongylus spp, Strongyloides spp, Cooperia spp, Nematodirus spp, Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Capilaria spp, Trichuris spp, Dictyocaulus spp, Moniezias spp and in horses: strongyles (large and small), Parascaris spp, Oxyuris spp and Strongyloides spp.</p>\r\n'),
(5131, 358, 3, '<p>Orally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cattle and horses: 1 mL per 20 kg of body weight (5 mg/Kg of body weight).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case of inhibited ostertagiasis: 1.5 mL per 20 kg of body weight (7.5 mg /Kg of body weight).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case of tapeworm infections: 2 mL per 20 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep and goats: 1 mL per 20 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case of tapeworm infections: 2 mL per 20 of body weight.</p>\r\n'),
(5132, 358, 8, '<p>As from last treatment until slaughter, in case of meat intended for human consumption, 8 days. Do not use in horses which meat is intended for human consumption. Milk: no withdrawal period.</p>\r\n'),
(5133, 358, 6, '5 L containers.'),
(5134, 269, 7, '<p>ECEGON es una preparaci&oacute;n altamente purificada de Gonadrotroina Cori&oacute;nica Equina (eCG-PMSG), que permite obtener un producto con &oacute;ptima relaci&oacute;n FSH/LH y potencia estable, garantizando as&iacute; resultados uniformes. La acci&oacute;n como FSH de la eCG es propiciar el crecimiento de las c&eacute;lulas intersticiales del ovario, adem&aacute;s de producir la maduraci&oacute;n de los fol&iacute;culos. Su acci&oacute;n como LH es producir la ovulaci&oacute;n actuando directamente sobre el ovario. En los machos la eCG estimula el desarrollo del tejido intersticial de los test&iacute;culos y de las gl&aacute;ndulas accesorias, tales como ves&iacute;culas seminales y pr&oacute;stata.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ECEGON, deber&aacute; aplicarse en vacas, ovejas y cabras luego de retirar los dispositivos intravaginales a base de progesterona, favoreciendo el inicio de la fase folicular, las manifestaciones del estro y la ovulaci&oacute;n. Dada su acci&oacute;n dual FSH/LH, ECEGON&reg;, act&uacute;a estimulando en forma directa el desarrollo folicular y la ovulaci&oacute;n en la mayor&iacute;a de las especies dom&eacute;sticas. Los progest&aacute;genos (esponjas vaginales, implantes, dispositivos, etc.) utilizados en muchas especies en forma previa, inhiben la liberaci&oacute;n de hormonas luteinizante (LH) y fol&iacute;culo estimulante (FSH) de la hip&oacute;fisis, frenando la ovulaci&oacute;n hasta el momento deseado. Cuando los progest&aacute;genos son retirados, la administraci&oacute;n de ECEGON en ese momento, potencia la acci&oacute;n sincronizante de los progest&aacute;genos asegurando una perfecta sincron&iacute;a de celos f&eacute;rtiles.</p>\r\n'),
(5135, 269, 2, '<p>Frasco ampolla conteniendo: 5.000 U.I. eCG-PMSG en forma de polvo lioilizado. Frasco ampolla conteniendo: 25 mL de soluci&oacute;n de cloruro de sodio 0,9%.</p>\r\n'),
(5136, 269, 1, '<p>Vacas: Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo e inducci&oacute;n de la ovulaci&oacute;n. Anestro. Se utiliza en los programas de I.A. y de I.A.T.F. en conjunto con los dispositivos intravaginales CRONIPRES y otras hormonas como benzoato de estradiol (BIOESTROGEN) y Prostaglandina F2 alfa (ENZAPROST DC). Se utiliza tambi&eacute;n para la superovulaci&oacute;n en la transferencia de embriones. Ovejas y cabras: Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo e inducci&oacute;n de la ovulaci&oacute;n, despu&eacute;s de utilizar dispositivos intravaginales. Anestro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cerdas: Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo e inducci&oacute;n de la ovulaci&oacute;n. En conjunto con ENZAPROST DC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yeguas: Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo e inducci&oacute;n de la ovulaci&oacute;n. En conjunto con una dosis de Prostaglandina F2 alfa. Anestro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perras y gatas: Inducci&oacute;n de celo y anestro. En conjunto con una dosis de Prostaglandina F2 alfa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conejas: Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Indicaciones generales: En todas las especies, se indica para inducci&oacute;n del estro y para sacar hembras del anestro. En machos de las diferentes especies, ECEGON estimula el desarrollo del tejido intersticial de los test&iacute;culos y de las gl&aacute;ndulas sexuales (ves&iacute;culas seminales y pr&oacute;stata).Tambi&eacute;n se utiliza para mejorar la calidad y cantidad de semen y la disfunci&oacute;n de la l&iacute;bido.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Modo de preparaci&oacute;n: Para reconstituir el producto, extraer el contenido del frasco de solvente con una jeringa y aguja est&eacute;riles, inyect&aacute;ndolo lentamente al frasco ampolla con polvo liofilizado, luego agitar para obtener una soluci&oacute;n estable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El preparado contiene 5000 U.I. de eCG-PMSG en 25 mL (equivalente a 200 U.I./mL).</p>\r\n'),
(5137, 269, 3, '<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Especie</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">V&iacute;a de administraci&oacute;n&nbsp;</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Superovulaci&oacute;n<br />\r\n			(mL/UI/animal)</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Sincronizaci&oacute;n de celo<br />\r\n			<strong>(mL/UI/animal)</strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Vaca</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>12,5 mL - 15 mL (2500 - 3000 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>2 mL - 3 mL (400 - 600 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Oveja</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>4 mL - 5 mL (800 - 1000 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL - 2 mL (200 - 400 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cabra</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>4 mL - 5 mL (800 - 1000 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL - 2 mL (200 - 400 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cerda</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>5 mL - 7,5 mL (1000 - 1500 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>3,5 mL - 5 mL (700 - 1000 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Yegua</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>12,5 mL - 15 mL (2500 - 3000 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>2 mL - 3 mL (400 - 600 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Coneja</td>\r\n			<td>Subcut&aacute;nea</td>\r\n			<td>0,5 mL - 0,75 mL (100 - 150 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>0,125 mL - 0,25 mL (25 - 50 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Perra - Gata</td>\r\n			<td>Subcut&aacute;nea</td>\r\n			<td>0,5 mL - 0,75 mL (100 - 150 UI)</td>\r\n			<td>0,125 mL - 0,25 mL (25 - 50 UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(5138, 269, 12, '<p>Bovinos:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>ECEGON se utiliza en bovinos, principalmente en protocolos de inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n de celo y ovulaci&oacute;n en vacas o vaquillonas que se encuentren en per&iacute;odo de anestro, por disponer de una condici&oacute;n corporal baja (menor a 2,5 en la escala de 1 a 5).</li>\r\n	<li>Inseminaci&oacute;n artificial: De acuerdo al protocolo utilizado por el profesional actuante, se aconseja el uso de ECEGON en el momento de extracci&oacute;n de los dispositivos (CRONIPRES). La dosis a utilizar, de ECEGON, var&iacute;a entre 2 a 3 mL (400 y 600 U.I.) de acuerdo a la condici&oacute;n corporal, edad, especie (B.taurus-B.indicus) y la din&aacute;mica folicular del ovario.</li>\r\n	<li>Superovulaci&oacute;n: Aplicaci&oacute;n de una dosis de 12,5 a 15 mL (2500 a 3.000 U.I. ) de ECEGON entre el d&iacute;a 10&ordm; y 11&ordm; del ciclo estral (estro = d&iacute;a 0). Se aconseja aplicar 48 hs despu&eacute;s de la administraci&oacute;n de ECEGON, una dosis de Prostaglandina F2 alfa (ENZAPROST DC).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo y ovulaci&oacute;n en hembras en anestro: D&iacute;a 0: Colocaci&oacute;n del dispositivo intravaginal.D&iacute;a 12: Retiro del dispositivo y aplicaci&oacute;n de 1 a 2 mL (200 - 400 U.I.) de ECEGON. D&iacute;a 14 - 16: detecci&oacute;n de celo y servicio o inseminaci&oacute;n artificial.</li>\r\n	<li>Sincronizaci&oacute;n de celos y ovulaci&oacute;n en hembras en actividad sexual: D&iacute;a 0: Colocaci&oacute;n del dispositivo intravaginal. D&iacute;a 13 - 14: Retiro del dispositivo y aplicaci&oacute;n de 1 a 2 mL (200 - 400 U.I.) de ECEGON. D&iacute;a 15 - 17: detecci&oacute;n de celo y servicio (es aconsejable servir las hembras con un carnero apto y hacerlo bajo supervisi&oacute;n, 48 horas posteriores a la aplicaci&oacute;n de ECEGON). Este servicio deber&aacute; repetirse a las 60 horas aproximadamente. Se puede realizar tambi&eacute;n la inseminaci&oacute;n artificial.</li>\r\n	<li>Superovulaci&oacute;n: Para realizar la superovulaci&oacute;n se aconseja aplicar 4 a 5 mL (800 - 1000 U.I.) de ECEGON en el momento de retirar el dispositivo intravaginal.</li>\r\n	<li>Inseminaci&oacute;n artificial: Con detecci&oacute;n de celo: Se aconseja utilizar ECEGON entre las 8 y 12 horas posteriores al celo observado. Sin detecci&oacute;n de celo: Si se utiliza semen fresco (v&iacute;a vaginal) se debe inseminar entre las 48 y 58 horas luego de la aplicaci&oacute;n de ECEGON. En caso de usar semen congelado (laparoscop&iacute;a) se debe inseminar entre las 55 y 65 horas luego de la aplicaci&oacute;n de ECEGON.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Caprinos:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Para sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo y ovulaci&oacute;n en hembras en anestro, o en hembras en temporadas reproductivas, se aconseja el siguiente programa:\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>D&iacute;a 0: Colocaci&oacute;n del dispositivo intravaginal.</li>\r\n		<li>D&iacute;a 9: Aplicaci&oacute;n de ECEGON, junto con una dosis de Prostaglandina F2 alfa.</li>\r\n		<li>D&iacute;a 11: Retiro del dispositivo.</li>\r\n		<li>D&iacute;a 12 - 14: Detecci&oacute;n de celo y servicio o inseminaci&oacute;n artificial.</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Dosis en cabras:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cabras adultas en anestro: 1 a 2 mL (200 - 400 U.I.).</li>\r\n	<li>Cabras adultas en estaci&oacute;n reproductiva: 1 a 2 mL (200 - 400 U.I.).</li>\r\n	<li>Cabrillas: 1 mL (200 U.I.).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Inseminaci&oacute;n artiicial:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Con detecci&oacute;n de celo:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>V&iacute;a cervical: Inseminar 12 horas despu&eacute;s del celo observado.</li>\r\n		<li>V&iacute;a intrauterina: Inseminar 20 horas despu&eacute;s del celo observado.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Sin detecci&oacute;n de celo:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>V&iacute;a cervical: Inseminar entre 31 y 48 horas luego de la aplicaci&oacute;n de ECEGON.</li>\r\n		<li>V&iacute;a intrauterina: Inseminar entre las 50 y 60 horas de aplicado el producto.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Superovulaci&oacute;n: Para la superovulaci&oacute;n se deben usar dosis de 4 a 5 mL (800 a 1000 U.I.) de ECEGON junto con una dosis de Prostaglandina F2 alfa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cerdos:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Inducci&oacute;n y sincronizaci&oacute;n del celo y ovulaci&oacute;n en hembras prim&iacute;paras y mult&iacute;paras: Aplicaci&oacute;n de 3,5 a 5 mL (700-1000 U.I.) de ECEGON hasta 24 horas post destete. El celo aparecer&aacute; desde el 4&ordm; al 6&ordm; d&iacute;a de la aplicaci&oacute;n.</li>\r\n	<li>Inducci&oacute;n de la pubertad en hembras nul&iacute;paras (cachorras): Aplicaci&oacute;n de 3,5 a 5 mL (700-1000 U.I.) de ECEGON en cachorras de 90 a 100 kg de p.v. El celo aparecer&aacute; entre el 3&ordm; al 5&ordm; d&iacute;a de la administraci&oacute;n.</li>\r\n	<li>Superovulaci&oacute;n: Aplicaci&oacute;n de 5 a 7,5 mL (1000-1500 U.I.) de ECEGON. Se sugiere la aplicaci&oacute;n de Gonadotroina Cori&oacute;nica Humana por v&iacute;a intramuscular a las 72 hs, a fin de sincronizar mejor la ovulaci&oacute;n.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(5139, 269, 10, '<p>No posee a las dosis recomendadas.</p>\r\n'),
(5140, 269, 11, '<p>Suero anti-eCG-PMSG.</p>\r\n'),
(5141, 269, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(5142, 269, 6, '<p>1 Frasco ampolla conteniendo: 5.000 U.I. eCG-PMSG en forma de polvo lioilizado.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 Frasco ampolla conteniendo: Solvente 25 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5143, 359, 7, '<p>Fasciolicide. Oral suspension for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5144, 359, 2, '<p>Triclabendazol 10 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5145, 359, 1, '<p>For the control and treatment of parasitic infections caused by Fasciola hepatica (known in South America as Saguayp&eacute;) in cattle. Susceptible species: Fasciola hepatica, Fasciola gigantica, Fascioloides magna and Paragonimus spp. It controls early immature, immature and adult stages.</p>\r\n'),
(5146, 359, 3, '<p>12 mL per 100 kg live weight administered orally with dosing syringe. Administer a single dose. It can be repeated in severe clinical conditions, as instructed by a licensed veterinarian.</p>\r\n'),
(5147, 359, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from treatment until slaughter must be 28 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not use in dairy cattle whose milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5148, 359, 6, '<p>2.5 L bottles for knapsack sprayers.</p>\r\n'),
(5155, 361, 7, '<p>Oral ecto and endoparasiticide for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5156, 361, 2, '<p>Closantel 15 g, excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5157, 361, 1, '<p>For the treatment of Fasciola hepatica (known in South America as Saguayp&eacute;); Haemonchus spp, Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Dermatobia hominis (ura), Cochliomyia hominivorax (myasis), Haematopinus eurysternus, Linognathus vituli y Solenopotes capillatus (sucking lice).</p>\r\n'),
(5158, 361, 3, '<p>Gastrointestinal parasites: 1 mL per 20 kg of body weight (7.5 mg/ kg of body weight). Fasciola hepatica: 1 mL per10 kg of body weight (15 mg/ kg of body weight). Ura: 1 mL per 10 kg of body weight. (15 mg/kg of body weight).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sucking lice: 1 mL per10 kg of body weight (15 mg/kg of body weight). Myasis: 1 mL per 10 kg of body weight (15 mg/kg of body weight).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administer orally.</p>\r\n'),
(5159, 361, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period between last treatment and slaughter is 30 days. Do not administer to dairy cattle whose milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5160, 361, 6, '<p>2.5 L bottles for knapsack sprayers.</p>\r\n'),
(5161, 360, 7, '<p>Internal and external oral antiparasitic solution for cattle and sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5162, 360, 2, '<p>Closantel (N-[5-chloro-4-(4-chlorophenyl) cianometil 2-methylphenyl] -2 hidroxi-3.5 diiodobenzamida), 7,5 g; formulating agents q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5163, 360, 1, '<p>Haemonchus spp, Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Chabertia ovina, Gaigeria pachyscelis, Oestrus ovis (Sheep Bot Fly), Fasciola hepatica, Dermatobia hominis, Cochliomyia hominivorax, C. macellaria, C. bezziana, Lucilia spp, Haematopinus eurysternus, Linognathus vituli and Solenopotes capillatus.</p>\r\n'),
(5164, 360, 3, '<p>Oral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gastrointestinal worms: (Haemonchus spp, Oesophagostomum spp, Bunostomum spp, Chabertia ovina and Gaigeria pachyscelis): 1 ml / 7,5 kg live weight (10 mg/kg). Fasciola hepatica (Saguayp&eacute; in Latin America): 1 ml / 5 kg live weight (15 mg/kg). Sheep Bot Fly (Oestrus ovis): 1 ml / 5 kg live weight (15 mg/kg). Myiasis (Cochliomyia hominivorax):</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prophylactic: 1 ml / 7,5 kg live weight (10 mg/kg). Treatment: 1 ml / 5 kg live weight (15 mg/kg) Human Bot Fly or Ura (Dermatobia hominis): 1 ml / 7,5 kg live weight (10 mg/kg). It is recommended to repeat treatment every 30 to 45 days in order to control the Human Bot ly in peak seasons (spring to fall). In severe infestations of lice or myiasis, repeat the dose every 21 days. Sucking lice: 1 mL / 7,5 kg live weight (10mg/kg)</p>\r\n'),
(5165, 360, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period between last treatment and slaughter is 30 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not use in dairy cattle, whose milk is meant for human consumption or industrialisation.</p>\r\n'),
(5166, 360, 6, '<p>Bottles of 1 L.</p>\r\n'),
(5167, 4, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n del s&iacute;ndrome respiratorio de los bovinos (Complejo de enfermedades respiratorias/Fiebre del transporte/Neumon&iacute;a) y cuadros reproductivos, nerviosos y ent&eacute;ricos provocados por la acci&oacute;n individual&nbsp;o combinada de los virus y bacterias presentes en la composici&oacute;n</p>\r\n'),
(5168, 4, 2, '<p>Cepas de Herpesvirus Bovino (BoHV) tipos 1 y 5, virus de la Diarrea Viral Bovina (BVDV) tipos 1 y 2, virus de Parainfluenza 3 (PI3) y virus Sincicial Respiratorio Bovino (BRSV) inactivados con BEI y cepas bacterianas de Mannheimia haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida e Histophilus somni inactivadas con formaldeh&iacute;do y emulsionadas en adyuvante oleoso.</p>\r\n'),
(5169, 4, 3, '<p>3 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea o intramuscular en la tabla&nbsp;del cuello o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.</p>\r\n'),
(5170, 4, 4, '<p><strong>Terneros al pie:&nbsp; </strong>Primera dosis: 3 meses de edad; Segunda dosis: 4 meses de edad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Terneros de destete convencional (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): </strong>Primera dosis: 45 d&iacute;as antes del destete; Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del destete.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Terneros de destete precoz: </strong>Primera dosis: 30 d&iacute;as antes del destete. Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del<br />\r\ndestete.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Animales transportados (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): </strong>Primera dosis: 30 d&iacute;as antes del transporte; Segunda dosis: 15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Animales transportados (Revacunaci&oacute;n): </strong>15 d&iacute;as antes del transporte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Animales que ingresan a invernada o feedlot (Primovacunaci&oacute;n): </strong>Primera dosis: Al ingreso; Segunda dosis: 21 d&iacute;as despu&eacute;s.<br />\r\n<strong>Vacas y vaquillonas (rodeo de cr&iacute;a):&nbsp; </strong>Primera dosis: s&eacute;ptimo mes de pre&ntilde;ez; Segunda dosis: octavo mes de<br />\r\npre&ntilde;ez.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vacas y vaquillonas (tambo): </strong>Primera dosis: Al secado; Segunda dosis: Al preparto.</p>\r\n'),
(5171, 4, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.<br />\r\nNo congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(5172, 4, 6, '<p>Frascos de 120 y 240 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5173, 10, 1, '<p>Vacuna para la prevenci&oacute;n de enfermedades que provocan infertilidad y abortos en bovinos, ocasionados por los microorganismos presentes en la composici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5174, 10, 2, '<p>Suspensi&oacute;n acuosa inactivada de Herpesvirus bovino (BoHV) tipo 1, virus de la Diarrea viral bovina (BVDV) tipos 1 y 2 y cepas bacterianas de Campylobacter fetus fetus, Campylobacter fetus venerealis, Histophilus somni y Leptospira interrogans Pomona pomona.</p>\r\n'),
(5175, 10, 3, '<p>5 mL por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea, en la tabla del cuello o detr&aacute;s de la paleta.</p>\r\n'),
(5176, 10, 4, '<p><strong>Primovacunaci&oacute;n (cualquier categor&iacute;a que recibe esta vacuna por primera vez): </strong>2 dosis con intervalo de 21 a 35 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cr&iacute;a:<br />\r\nToros y vaquillonas: </strong>Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as previos al servicio o Inseminaci&oacute;n Artificial (I. A.); Segunda dosis: 30 d&iacute;as previos al servicio o Inseminaci&oacute;n Artificial (I. A.).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vacas (revacunaci&oacute;n): </strong>Aplicar 30 d&iacute;as previos al servicio&nbsp;o Inseminaci&oacute;n Artificial (I. A).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tambo:</strong><br />\r\nVaquillonas: Primera dosis: 60 d&iacute;as previos al servicio o Inseminaci&oacute;n Artificial (I. A.); Segunda dosis: 30 d&iacute;as previos al servicio o Inseminaci&oacute;n Artificial (I. A.).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vacas y toros: </strong>Aplicar una dosis cada 6 meses. En vacas y vaquillonas de rodeos de cr&iacute;a y tambo<br />\r\ncon altas merm&aacute;s en el per&iacute;odo tacto - parici&oacute;n se sugiere aplicar una dosis al tacto.</p>\r\n'),
(5177, 10, 5, '<p>Mantener entre 2 &ordm;C y 8 &ordm;C al resguardo de la luz.<br />\r\nNo congelar.</p>\r\n'),
(5178, 10, 6, '<p>Frascos de 125 y 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5179, 362, 7, '<p>Internal and external inyectable antiparasitic solution for cattle and sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5180, 362, 2, '<p>Closantel (N-[5-chloro-4-(4-chlorophenyl) cianometil 2-methylphenyl] -2 hidroxi-3.5 diiodobenzamida), 10 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5181, 362, 1, '<p>To control and treat internal and external parasites in cattle and sheep.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep: Internal parasites: Haemonchus spp, especially benzimidazol resistent strains; Oesophagostomum spp; Bunostomum spp; Chabertia ovina; Fasciola hepatica. External parasites: Sucking lice (Linognathus ovillu, L. pedalis); myiasis (Cochliomyia hominivorax); Sheep Bot Fly (Oestrus ovis).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cattle: Internal parasites: Haemonchus spp; Oesophagostomum spp; Bunostomum spp; Fasciola hepatica. External parasites: Sucking lice (Linognathus vituli; Haematopinus eurysternus); myiasis (Cochliomyia hominivorax); Human Bot Fly or Ura (Dermatobia hominis).</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `tbl_producto_contenido` (`id`, `producto_id`, `parte`, `text`) VALUES
(5182, 362, 3, '<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<caption>Dosage Table (Sheep):</caption>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col" style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Treatment</th>\r\n			<th scope="col" style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Spectrum</th>\r\n			<th scope="col" style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Dosage</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">A</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Internal parasites with a prolonged effect for 60 days. External parasites: Oestrus ovis</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">1 mL / 20 kg (5 mg/ kg);</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">B</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Internal parasites with a prolonged effect for 60 days. External parasites. (*)</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">1 mL / 10 kg (10 mg/ kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>(*) Repeat every 21 days with sucking lice infestations. Administer in subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Kg live weight</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Treatment A</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Treatment B</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>10-20</td>\r\n			<td rowspan="2">1mL</td>\r\n			<td>1mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>20-30</td>\r\n			<td>2mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>30-40</td>\r\n			<td rowspan="2">2mL</td>\r\n			<td>3mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>40-50</td>\r\n			<td>4mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<caption>&nbsp;</caption>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col" style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Treatment</th>\r\n			<th scope="col" style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Spectrum</th>\r\n			<th scope="col" style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Dosage</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">A</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Internal parasites with a prolonged effect for 60 days.</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">1 mL / 20 kg (5 mg/ kg);</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">B</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">Internal parasites with a prolonged effect for 60 days. External parasites. (*)</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:150px">1 mL / 10 kg (10 mg/ kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>(*) Repeat every 21 days with sucking lice infestations.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>(*) Repeat every 45 days with ura in festations.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Kg live weight</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Treatment A</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Treatment B</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>50</td>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>5</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>100</td>\r\n			<td>5</td>\r\n			<td>10</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>200</td>\r\n			<td>10</td>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>300</td>\r\n			<td>15</td>\r\n			<td>30</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>400</td>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n			<td>40</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n'),
(5183, 362, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period between last treatment and slaughter for human consumption is minimum 42 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not use in lactating animals.</p>\r\n'),
(5184, 362, 6, '<p>Bottles of 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5185, 363, 7, '<p>Injectable parasiticide to control hemoparasites, such as Babesiosis or Piroplasmosis in cattle. On account of its chemotherapeutic action it is also effective against Anaplasma marginale. It is a clear and sterile aqueous solution of Imidocarb dipropionate at 12%, belonging to the Diamidines class and to the Carbanilides group, acting against protozoa and rickettsias.</p>\r\n'),
(5186, 363, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Imidocarb dipropionate, 12 g; Water for injection, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5187, 363, 1, '<p>Stand Up is indicated for the treatment and control of Babesiosis caused by Babesia spp in cattle, as well as Anaplasmosis caused by Anaplasma marginale in cattle. Both diseases can occur separately or together and they form a parasitic-rickettsial complex (a syndrome known as &ldquo;Tristeza Bovina&rdquo; in South America) transmitted by vectors such as ticks and other haematophagous insects. It is also indicated to control clinical reactions caused by the inoculation of live vaccines of Babesia spp and Anaplasma spp, during immunization processes.</p>\r\n'),
(5188, 363, 3, '<p>Dosages differ depending on the disease to be controlled and on the route of administration, intramuscular or subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>To treat babesiosis (conirmed by laboratory), administer 1 mL of STAND UP per 100 kg of body weight, equivalent to 1.2 mg de Imidocarb / kg of body weight.</li>\r\n	<li>To treat anaplasmosis and mixed infections (by Anaplasma and Babesia), administer 2.5 mL of STAND UP per 100 kg of body weight, equivalent to 3.0 mg of Imidocarb / kg of body weight.</li>\r\n	<li>During immunization with live vaccines (INTA RAFAELA- MERCEDES), clinical symptoms of babesiosis appear irst since its incubation period is shorter (between 9-15 days). The recommended dose for babesiosis control is 1 mL per 100 kg of body weight, equivalent to 1.2 mg of Imidocarb / kg of body weight. Administer STAND UP, only if clinical symptoms are observed.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Some weeks later (between 35 and 42 days) anaplasmosis signs may appear. In the event of severe symptoms, a dose of 2.5 mL per 100 kg of body weight could be used.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As chemoprophylactic agent, STAND-UP can be used in the following situations: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>When susceptible animals are moved to areas with a high incidence of babesiosis. Administer STAND UP upon arrival or during the irst 5 days since arrival at a dose rate of 1 mL per 100 kg of body weight, equivalent to 1.2 mg of Imidocarb / kg of body weight.</li>\r\n	<li>When susceptible animals are moved to areas with a high incidence of anaplasmosis. Administer STAND UP upon observing the irst clinical symptoms (between 40 to 90 days), at a dose rate of 2.5 mL per 100 kg of body weight, i.e., 3.0 mg of Imidocarb / kg of body weight.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Taking into account the prolonged incubation period of anaplasmosis, no treatment must be administered before the appearance of the irst symptoms of the disease, since this will prevent immunity development after tick infestation and/or haematophagous insect bites.</p>\r\n'),
(5189, 363, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period between last treatment and slaughter is 90 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal period between last treatment in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 10 days.</p>\r\n'),
(5190, 363, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 20 mL and 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5191, 364, 7, '<p>External, pour-on parasiticide containing cypermethrin for cattle, horses, sheep and swine. It&rsquo;s main feature is its long-lasting anti-parasitic and repellent action hence offering a prolonged residual power.</p>\r\n'),
(5192, 364, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin, 6 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5193, 364, 1, '<p>Ectoparasite control and treatment: sucking lice, chewing lice, lies, mosquitoes, horn-lies, horse lies in cattle, sheep, horses and swine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lice: the time to achieve parasite elimination is 4 to 6 weeks. In adult sheep, treatments must be performed within the 45 days after shearing. Lambs can be treated at any time.</p>\r\n'),
(5194, 364, 3, '<p>Cattle: 10 mL per animals up to 400 kg of body weight and 20 mL for animals over 400 kg of body weight. The dose can be adjusted according to the professional judgment of the attending veterinarian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep and swine: 5 mL per animal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Horses: 20 mL, pouring-on: 5 ml down the neck and chest and 5 ml on each lank and loin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administer by pouring-on</p>\r\n'),
(5195, 364, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 6 days. Withdrawal time from application until milking for human consumption or industrialization is 6 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5196, 364, 6, '<p>1 L dosing containers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5 L containers for knapsack sprayer.</p>\r\n'),
(5197, 365, 7, '<p>Pour-on ectoparasiticide for cattle, sheep and goats. Its main features are: high knock-down power, long-lasting anti-parasitic and repellent action, which offers a high residual power.</p>\r\n'),
(5198, 365, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin 5 g; Chlorpyriphos 2.5 g; Piperonyl butoxide (PBX) 1 g; excipients q.s.f. 100</p>\r\n'),
(5199, 365, 1, '<p>For the control and treatment of sucking lice (Haematopinus eurysternus; Linognathus vituli, ovillus and pedalis), chewing lice (Bovicola bovis and Damalinia ovis) and horn lies (Haematobia irritans), in cattle, sheep and goats. It is also indicated to ight other harmful haematophagous insects (mosquitoes, horse lies, stable lies, etc.).</p>\r\n'),
(5200, 365, 3, '<p>Cattle: 10 mL for animals up to 400 kg body weight and 20 mL for animals over 400 kg body weight. The dose can be adjusted according to the professional judgment of the attending veterinarian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep and goats: 1 mL per 10 kg of body weight Apply from neck to rump and on the lanks spraying with a pour-on applicator. Lice: the time needed to eliminate parasites is 4 to 6 weeks. In adult sheep, treatments must be performed during the 45 after shearing. Lambs can be treated at any time.</p>\r\n'),
(5201, 365, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 35 days. Withdrawal time for dairy cattle from application until next milking in case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 12 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5202, 365, 6, '<p>1 L dosing containers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.5 L containers for knapsack sprayer.</p>\r\n'),
(5203, 366, 7, '<p>Pour-on ectoparasiticide against lice and lies for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5204, 366, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Cypermethrin, 4g; Imidacloprid, 4g; Piperonyl butoxide, 4g: excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5205, 366, 1, '<p>Chewing lice: Damalinia (Bovicola) bovis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Horn fly: Haematobia irritans irritans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stable fly: Stomoxis calcitrans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Myiasis: Cochliomia hominivorax, Chrysomya Bezziana, Hypoderma spp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Warble fly: Dermatobia hominis, Dermatobia hominis (Ura).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Horse fly: Tabanidae spp. Mosquitoe: Mosquitoes spp.</p>\r\n'),
(5206, 366, 3, '<p>10 mL for animals weighing between 80 and 150 kg of body weight (calves). 15 mL for animals weighing between 150 and 350 kg of body weight (steers and heifers). 20 mL for animals over 305 kg body weight (caws/bulls/heavy steers). Pour product evenly along the spine, from neck to rump with the syringe of a dosing gun or similar applicator. Product is ready to use directly, without prior or special preparation.</p>\r\n'),
(5207, 366, 9, '<p>Do not treat cattle if rain is expected. In case of rain within 24 hours of treatment, repeat treatment.</p>\r\n'),
(5208, 366, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 35 days. Withdrawal time for dairy cattle from application until next milking in case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 12 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5209, 366, 6, '<p>1 L, 2.5 L and 5 L containers</p>\r\n'),
(5210, 367, 7, '<p>Pour-on ectoparasiticide against lice and melophaguicide for sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5211, 367, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Cypermethrin, 3g; Imidacloprid, 2 g; Piperonyl butoxide, 3 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5212, 367, 1, '<p>Melophaguicide, insecticide and parasiticide against lice for sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5213, 367, 3, '<p>1 mL per 2.5 kg of body weight, equivalent to 4 mL per 10 kg of body weight. Lambs: from 10 to 20 kg of body weight, administer 8 mL. Yearlings: from 20 to 30 kg of body weight, administer 12 mL. Ewes/ wethers: from 30 to 40 kg of body weight, administer 16 mL. Rams/ewes/wethers: having over 40 kg of body weight, administer 20 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pour product evenly along the spine with the syringe of a dosing gun or similar applicator. Product is ready to use directly, without prior or special preparation.</p>\r\n'),
(5214, 367, 9, '<p>Do not treat animals if rain is expected. In case of rain within 24 hours of treatment, repeat treatment.</p>\r\n'),
(5215, 367, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment in the case of meat ntended for human consumption is 10 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not use in ewes which milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5216, 367, 6, '2.5 L and 5 L containers.'),
(5217, 368, 7, '<p>Ectoparasiticide based on a mixture of Cypermethrin and Chlorpyriphos. This combination boosts the effect of both active ingredients due to the synergy of pyrethroids and organophosphorated insecticides. Its special formulation for spraying facilitates the correct drenching and adherence of active ingredients on to the skin of the animal. Insecticide against mange mites, lice and mosquitoes for cattle. Melophaguicide for sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5218, 368, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin 20 g; Chlorpyriphos 50 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5219, 368, 1, '<p>For the control and treatment of infestations by: mange mites in cattle (Psoroptes communis var. bovis), sucking lice (Linognathus spp), chewing lice (Damalinia spp; Bovicola spp), melophagous (Melophagus ovinus), and a wide range of melophagous insects, lies, stable lies, and especially hornlies (Haematobia irritans).</p>\r\n'),
(5220, 368, 3, '<p>ASPERSIN&reg; is applied by power spraying with pumps or manual knapsack sprayers, which must provide the appropriate pressure to enable the correct spraying of the animals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Insecticide against mosquitoes and Melophaguicide: </strong>Dosage: add 1 L of ASPERSIN&reg; into 1200 liters of water, equivalent to the content of one cap of ASPERSIN&reg; into 25 liters of water. In case of having a liquid recovery system, the reinforcing dose must be 2 (two) liters every 1200 liters of water.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Insecticide against mange mites for cattle: </strong>Add 1 liter of ASPERSIN&reg; into 1333 liters of water, equivalent to the content of one cap of one 250 mL bottle into 333 liters of water. All body surfaces of the animals must be fully drenched, taking special care of lesions and skin folds. It is recommended to remove scabs of mange lesions by brushing before spraying. Two sprayings must be performed at a 10-12 day interval in order to break the cycle of the disease.</p>\r\n'),
(5221, 368, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 48 hours. Withdrawal time from last treatment until milking in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5222, 369, 7, '<p>Tickicide for cattle; insecticide against mange and melophaguicide for sheep. Emulsiiable liquid formulation.</p>\r\n'),
(5223, 369, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin 20 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5224, 369, 1, '<p>For the control and treatment of ticks (Rhipicephalus microplus) in cattle, sheep mange (Psoroptes communis var. ovis) and Melophagus ovinus.</p>\r\n'),
(5225, 369, 3, '<p><strong>Tickicide for the most common tick in cattle (Rhipicephalus microplus) </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dipping: </strong>1 L in 1,000 liters of fresh or salt water (1:1,000).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Replenishment and reinforcement: </strong>it is recommended when the bath descends 1,000 L. Replenishment and reinforcement must be made at the same time at a rate of 1.5 L of CIPERSIN&reg; for every 1,000 L of water (1.5:1,000).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dry replenishment: </strong>To carry on without replenishing the water consumed, add 0.5 L of CIPERSIN&reg; for every 1,000 L of water that descend in the bath (0.5:1,000).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To clean herds: </strong>Perform two dips at a 9 day interval. Keep the animals submerged in the bath about 15 seconds, submerging the head fully three times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For general dippings: </strong>Two dips at a 21-day interval. Ectoparasiticide against mange for sheep (Psoroptes communis var. ovis)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dipping: </strong>1 L in 1,000 liters of fresh or salt water (1:1,000).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Replenishment and reinforcement: </strong>2 L in 1,000 liters of fresh or salt water (2:1,000).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dry replenishment: </strong>In order to carry on without replenishing the water consumed, add 1 L of CIPERSIN&reg; for every 1,000 L of water that descend in the bath (1:1,000). To ight mange in sheep a second dipping must be performed 9-11 days after the irst one, with new water. Melophaguicide for sheep against melophagous (Melophagus Ovinus) or false tick</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fresh Fill:</strong> 1 L of CIPERSIN&reg; in 1,000 liters of fresh or salt water (1:1,000). Repeating the melophaguicide dip shall be according to the practicing veterinarian&rsquo;s opinion.</p>\r\n'),
(5226, 369, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 48 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until milking in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5227, 369, 6, 'Bottles containing 1 L and 5 L.'),
(5228, 370, 7, '<p>External larvicide. Anti-myiasis powder. For cattle, Sheep, swine and goats.</p>\r\n'),
(5229, 370, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin, [alpha-cyano-3-phenoxybenzyl R-S-(cis-trans)-3 &ndash;(2,2 dichlorovinyl) 2,2 dimethylcyclopylcarboxylate], 2 g; Chlorpyriphos [0,1-diethyl 0-(3,5,6-trichloro-2-pyridyl) phosphorothioate], 2g; inert excipients, q.s.f. 100 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5230, 370, 3, '<p>For the treatment of screw worm wounds (know as &ldquo;bicheras&rdquo; in South America) caused by Cochliomyia hominivorax, Lucilia sericata and L. cuprina. It has a residual action for 12 days against myiasis-producing larvae. For the treatment of myiasis, completely cover cavities and surfaces of wounds and up to 2 cm of the external edge of the lesion. In the case of deep wounds, introduce the powder inside the cavity. As preventive treatment, it is recommended to apply GALMETRIN&reg; PLUS POLVO to the wounds caused by tagging, branding or marking, castration, shearing, tail docking, etc. The residual action of GALMETRIN&reg; PLUS POLVO is prolonged, lasting up to 12 days; however, in the season of high incidence of lies, high humidity and rain, in large and bleeding lesions or lesions located in joints or in places where the dust can be eliminated, it is recommended to repeat the application at shorter intervals.</p>\r\n'),
(5231, 370, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 48 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until milking in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not use in horses whose meat is intended for human consumption</p>\r\n'),
(5232, 370, 6, '1 kg container'),
(5233, 371, 7, '<p>External larvicide; anti-myiasis pomade for cattle, sheep, goats, horses and swine.</p>\r\n'),
(5234, 371, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin 2 g; Dichlorvos 1 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 g. Indications Specially indicated to treat myiasis caused by Cochliomyia hominivorax, Lucilia cuprina and L. sericata in cattle, sheep, goats, horses and swine. Its residual action lasts 12 days.</p>\r\n'),
(5235, 371, 3, '<p>For the treatment of myiasis, completely cover cavities and surfaces of lesions to eliminate larvae, activating and facilitating healing. The use of GALMETRIN&reg; PLUS POMADA as preventive treatment is recommended for wounds caused by shearing, tagging, branding or marking, tail docking, castration, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The residual effect of GALMETRIN&reg; PLUS POMADA is prolonged; however, in the season of high incidence of lies, it is recommended to repeat the treatment at a 12-day interval.</p>\r\n'),
(5236, 371, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 48 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until milking in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5237, 371, 6, '<p>1 kg container</p>\r\n'),
(5238, 372, 7, '<p>External larvicide; anti-myiasis solution for cattle, sheep, goats, horses and swine.</p>\r\n'),
(5239, 372, 2, '<p>Cypermethrin 2 g; Dichlorvos 1 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5240, 372, 1, '<p>Specially indicated to treat lesions caused by Cochliomyia hominivorax, Lucilia cuprina and L. sericata in cattle, sheep, goats, horses and swine. Its residual action against ly larvae lasts 12 days.</p>\r\n'),
(5241, 372, 3, '<p>For the treatment of myiasis, completely cover cavities and surfaces of lesions to eliminate larvae, activating and facilitating healing. The use of GALMETRIN&reg; PLUS SOLUCI&Oacute;N as preventive treatment is recommended for wounds caused by shearing, tagging, branding or marking, tail docking, castration, etc. The residual effect of GALMETRIN&reg; PLUS SOLUCI&Oacute;N is prolonged, however in the season of high incidence of lies, it is recommended to repeat the treatment at a 12-day interval.</p>\r\n'),
(5242, 372, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 48 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until milking in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours</p>\r\n'),
(5243, 372, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 1 L.</p>\r\n'),
(5244, 373, 7, '<p>External antiparasitic spray that is larvicide, repellant, contains antibiotics and promotes wound healing for cattle, swine, sheep, goats and canines.</p>\r\n'),
(5245, 373, 2, '<p>Every 100 gr of concentrate contains: Cypermethrin, 1,6260 g; Imidacloprid, 0,8200 g; Silver sulfadiazine, 0,0995 g; Excipients, q.s.f. 100 g. Propellant: Propane/ Butanes.</p>\r\n'),
(5246, 373, 1, '<p>External antiparasitic spray for the prevention and treatment of cutaneous myiasis caused by larvae of Cochliomyia hominivorax in cattle, sheep, swine, goats, horses and canines. Repellant, contains antibiotics and promotes wound healing. It can be used for treating wounds or as prevention after castrations, tail docking or dehorning, on a newborns navel and surgical procedures.</p>\r\n'),
(5247, 373, 3, '<p>Spray the wound and its edges from 10 to 15 cm. Apply generously to completely cover the surface and depth of the wound. Generally 5 to 10 seconds are suficient.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Myiasis Treatment: once daily until wound heals, which generally takes 4 to 5 days. When dealing with severe cases of myiasis, it is recommended to remove all larvae from the affected area, clean the wound profusely to favour product penetration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Myiasis Prevention and Healing: generally one application is suficient, but this may vary according to the type wound and environmental conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Intervals between doses and length of treatment may be modiied according to the acting veterinarians opinion. Administered by external spraying.</p>\r\n'),
(5248, 373, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5249, 373, 9, '<p>Do not administer in felines.</p>\r\n'),
(5250, 373, 6, '<p>Aerosol spray of 440 mL/260 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5251, 374, 7, '<p>Ectoparasiticide. Tickicide, parasiticide against mange and lice by dip for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5252, 374, 2, '<p>Amitraz, 12.5 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL. Stabilizer: Calcium Hydroxide,</p>\r\n'),
(5253, 374, 1, '<p>For the control of common ticks (Rhipicephalus microplus), mange and lice in cattle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Diping: </strong>1 bottle (4 L) of GARRAMIX &reg; and 20 kg of stabilizer per 2,000 L of water. Replenishment and reinforcement: 4 L of GARRAMIX&reg; and 20 kg of stabilizer per 1,000 L of water. Replenishment must be performed every time the level of water in the bathing pool falls 1,000 L</p>\r\n'),
(5254, 374, 3, '<p><strong>As tickicide: </strong>For total cleaning: 2 dips with a 9 day interval. For general dips: 2 dips with a 21-day interval.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As insecticide for mange: </strong>2 dips with a 8-12 day interval.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As insecticide for lice: </strong>1 dip.</p>\r\n'),
(5255, 374, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is 14 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until milking in the case of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 48 hours</p>\r\n'),
(5256, 374, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 4 L and bags containing 20 kg of stabilizer (4 bags containing 5 kg each).</p>\r\n'),
(5257, 375, 7, '<p>Ecto and endo parasiticide for cattle, sheep and swine, to control gastrointestinal and lung parasites, mange, lice, ura and myiasis. 1% Ivermectin injectable solution.</p>\r\n'),
(5258, 375, 2, '<p>Ivermectin, 1 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5259, 375, 1, '<p><strong>Cattle</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Endoparasites: </strong>Gastrointestinal parasites: Bunostomum phlebotomum (adults, L3 and L4); Cooperia oncophora (adults and L4); Cooperia pectinata (adults and L4); Cooperia punctata (adults and L4); Cooperia spp (adults and L3); Haemonchus placei (adults, L3 and L4); Mecistocirrus digitatus (adults); Nematodirus helvetianus (adults); Nematodirus spathiger (adults); Oesophagostomum radiatum (adults, L3 and L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) lyrata (adults and L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) ostertagi (adults, L3 and L4 including inhibited larvae); Strongyloides papillosus (adults); Trichostrongylus axei (adults and L4); Trichostrongylus colubriformis (adults and L4); Toxocara vitulorum (adults). <strong>Lung parasites: </strong>Dictyocaulus viviparus (adults, L4 and inhibited stages). <strong>Ectoparasites: Mange: </strong>mange caused by: Psoroptes communis var. bovis; Sarcoptes scabiei var. bovis; Chorioptes bovis. <strong>Sucking lice: </strong>Haematopinus eurysternus; Linognathus vituli; Solenopotes capillatus. <strong>Myiasis: </strong>Dermatobia hominis (Ura); Hypoderma bovis; Hypoderma lineatum. As adjuvant treatment for the control of chewing lice (Damalinia bovis). Ivermectin has been shown to be effective with other parasites such as: Paralaria bovicola (adults); Thelazia spp (adults); Chrysomyia bezziana.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Endoparasites: Gastrointestinal parasites: </strong>Haemonchus contortus (adults, L3 and L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) circumcincta (adults, L3 and L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) trifurcata (adults and L4); Trichostrongylus axei (adults); Trichostrongylus vitrinus (adults); Trichostrongylus colubriformis (adults, L3 and L4); Nematodirus spathiger (L3 and L4); Nematodirus licollis; Cooperia curticei (adults, L3 and L4); Oesophagostomum venulosum (adults); Oesophagostomum columbianum (adults, L3 and L4);Chabertia ovina (adults, L3 and L4); Thichuris ovis (adults); Strongyloides papillosus (L3 and L4); Gaigeria pachyscelis (adults, L3 and L4). Lung parasites: Dictyocaulus laria (adults); Protostrongylus rufescens (adults). <strong>Sheep nose bot: </strong>Oestrus ovis (all larval stages). <strong>Ectoparasites: Mange mites: </strong>Psoroptes communis var. ovis; Sarcoptes scabiei var. ovis; Psorergates ovis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Swine </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Endoparasites: Gastrointestinal parasites: </strong>Ascaris suum (adults and L4); Hyostrongylus rubidus (adults and L4); Oesophagostomum spp (adults and L4); Strongyloides ransomi (adults); Trichuris suis (adults). <strong>Lung parasites: </strong>Metastrongylus spp (adults). <strong>Kidney parasites: </strong>Stephanurus dentatus (adults and L4). <strong>Ectoparasites: Lice: </strong>Haematopinus suis; <strong>Mites: </strong>Sarcoptes scabiei var suis.</p>\r\n'),
(5260, 375, 3, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong>1 mL per 50 kg of body weight (200 mcg/kg) administered in subcutaneous tissue with 10/18 gauge needle. <strong>Sheep: </strong>0.5 mL per 25 kg of body weight. (200 mcg/kg) administered in subcutaneous tissue with 40/15 gauge needle, tenting the skin, in the area behind the shoulder blade or the groin, in the inner side of the leg. <strong>Swine: </strong>1 mL per 33 kg body weight (300 mcg/kg) administered in subcutaneous tissue, tenting the skin in the area behind the ear or in the groin (inner side of the leg).</p>\r\n'),
(5261, 375, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter in case of meat intended for human consumption:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cattle: 35 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep: 35 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Swine: 18 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to dairy cows during lactation period or within 28 days before delivery when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization. Do not administer to ewes during lactation period when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5262, 375, 6, 'Bottles containing 50 mL and 500 mL'),
(5263, 376, 7, '<p>Ecto and endo parasiticide for cattle, sheep and swine. Parasiticide against mange and ticks.</p>\r\n'),
(5264, 376, 2, '<p>Ivermectin 1 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5265, 376, 1, '<p>BOVIFORT&reg; is an injectable solution of Ivermectin at 1%, ready to be used. Its pharmacokinetic properties include a slow metabolism, therefore its therapeutic action is more prolonged than that of conventional injectable Ivermectin formulas. At the indicated doses for cattle, sheep and swine, it is highly effective for the control and treatment of ecto and endoparasites.</p>\r\n'),
(5266, 376, 3, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong>1 mL per 50 kg of body weight in subcutaneous tissue only. The suggested inoculation site is in front of or behind the shoulder blade, using suitable syringes with 15 x 15 gauge needles. As with any injectable product, asepsis standards must be complied with in order to avoid subsequent lesions in injection site (abscesses). <strong>Sheep: </strong>The dose for gastrointestinal, lung and ectoparasites (dipterous insects, lice and myiasis), is 0.5 mL per 25 kg of body weight</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In the case of mange, alternative treatments are the following: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A SINGLE dose of 1 mL per 30 kg of body weight</li>\r\n	<li>TWO doses of 0.5 mL per 25 kg of body weight at a 7 day interval.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>BOVIFORT&reg; must be administered in subcutaneous tissue only. The suggested injection site is in the groin, using a 12/8 gauge needle (or a 12/10 gauge needle i n cold climates).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Swine: </strong>1 mL per 33 kg of body weight, in a single dose. It must be administered in subcutaneous tissue only. The suggested injection site is behind the ear using 12/6 gauge needles.</p>\r\n'),
(5267, 376, 9, '<p>Administer in subcutaneous tissue only.</p>\r\n'),
(5268, 376, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cattle: 49 days.</li>\r\n	<li>Sheep: 49 days.</li>\r\n	<li>Swine: 28 days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to dairy animals during lactation period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to dairy cows 28 days before parturition when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5269, 376, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 50 and 500 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5270, 377, 7, '<p>Ecto and endoparasiticide for cattle and sheep. Tickicide for cattle. Parasiticide against mange for sheep. Injectable oil emulsion of Ivermectin 1% with vitamins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Action spectrum</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cattle: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Endoparasites: Gastrointestinal parasites: Cooperia oncophora (adults and L4), Cooperia punctata (adults and L4), Cooperia spp (adults and L3), Haemonchus placei (adults, L3 and L4), Nematodirus helvetianus (adults), Nematodirus spathiger (adults), Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) ostertagi (adults, L3 and L4 including inhibited larvae).</li>\r\n	<li>Lung parasites: Dictyocaulus viviparus (adults, L4 and inhibited stages).</li>\r\n	<li>Common tick in cattle: Rhipicephalus microplus. Sucking lice: Haematopinus eurysternus, Linognathus vituli, Solenopotes capillatus.</li>\r\n	<li>Myiasis: Dermatobia hominis (Ura), Hypoderma bovis, Hypoderma lineatum.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As co-treatment for the control of: Chewing lice: </strong>Damalinia bovis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Endoparasites: Gastrointestinal parasites: Gastrointestinal and lung nematodes, immature stages and adults.</li>\r\n	<li>Ectoparasites: Oestrus ovis (nose bot).</li>\r\n	<li>Mange mites: Psoroptes communis var. ovis, Sarcoptes scabiei var. ovis; Psorergates ovis.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n'),
(5271, 377, 13, '<p>BAGOMECTINA&reg; AD3E FORTE is an injectable parasiticide, endectocide formulated with Ivermectin 1% with next generation vehicles. Its parasiticide action is complemented with a balanced composition of three liposoluble vitamins which are essential for the development and reproduction of cattle and sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5272, 377, 2, '<p>Ivermectin 1 g; Vitamin A (Palmitate) 8.85 g; Vitamin D3 0.06 g; Vitamin E 1.5 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5273, 377, 1, '<p>For the treatment and control of endoparasites (gastrointestinal and lung parasites, in adult, early and inhibited larval stages) and ectoparasites (ticks, mange mites, sucking lice, ura and myiasis) in cattle and sheep. Being a combined vitamin product, its administration is excellent for growing animals, for achieving the best immune response in vaccinations, for avoiding weight losses during weanings or herd movements and for improving fertility and fattening indexes. The vitamin dose administered exceeds the requirements for the different categories, facilitating management and reducing cattle movements.</p>\r\n'),
(5274, 377, 3, '<p>Cattle: 1 mL/50 kg of body weight (200 mcg/kg) in subcutaneous tissue with 10/18 gauge needle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep: 0,5 mL per 25 kg of body weight (200 mcg/kg) in subcutaneous tissue with 10/15 gauge needle, in the loose skin behind the shoulder blade or the groin, in the inner side of the leg. For mange treatment by Psoroptes communis var. ovis administer in two doses of 1 mL per 50 kg of body weight with a 7 day interval between the 1st and the 2nd dose or a single dose of 1 mL per 30 kg of body weight (300 mcg/kg). For mange treatment by Sarcoptes scabiei administer a single dose of 1 mL per 50 Kg of body weight</p>\r\n'),
(5275, 377, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cattle: 35 days.</li>\r\n	<li>Sheep: 28 days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to dairy cows during lactation period nor within 35 days before parturition when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization. .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to ewes during lactation period nor within 28 days before parturition when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization</p>\r\n'),
(5276, 377, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 50 mL and 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5277, 378, 7, '<p>Injectable parasiticide, endectocide made up of 3.15% ivermectin, specially formulated with vehicles that enable a sustained and eficient action in cattle. Its sustained action over a prolonged period of time facilitates animal handling and reduces animal movements as periods between treatments are longer.</p>\r\n'),
(5278, 378, 1, '<p>For the treatment and control of endoparasites (gastrointestinal and lung parasites, in early stages &ndash; adults &ndash; inhibited stages) and ectoparasites (mange &ndash; sucking lice &ndash; ticks &ndash; bot ly - myiasis) in cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5279, 378, 3, '<p>The recommended dose is 1 mL per 50 kg of body weight equivalent to 630 mcg/ per kilogram of body weight. In animals over 600 kilos of body weight, administer at a rate of 1 mL/ 50kg. Administer in subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n'),
(5280, 378, 6, 'Bottles containing 50 mL and 500 mL.'),
(5281, 378, 8, 'Meat: 50 day from last treatment until slaughter \r\nfor human consumption.\r\nMilk: Do not administer to cows during lactation period \r\nif milk is intended for human consumption \r\nor industrialization'),
(5282, 379, 7, '<p>Ecto and endoparasiticide based on 3.15% ivermectin, specially formulated with vehicles that enable a sustained and eficient action in cattle and sheep. The presence of three liposoluble vitamins, essential for animal development, growth and breeding, together with the sustained action of the product over a prolonged period of time facilitates animal handling, reducing animal movements since periods between treatments are longer.</p>\r\n'),
(5283, 379, 2, '<p>Injectable solution containing per 100 mL: Ivermectin, 3.15 g; Vitamin A (Palmitate), 8.85 g; Vitamin D3, 0.06 g; Vitamin E, 1.5 g; Excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5284, 379, 1, '<p>For the treatment and control of endoparasites (gastrointestinal and lung parasites, immature stages &ndash; adults &ndash; inhibited stages) and ectoparasites (mange &ndash; lice &ndash; myiasis) in cattle and sheep. Tickicide for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5285, 379, 3, '<p>Cattle: 1 mL per 50 kg of body weight (630 mcg/kg of body weight) in subcutaneous tissue</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep: 1 mL per 30 kg of body weight (1050 mcg/kg of body weight) in subcutaneous tissue</p>\r\n'),
(5286, 379, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cattle: 50 days.</li>\r\n	<li>Sheep: 14 days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to dairy cows or ewes during lactation period when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization</p>\r\n'),
(5287, 379, 6, 'Bottles containing 500 mL.'),
(5288, 380, 7, '<p>External and internal anti parasitic highly effective to control and treat gastrointestinal and pulmonary parasites, mange, myiasis and ticks for cattle and sheep. Inyectable solution of Doramectin at 1,1% ready to use.</p>\r\n'),
(5289, 380, 2, '<p>Doramectin 1,1 g; Excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5290, 380, 1, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong>Gastrointestinal parasites: Ostertagia ostertagi (adults); O. ostertagi inhibited (L4); O. lyrata (adults and immature larvae); Haemonchus place (adults and immature larvae); Mecistocirrus digitalis (adults); Trichostrongylus axei (adults and immature larvae); T. colubriformis (adults and immature larvae); Cooperia punctata (adults and immature larvae); C. pectinata (adults and immature larvae); C. oncophora (adults and immature larvae); Cooperia spp (adults and immature larvae); Oesophagostomum radiatum (adults and immature larvae); Nematodirus helvetianus (adults); N. spathiger (adults); Strongyloides papillosus (adults); Bunostomum phlebotomum (adults and immature larvae); Toxocara vitulorum (adults). <strong>Pulmonary parasites:</strong> Dictyocaulus viviparous (adults, immature and inhibited larvae). <strong>Ectoparasites:</strong> Cutaneous Myiasis: Dermatobia hominis (ura, botly, &ldquo;nuche&rdquo; or &ldquo;torsalo&rdquo; in South America) (larval stages); Hypoderma bovis (&ldquo;heel lies&rdquo;) (larval stages); Hypoderma lineatum (larval stages); Cochliomyia hominivorax (myiasis) (larval stages); Chrysomya bezziana (larval stages). <strong>Ticks:</strong> Rhipicephalus microplus. Approved as tickicide with a 99,47% eficiency rate and an absolute residual power of 11 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep</strong>: Gastrintestinal parasites: Haemonchus contorts (adultos, L3 and L4); Ostertagia (Teladorsagia) circumcincta (adults, L3 and L4); Mecistocirrus digitalis (adults and immature larvae); O. (Teladorsagia) trifurcata (adults and L4); Trichostrongylus vitreous (adults); Nematodirus Filicollis; Nematodirus spathiger (adults and L4); Cooperia curticei (adults and L4); Oesophagostomum venulosum (adults); Trichuris ovis (adults); Strongyloides papillosus (L3 and L4); Gaigeria pachyscelis (adults, L3 and L4); Chabertia ovina (adults, L3 and L4).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Endectocides</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pulmonary parasites: Dictyocaulus Filaria (adults); Protostrongylus rufescens (adults). Ectoparasites: Myiasis: Cochliomyia hominivorax (larval stages); C. macellaria (larval stages); Lucilia spp (larval stages); Oestrus ovis (larval stages). Mange mites: Psoroptes communis var. ovis; Sarcoptes scabei.</p>\r\n'),
(5291, 380, 3, '<p><strong>Cattle:</strong> Use 1 mL/50 kg of body weight (equivalent to 220 mcg of doramectin). Administer only one dose in subcutaneous tissue in the neck immediately in front of the shoulder blade or behind it, in the upper area of the ribcage. Use a multi dose gun, with a 15/15 gauge needle and, as done with any injections, maintain all rules of sterility so as to avoid any posterior lesions. The syringe and all needles must be sterilized before use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep:</strong> FLOK&reg; must be used exclusively as a single dose in subcutaneous tissue. Recommended inoculation site is the groin, using 12x8 or 12x10 needles and an 2 mL auto injector calibrated at 0,5 mL, applied while the animal is laying down. As done with any injections, maintain all rules of sterility. The dose for gastrointestinal and pulmonary parasites and external parasites (myiasis) is of 0,5 mL/25 kg of body weight. Mange: 1 mL/25 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n'),
(5292, 380, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption is of 44 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Do not administer to dairy cows or ewes during lactation period when the milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5293, 380, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 50 mL and 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5294, 381, 7, '<p>Internal and external antiparasitic for horses. Geliied ivermectin solution 1% to be administered orally, of excellent palatability and easy application.</p>\r\n'),
(5295, 381, 2, '<p>Ivermectin 1g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5296, 381, 1, '<p>Multidose Bagomectina&reg; Equina gel is indicated to treat the following parasites in their immature and adult forms. Large strongyles: Strongylus vulgaris (adults and larval stages), Strongylus edentatus (adults and tissue stages), Strongylus equinus (adults) and Triodontophorus spp (adults).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Small strongyles: Cyathostominae (adults and L-4) of the following species: Cyathostomum spp, Cylicocyclus spp, Cylicostephanus spp, Cylicodontophorus spp, Gyalocephalus spp and Poteriostomum spp. Other internal parasites: Parascaris equorum (adults, L-3 and L-4), Trichostrongylus axei (adults), Strongyloides westeri (adults), Habronema muscae (adults), Habronema majus (adults) and Oxyuris equi (adults and L -4).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Omasum Parasites: Gasterophilus nasalis (L-2 and L-3).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pulmonary Parasites: Dictyocaulus arnieldi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cutaneous Habronemiasis: (Summer sores, Jack sores, Bursatti) caused by: Habronema muscae, Habronema majus and Draschias spp in their cutaneous larval stages L-3. Dermatitis caused by Filaroides (microilariae): Onchocerca cervicalis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ticks: Help control Amblyomma cajennense and Dermacentor nitens.</p>\r\n'),
(5297, 381, 3, '<p>1 g every 50 kg live weight (200 mcg of Ivermectin per kg of live weight).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administer orally exclusively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Uncover the bottle, place insert with nozzle for syringe on the bottle, ill the dosing syringe with the adequate amount of product according to the animals weight. Do not remove insert once placed on the bottle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administer the product in the posterior part of the mouth, then elevate the animals head to ensure the product is properly swallowed. Avoid administering forcefully in order to reduce possibility of aspiration.</p>\r\n'),
(5298, 381, 6, 'Mono dose syringes of 12 g and multidose bottles of 240 g.'),
(5299, 382, 7, '<p>Ecto and endo parasiticide for horses. Wide spectrum gel combining Ivermectin 1% and Praziquantel to be administered orally. It has excellent palatability and is very easy to administer. It is indicated to ight the following parasites, both in their immature and adult stages: large strongyles, small strongyles, stomach bots, cestodes, lung parasites, cutaneous habronemosis, dermatitis caused by ilariid worms and helps control ticks.</p>\r\n'),
(5300, 382, 2, '<p>Ivermectin, 1 g ; Praziquantel, 7,5 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5301, 382, 1, '<p>FORTIUM&reg; is indicated to control the following parasites both in its adult and immature forms: <strong>Large strongyles: </strong>Strongylus vulgaris (adults and arterial larval stages); Strongylus edentatus (adults and tissular stages); Strongylus equinus (adults); Triodontophorus spp (adults). <strong>Small strongyles: </strong>Cyathostominae (Adults and L4): Cyathostomum spp; Cylicocyclus spp; Cylicostephanus spp; Cylicodontophorus spp; Gyalocephalus spp; Poteriostomum spp. <strong>Other endoparasites: </strong>Parascaris equorum (adults, L3 and L4); Oxyuris equi (adults and L4); Trichostrongylus axei (adults); Strongyloides westeri (adults); Habronema muscae (adults); Habronema majus (adults); Anoplocephala perfoliata; Anoplocephala magna; Paranoplocephala mamillana. <strong>Stomach bots: </strong>Gasterophilus nasalis (L2 y L3). <strong>Lung parasites: </strong>Dictyocaulus arnfeldi. Cutaneous habronemosis (summer sores) caused by: Habronema muscae; Habronema majus; Draschias spp in cutaneous larval stages L3. <strong>Dermatitis caused by Filarias (microlariae): </strong>Onchocerca cervicalis. <strong>Ticks: Help control: </strong>Amblyomma cajenense; Dermacentor nitens</p>\r\n'),
(5302, 382, 3, '<p>1 g per 50 kg of body weight (200 mcg of Ivermectin/ kg of body weight and 1.5 mg of Praziquantel/kg of body weight). Administer orally only. For the correct dosing of the product, calibrate the dosing syringe according to the weight of the animal to be treated.</p>\r\n'),
(5303, 382, 16, '<p>Open the mouth and put your ingers into the nose and your thumb onto the palate, exerting gentle pressure. Remove the cap of the syringe and place the tip in the animal&rsquo;s mouth on the back of the tongue, then push the plunger slowly. The horse will taste the lavor and will swallow the gel. Avoid brisk administration to prevent aspiration.</p>\r\n'),
(5304, 382, 17, '<p>At the indicated dose it can be administered to horses of all ages, including mares in any pregnancy stage. Stallions fertility and semen quality will not be affected. It is not teratogenic.</p>\r\n'),
(5305, 382, 8, '<p>Withdrawal time from treatment until slaughter for human consumption is 14 days.</p>\r\n'),
(5306, 382, 6, '<p>Monodose syringes containing 12 g and multidose bottles containing 240 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5307, 383, 7, '<p>Broad spectrum injectable antibiotic for cattle and swine.</p>\r\n'),
(5308, 383, 2, '<p>Ceftiofur base (as Chlorhydrate) 5 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5309, 383, 1, '<p>Indicated to control the most common bacterial infection caused by gram positive and negative bacteria. Indicated for use in cattle of all ages and type of production, including dairy heifers and cows; in swine: indicated for use in pigs and piglets for breeding and fattening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Cattle: it is indicated for treatment of Bovine Respiratory Disease (BRD), shipping fever or pneumonia associated with Mannheimia (Pasteurella) haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida and Histophilus somni. For the treatment of acute interdigital necrobacillosis (foot-rot or pododermatitis) associated with Fusobacterium necrophorum and Bacteroides melaninogenicus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In swine: it is indicated for the treatment and control of swine bacterial respiratory disease (swine bacterial pneumoniae) associated with Pasteurella multocida, Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae and Streptococcus suis Type 2. Effective against infections caused by Escherichia coli, Salmonella typhimurium, Haemophilus pleuropneumoniae, Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus agalactiae, S. dysgalactiae, S. uberis and S. bovis.</p>\r\n'),
(5310, 383, 3, '<p>Cattle: 1 to 2 mL per 50 kg of body weight in subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Swine: 0.5 - 1 mL per 10 kg of body weight in deep intramuscular tissue only.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In both species the dose must be repeated every 24 hours for at least 3 days. The extension of the treatment will be according to the professional judgment of the attending veterinarian.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No withdrawal period for meat or milk intended for human consumption.</p>\r\n'),
(5311, 383, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 30 and 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5312, 384, 7, '<p>Broad spectrum injectable antibiotic &ndash; antipyretic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For cattle and horses. Synergic biphasic association of Penicillin and Streptomycin with Dipyrone and Vitamin C.</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `tbl_producto_contenido` (`id`, `producto_id`, `parte`, `text`) VALUES
(5313, 384, 2, '<p>Each powder vial contains: Penicillin G. sodium, 2,500,000 IU; Penicillin G. benzathine, 2,500,000 IU; Streptomycin (as sulfate), 2000 mg; Dipyrone, 1000 mg. Each vial with the diluting agent contains: Vitamin C, 1100 mg; Lidocaine chlorhydrate, 60 mg; excipients, q.s.f. 16 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5314, 384, 1, '<p>Pneumonia, bronchopneumonia, pneumoenteritis, nephritis, pyelonephritis, cystitis, metritis, hepatitis, mastitis, septicemia, adenitis in horses, interdigital furunculosis, actinomycosis, carbuncle, tetanus, leptospirosis. For the treatment of infections from germs sensitive to penicillin or streptomycin.</p>\r\n'),
(5315, 384, 3, '<p>10,000 to 20,000 I.U. of penicillin/kg of body weight, in deep intramuscular tissue, equivalent to about 3.2 mL of reconstituted product per 100 kg of body weight, given according to the severity of the condition. Usually a single injection is enough. If symptoms do not recede, the application can be repeated after 24-48 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5316, 384, 8, '<p>From last treatment until slaughter in the case of meat intended for human consumption: 30 day From last treatment and the use of milk intended for human consumption or industrialization: 4 days (8 milkings).</p>\r\n'),
(5317, 384, 6, 'Package containing 12 boxes. Each box contains one \r\npowder vial and one vial with the diluting agent.'),
(5318, 385, 7, '<p>Broad spectrum antibiotic for cattle and swine.</p>\r\n'),
(5319, 385, 2, '<p>Florphenicol 30% (30 g/mL).</p>\r\n'),
(5320, 385, 1, '<p>Cattle: Bovine Respiratory Disease (Shipping Fever): Mannheimia (Pasteurella) haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida and Histophilus somni (Haemophilus somnus). Calf diarrhea (neonatal calf diarrhea syndrome): Escherichia coli ET and pneumoenteric conditions: Corynebacterium pyogenes, Salmonella spp, Streptococcus spp, Staphilococcus spp, Klebsiella spp. Pododermatitis: Fusobacterium necrophorum, Bacteroides nodosus, melaninogenicus bacteroids. Infectious Bovine Keratoconjunctivitis, including Moraxella spp. Genital tract infections (metritis, pyometra and endometritis) and infections in general. Swine: Respiratory infections (Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae), enzootic pneumonia (Haemophilus inluenzae), atrophic rhinitis (Pasteurella multocida, Bordetella bronchyseptica). Diarrhea caused by Escherichia coli, Salmonella spp. Infections of genital organs (metritis, pyometra) and metritis, mastitis and agalactiae syndrome (M.M.A.).</p>\r\n'),
(5321, 385, 3, '<p>Cattle: 40 mg/kg of body weight (2 ml/15 kg) a single dose in subcutaneous tissue. 20 mg/kg of body weight (1 ml /15 kg), in intramuscular tissue, repeat after 48 hours. (Do not administer more than 10 ml in each injection site). Swine: 10 to 15 mg/kg of body weight, equivalent to 1 mL per 30 to 20 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n'),
(5322, 385, 8, '<p>Meat: from last treatment until slaughter for human consumption, 28 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Milk: do not use in cows during lactation period if milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5323, 385, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5324, 386, 7, '<p>Broad spectrum antibiotic with a prolonged action for cattle, swine, sheep and goats. The excipients of this formula enable:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtain high and immediately effective tissular and plasmatic concentrations.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintains concentrations for three to ive days.</li>\r\n	<li>Treat infections administering a single dose, even in acute cases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MAXIBIOTIC L.A. has a very broad spectrum covering Gram (+) and Gram (-) germs; Mycoplasms, Protozoan, Rickettsias, Chlamydia and Actinomycetes.</p>\r\n'),
(5325, 386, 2, '<p>Oxytetracycline base, 20 g; prolonged action excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5326, 386, 1, '<p><strong>Cattle: </strong>Pneumopathologies and Infectious Gastroenteritis, infectious abortions, joint infections, pododermatitis, arthritis, infectious keratoconjunctivitis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Swine: </strong>Pneumopathologies and Infectious Gastroenteritis, metritis, mastitis, agalactia, Infectious abortions, Atrophic rhinitis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep and goats:</strong> Pododermatitis, abortions caused by Chlamydia and Salmonellas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Other indications: </strong>Shipping fever, Anaplasmosis, Pyroplasmosis, Leptospirosis and Symptomatic Carbuncle.</p>\r\n'),
(5327, 386, 3, '<p>1 mL per 10 kg of body weight (20 mg/kg of body weight) in deep intramuscular tissue in cattle, sheep, goats and swine; and in subcutaneous tissue for piglets under 10 kg of body weight. In the case of severe infections, another dose can be administered after three days.</p>\r\n'),
(5328, 386, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter for human consumption is 28 days. Do not administer to dairy cattle whose milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5329, 386, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 100 mL and 250 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5330, 387, 7, '<p>Antibiotic. Injectable solution for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5331, 387, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Tilmicosin, 30 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5332, 387, 1, '<p>It is indicated for the treatment of respiratory disease in cattle, mainly associated to shipping fever, caused by Mannheimia haemolytica (Pasteurella haemolytica), treatment of infectious pododermatitis, pneumonia in calves and bovine infectious keratoconjunctivitis (BIK). The etiological agents susceptible to MAXITYL&reg; are: Mannheimia (Pasteurella) haemolytica; Pasteurella multocida; Histophilus somni (Haemophilus somnus); Mycoplasma dispar; Mycoplasma bovis; Staphyloccocus aureus; Streptoccocus agalactiae; Actinomyces pyogenes; Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae; Moraxella bovis; Clostridium perfringens; Fusobacterium necrophorum.</p>\r\n'),
(5333, 387, 3, '<p>5 to 10 mg/kg of body weight, equivalent to 1 mL of MAXITYL&reg; per 30 to 60 kg of body weight, according to the practicing veterinarian&rsquo;s criterion. MAXITYL&reg; is administered to cattle in subcutaneous tissue only in the neck or behind the shoulder blade, with regular syringes and 12/18 gauge needles. Do not use in auto injectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class="marker"><strong>DO NOT ADMINISTER ENDOVENOUSLY- ENDOVENOUS INJECTION OF THIS PRODUCT HAS BEEN SHOWN TO BE FATAL. </strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pneumonia: 1 mL/30 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pododermatitis: 1 mL/60 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keratoconjunctivitis: 1 mL/60 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Usually single doses are used. If symptoms do not recede after 48 hours, reevaluate diagnosis.</p>\r\n'),
(5334, 387, 9, '<p>For cattle only. Do not use in other species since it may be lethal. Handle with care, accidental injection may result in death.</p>\r\n'),
(5335, 387, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter for human consumption is 28 days. Do not administer to dairy cattle whose milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5336, 387, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 20 mL and 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5337, 388, 7, '<p>Antibiotic and anti-inlammatory. Injectable solution for cattle. MAXITYL&reg; PLATINUM combines a broad spectrum antibiotic (Tilmicosin) with a modern non-steroidal anti-inlammatory (Ketoprofen), where tilmicosin acts as a chemotherapeutic agent while ketoprofen reduces pain, fever and inlammation.</p>\r\n'),
(5338, 388, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Tilmicosin, 30 g; Ketoprofen, 9 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5339, 388, 1, '<p>The combined action of the two active ingredients of MAXITYL&reg; PLATINUM allows the treatment of bovine respiratory disease, mainly associated to shipping fever caused by Mannheimia (Pasteurella) haemolytica, infectious pododermatitis (Pododermatitis Infecciosa), and bovine infectious keratoconjunctivitis (BIK) thanks to the Tilmicosin. On the other hand, Ketoprofen contributes to alleviate pain, reduce fever and inlammation associated to any infectious process, thus improving the general health status and restoring normal appetite in affected animals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The etiological agents susceptible to MAXITYL&reg; PLATINUM are: Mannheimia (Pasterurella) haemolytica, Pasteurella multocida, Histophilus somni (Haemophilus somnus), Mycoplasma dispar, Mycoplasma bovis, Staphylococcus aureus, Streptococcus agalactiae, Actinomyces pyogenes, Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae, Moraxella bovis, Clostridium perfringens, Fusobacterium necrophorum.</p>\r\n'),
(5340, 388, 3, '<p>1 mL per 30 or 60 kg of body weight, according to the professional judgment of the attending veterinarian, equivalent to 5 to 10 mg/kg of Tilmicosin and 1.5 to 3 mg/ kg of Ketoprofen. In general a single dose is necessary. If the condition has not improved after 48 hours, reevaluate diagnosis.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pneumonia: 1 mL/30 kg of body weight</li>\r\n	<li>Pododermatitis: 1 mL/60 kg of body weight</li>\r\n	<li>Keratoconjunctivitis: 1 mL/60 kg of body weight</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Administer in subcutaneous tissue in the neck or behind the shoulder blade with regular syringes and 12/18 gauge needles. Do not use in auto injectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DO NOT ADMINISTER BY ENDOVENOUSly - ENDOVENOUS INJECTION OF THIS PRODUCT HAS BEEN SHOWN TO BE FATAL.</strong></p>\r\n'),
(5341, 388, 9, '<p>Use only in cattle. Its use in other species may be fatal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Handle with care, accidental injection of this drug in humans has been associated with fatalities.</p>\r\n'),
(5342, 388, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter for human consumption is 28 days. Do not administer to dairy cattle whose milk is intended for human consumption or industrialization.</p>\r\n'),
(5343, 388, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 20 mL and 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5344, 389, 7, '<p>Hormonal agent for estrus and reproduction management in cattle, sheep, horses, swine, dogs and cats.</p>\r\n'),
(5345, 389, 2, '<p>Estradiol Benzoate, 100 mg; Excipients q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5346, 389, 1, '<p>Therapeutic indications: BIOESTROGEN&reg; is a hormonal agent with estrogenic effects, indicated as coadjuvant for the treatment of tocogynecological conditions such as dystocia, placental retention, abortions, metritis and pyometra in horses, cattle, sheep, swine, dogs and cats and for the treatment of pseudo-pregnancies in dogs. BIOESTROGEN&reg; is also indicated as coadjuvant for the treatment of anestrus in those species.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reproductive management: </strong>BIOESTROGEN&reg; is indicated to be used in several Reproductive Programs for horses, cattle, sheep, swine, dogs and cats, for estrus synchronization in Artiicial Insemination at ixed times or in natural service schemes.</p>\r\n'),
(5347, 389, 3, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Cattle: 0.5 to 10 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Horses: 2 to 10 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Sheep: 0.5 to 3 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Swine: 1 to 4 mL.</li>\r\n	<li>Dogs and Cats: 0.01 to 0.1 mL /kg of live weight</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Route of administration for all species is in deep intramuscular tissue.</p>\r\n'),
(5348, 389, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter or for milk in the case of milk intended for human use and/ or industrialization is 30 days.</p>\r\n'),
(5349, 389, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5350, 390, 7, '<p>Hormones that manage estrous cycle and reproduction in cattle, horses, sheep, goats, swine and canines.</p>\r\n'),
(5351, 390, 2, '<p>Estradiol cypionate, 50 mg; excipients, q.s.f 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5352, 390, 1, '<p>Ovulation synchronization protocols in ixed-time artiicial insemination (FTAI) and reproduction programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the treatment of: Anestrous, persistent corpus luteum, metritis, pyometra, placenta retention and mummiied bovine fetuses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anestrous in sheep, goats, swine and estrous syncronization in goats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Urinary incontinence in spayed female canines, anestrous, pseudopregnancy, benign prostatic hyperplasia and as an adjuvant in the treatment of anal adenomas in canines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Potentiates intrauterine defense mecanisms and estrous induction in horses.</p>\r\n'),
(5353, 390, 3, '<p>Cattle</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Treatment of anestrous: 3 - 5 mg (6 -10 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>Persistent corpus luteum: 4 mg (8 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>Metritis, pyometra, placenta retention and mummiied fetuses: 10 mg (20 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>Estrous synchronization: 0,5 - 1 mg (1-2 mL)</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed-time artiicial insemination (FTAI) protocols in cattle:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Protocol N&deg; 1:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Day 0: place intravaginal device with progesterone (CRONIPRES&reg;) and administer 2 mg of estradiol benzoate (BIOESTROGEN&reg;).</li>\r\n			<li>Day 7: remove intravaginal device with progesterone (CRONIPRES&reg;) and administer 0,150 g of D-cloprostenol (Enzaprost DC) and 0,5 to 1 mg of Croni-Cip.</li>\r\n			<li>Day 9: 48 to 56 hours after removing intravaginal device with progesterone perform FTAI.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>Protocol N&deg; 2:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Day 0: place intravaginal device with progesterone (CRONIPRES&reg;) and administer 2 mg of estradiol benzoate (BIOESTROGEN&reg;).</li>\r\n			<li>Day 8: remove intravaginal device with progesterone (CRONIPRES&reg;) and administer 0,150 g of D-cloprostenol (Enzaprost DC) and 0,5 to 1 mg of Croni-Cip.</li>\r\n			<li>Day 10: 48 to 56 hours after removing intravaginal device with progesterone perform FTAI.</li>\r\n			<li>It is recommended that cows in anestrous receive 400 IU of equine chorionic gonadotropin (eCG) (ECEGON&reg;) when removing the intravaginal device with progesterone (day 7 or 8, respectively).</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Horses</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Estrous induction during anovulatory phase: 10 mg (20 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>Estrous induction during reproduction phase: 1 mg (2 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>To potentiate intrauterine mechanisms of defence: 1-2 mg (2-4 mL) for 3 to 5 days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep, Goats and Swine</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Treatment of anestrous in goats: 0,5-1 mg (1 to 2 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>Estrous synchronization in goats: 1 mg (2 mL).</li>\r\n	<li>Estrous synchronization protocol in goats:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Day 0: place intravaginal device with progesterone and administer 1 mg of Croni-Cip and 5 mg of prostaglandin F2.</li>\r\n		<li>Day 4: apply 250 IU of equine chorionic gonadotropin (eCG) (ECEGON&reg;).</li>\r\n		<li>Day 5: remove intravaginal device with progesterone.</li>\r\n		<li>Day 6: 24 hours after removing intravaginal device with progesterone administer 1 mg of Croni-Cip.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Goats remain in estrous from the removal of the intravaginal device with progesterone until 48 hours later.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Canines</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Treatment of anestrous, urinary incontinence, pseudopregnancy, benign prostatic hyperplasia and as an adjuvant in the treatment of anal adenomas: 0,5 - 1 mg (0,02 - 0,04 mg/Kg or 0,04 - 0,08 mL/Kg).</li>\r\n	<li>Do not exceed a total of 1 mg.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Route of administration for all species is exclusively intramuscular.</p>\r\n'),
(5354, 390, 8, '<p>None</p>\r\n'),
(5355, 390, 6, 'Bottles of 100 mL'),
(5356, 391, 7, '<p>Intravaginal device for the regulation of estrus cycle in heifers and cows. Once the device is placed in the vagina, it starts to release progesterone rapidly; therefore high levels of this hormone are reached in serum immediately. Such high levels of progesterone have a critical effect on follicular dynamics in the ovaries, since they act as an artiicial corpus luteum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More speciically, they cause the regression of the dominant follicle, accelerating the appearance of the next follicular wave with the subsequent cease of the secretion of estrogen and inhibin. The descending levels of ovarian hormones cause an increase in GnRH and FSH secretion from the hypothalamus&ndash;hypophysis axis. The latter is responsible for maturing the next follicular wave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then, upon removal of the device from the vagina, there is a sudden fall of progesterone levels in serum causing an increase in frequency of pulsatile LH release, responsible for ovulation and maturation of corpus luteum and also increasing estradiol secretion in the ovaries, producing the manifestation of estrus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The concept of estrus induction implies triggering a follicular phase that together with estrus behavior, results in ovulation. Estrus synchronization, on the other hand, refers to such simultaneous events induced in a group of treated animals.</p>\r\n'),
(5357, 391, 2, '<p>Each insert contains:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progesterone * 186 mg</li>\r\n	<li>Inert silicon q.s.f. 5.6 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>* Steroid hormone of vegetal origin.</sub></p>\r\n'),
(5358, 391, 1, '<p>Control of estrus cycles in heifers and cows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fixed-time artiicial insemination (FTAI) and systematic artiicial insemination (SAI). Shortening of the interval between parturition and a new pregnancy and of the breeding season cycle. Preparation of donors and recipients for Embryo Transfer Programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reproductive treatments for young heifers. All these indications are accompanied with the use of hormones that play important roles in the control of the hypothalamus&ndash;hypophysis&ndash;ovaries axis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TREATMENT PROGRAMS WILL BE STRICTLY DIRECTED BY PROFESSIONAL INTERVENTION.</p>\r\n'),
(5359, 391, 3, '<p><strong>Intravaginal route</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The use of gloves is recommended when handling devices and inserts.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicator must be disinfected before use</li>\r\n	<li>Place the device inside the applicator with the string for removal towards the interior, folding its arms.</li>\r\n	<li>Disinfect the vulva of the animal to be treated.</li>\r\n	<li>Insert the applicator in the vagina after disinfection with povidone-iodine or quaternary ammonium and lubrication, until reaching the bottom of the vaginal sac (critical position for its correct anchorage). Then carefully remove the applicator keeping the ejector in a ixed position.</li>\r\n	<li>Upon checking the correct anchorage of the device, remove the applicator.</li>\r\n	<li>To facilitate administration in animals resisting the procedure, use appropriate restraining methods.</li>\r\n	<li>In those cases where the device cannot be inserted easily, check the genital status of the animal in question since congenital or acquired anomalies may be present.</li>\r\n	<li>According to the time indicated in the estrus synchronization protocol used, remove the device from the vagina pulling from its plastic string.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(5360, 391, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5361, 391, 6, '<p>Package containing 20 hangers made of unharmful plastic. Each hanger has 4 medicated inserts mounted and one inert silicon insert as support. The three inserts mounted in the inert plastic hangers provide a total of 558 mg of progesterone. Use one hanger per animal in heifers or cows, one time only.</p>\r\n'),
(5362, 392, 7, '<p>Intravaginal device to regulate estrus cycle in cows and heifers. CRONIPRES&reg; TRES USOS is an intravaginal device made of inert silicone and progesterone (P4) used for estrus cycle synchronization in cattle. This enables to improve the development of artiicial insemination (A.I.), whether ixed-time artiicial insemination (FTAI) or systematic artiicial insemination (SAI) as well as management conditions of productive systems. The device CRONIPRES&reg; TRES USOS can be used twice in its original presentation and a third time with the complementary use of the inserts. Three inserts must be mounted per device. Once the device is placed in the vagina, it starts to release progesterone rapidly; therefore high levels of this hormone are immediately achieved in serum. Such high levels of progesterone have a critical effect on follicular dynamics in the ovaries, since they act as an artiicial corpus luteum. More speciically, they cause the regression of the dominant follicle, accelerating the appearance of the next follicular wave with the subsequent cease of the secretion of estrogen and inhibin. The descending levels of ovarian hormones cause an increase in GnRH and FSH secretion from the hypothalamus&ndash;hypophysis axis. The latter will be responsible for maturing the next follicular wave. Then, upon removal of the device from the vagina, there is a sudden fall of progesterone levels in serum causing an increase in frequency of pulsatile LH release, responsible for ovulation and maturation of corpus luteum and also increasing estradiol secretion in the ovaries, producing the manifestation of estrus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The concept of estrus induction implies triggering a follicular phase that together with estrus behavior, results in ovulation. Estrus synchronization, on the other hand, refers to such simultaneous events induced in a group of treated animals.</p>\r\n'),
(5363, 392, 2, '<p>Each device contains:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progesterone* 1.00 g</li>\r\n	<li>Inert silicone, q.s.f 29.0 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>* Steroid hormone of vegetal origin.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each insert contains:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Progesterone * 100 mg</li>\r\n	<li>Inert silicone, q.s. 2.90 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>* Steroid hormone of vegetal origin.</sub></p>\r\n'),
(5364, 392, 1, '<p>Control of estrus cycles in heifers and cows. Fixed-time artiicial insemination (FTAI) and systematic artiicial insemination (SAI). Shortening of the interval between parturition and a new pregnancy and of breeding season cycle. Preparation of donors and recipients for Embryo Transfer Programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reproductive treatments for young heifers. All these indications are accompanied by the use of hormones that play important roles in the control of hypothalamus&ndash; hypophysis&ndash;ovaries axis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>TREATMENT PROGRAMS WILL BE STRICTLY DIRECTED BY PROFESSIONAL INTERVENTION.</strong></p>\r\n'),
(5365, 392, 3, '<p><strong>Intravaginal route</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The use of latex gloves is recommended when handling devices and inserts.</li>\r\n	<li>The applicator must be disinfected before use.</li>\r\n	<li>Place the device inside the applicator with the string for removal towards the interior, folding its arms.</li>\r\n	<li>Insert the applicator in the vagina after disinfection and lubrication, until reaching the bottom of the vaginal sac (critical position for its correct anchorage). Then carefully.</li>\r\n	<li>Upon checking the correct anchorage of the device, remove the applicator.</li>\r\n	<li>To facilitate administration in animals resisting the procedure, use appropriate restraining methods.</li>\r\n	<li>According to the time indicated in the estrus synchronization protocol used, remove the device from the vagina pulling from its plastic string.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(5366, 392, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5367, 392, 6, '<p>Package containing 10 intravaginal devices and 30 inserts.</p>\r\n'),
(5368, 393, 7, '<p>Luteolytic agent for cattle y swine.</p>\r\n'),
(5369, 393, 2, '<p>D-Cloprostenol 0.075 mg; excipients q.s.f. 1 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5370, 393, 13, '<p>Luteolytic agent based on D-cloprostenol, synthetic analogue of prostaglandin F2alpha. The dextrorotatory enantiomer D-cloprostenol is the active form and therefore the most potent Cloprostenol enantiomer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ENZAPROST DC is available as a ready to use injectable solution.</p>\r\n'),
(5371, 393, 1, '<p>Biotechnical: Estrus synchronization and induction in cows and heifers. Donor and recipient estrus synchronization in Embryo Transfer programs. Farrowing induction in sows. Therapeutic: Ovarian disorders. Silent estrus due to post-breeding or post-parturition anestrus. Irregular or anovulatory cycles. Persistent corpus luteum. Corpus luteum cysts. Puerperal diseases: Endometritis, pyometra, etc. Therapeutic abortions during the irst quarter of pregnancy.</p>\r\n'),
(5372, 393, 3, '<p>Cattle: 2 mL (150 mcg), in intramuscular tissue at the base of the neck or in the rump.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Swine: 1 mL, in intramuscular tissue at the base of the neck behind the ear.</p>\r\n'),
(5373, 393, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until slaughter for human consumption is 24 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal period from last treatment until milk is usable for human consumption or industrialization is 4 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5374, 393, 6, 'Vials containing 20 mL.'),
(5375, 394, 7, '<p>Ecegon&reg; is a highly puriied preparation of Equine Chorionic Gonadrotropin (eCG-PMSG), thus rendering a product with an optimal FSH/LH ratio and stable potency which ensures uniform results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a FSH, eCG action is to promote the growth of ovarian interstitial cells while stimulating follicle maturation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a LH, its action is to initiate ovulation acting directly on the ovary. In males, eCG stimulates growth of interstitial cells in testis and accessory glands, such as seminal vesicles and prostate gland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ECEGON&reg; should be administered after removing progesterone-based inserts, thus promoting the initiation of the follicular phase, estrus manifestation and ovulation. Thanks to its dual FSH/LH action, ECEGON&reg; acts directly stimulating follicular growth and ovulation in most domestic species. Progestogens (vaginal sponges, inserts, devices, etc.) which are used in many species as a prior treatment, act inhibiting the release of luteinizing hormones (LH) and follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) produced in the hypophysis, thus preventing ovulation until the desired time. When progestogens are removed, administering ECEGON&reg; at that moment increases the synchronizing action of progestogens ensuring a perfect synchronization of fertile estrus.</p>\r\n'),
(5376, 394, 2, '<p>Vial containing 5,000 I.U. of eCG-PMSG as a freeze-dried powder.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vial containing 25 mL of sodium chloride solution 0.9%. Indications</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cows: </strong>Estrus induction and synchronization, and ovulation induction. Anestrus. It is used in A.I and ixed- time A.I. programs concomitantly with CRONIPRES&reg; intravaginal inserts and other hormones such as Estradiol benzoate (BIOESTROGEN&reg;) and Prostaglandin F2 alpha (ENZAPROST DC). It is also used to induce superovulation in embryo transfer programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep and goats: </strong>Estrus induction and synchronization, and ovulation induction, after using intravaginal inserts. Anestrus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sows: </strong>Estrus induction and synchronization, and ovulation induction. Joint administration with ENZAPROST DC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Mares:</strong> Estrus induction and synchronization, and ovulation induction, conjunctly with a dose of prostaglandin F2 alpha. Anestrus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bitches and queens:</strong> Estrus induction and anestrus, conjunctly with a dose of prostaglandin F2 alpha.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Female rabbits:</strong> Estrus induction and synchronization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General indications for all species:</strong> it is indicated to induce estrus and to treat anestrus conditions in females. In males of several species, ECEGON&reg; stimulates the growth of interstitial tissue in testis and sex glands (seminal vesicles and prostate gland). It is also used to improve semen quality and quantity and to treat libido-related dysfunctions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Product preparation instructions: to reconstitute the product, draw the diluting agent from the bottle with sterile syringe and needle, then inject it slowly in the bottle containing the freeze-dried powder; then shake well until obtaining a stable solution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reconstituted product contains 5000 I.U. of eCG-PMSG in 25 mL (equivalent to 200 I.U./mL).</p>\r\n'),
(5377, 394, 3, '<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:0px">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope="col">Species</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Route of<br />\r\n			Administration</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Superovulation<br />\r\n			(mL / UI / animal)</th>\r\n			<th scope="col">Estrus Synchronization<br />\r\n			(mL / UI / animal)</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Cow</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>12,5mL-15mL (2500-3000UI)</td>\r\n			<td>2mL-3mL (400-600UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Ewe</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>4mL-5mL (800-1000UI)</td>\r\n			<td>1mL-2mL (200-400UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Doe</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>4mL-5mL (800-1000UI)</td>\r\n			<td>1mL-2mL (200-400UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Sow</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>5mL-7,5mL (1000-1500UI)</td>\r\n			<td>3,5mL-5mL (700-1000UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Mare</td>\r\n			<td>Intramuscular</td>\r\n			<td>12,5mL-15mL (2500-3000UI)</td>\r\n			<td>2mL-3mL (400-600UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Female Rabbit</td>\r\n			<td>Subcutaneous</td>\r\n			<td>0,5mL-0,75mL (100-150UI)</td>\r\n			<td>0,125mL-0,25mL (25-50UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Bitch Queen</td>\r\n			<td>Subcutaneous</td>\r\n			<td>0,5mL-0,75mL (100-150UI)</td>\r\n			<td>0,125mL-0,25mL (25-50UI)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
(5378, 394, 12, '<p><strong>Cattle:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>ECEGON&reg; is used for cattle, mainly in protocols intended for estrus induction and synchronization, and ovulation in cows and heifers in anestrous due to poor body conditions (under 2.5 in a 1 to 5 scale).</li>\r\n	<li>Artiicial insemination: Depending on the protocol used by the attending veterinarian, it is recommended to administer ECEGON&reg; at the moment of removing the inserts (CRONIPRES&reg;). The dose of ECEGON&reg; to be used ranges from 2 mL to 3 mL (400 to 600 I.U.) according to body condition, age, species (B. taurus - B. indicus) and ovarian follicle dynamics.</li>\r\n	<li>Superovulation: Administer one dose of 12.5 to 15 mL (2500 to 3.000 I.U. ) of ECEGON&reg; between day 10 and day 11 of the estral cycle (estrus = day 0). It is recommended to administer one dose of Prostaglandin F2 alpha (ENZAPROST DC) 48 hours after the administration of ECEGON&reg;.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sheep</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Estrus induction and synchronization and ovulation of anestrous ewes:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Day 0: Placement of intravaginal insert.</li>\r\n		<li>Day 12: Removal of the insert and administration of 1 to 2 mL (200 &ndash; 400 I.U.) of ECEGON&reg;.</li>\r\n		<li>Day 14 - 16: Estrus detection and mating or artiicial insemination.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Estrus synchronization and ovulation in sexually active.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ewes</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Day 0: Placement of intravaginal insert.</li>\r\n	<li>Day 13 - 14: Removal of insert and administration of 1 to 2 mL (200 &ndash; 400 I.U.) of ECEGON&reg;.</li>\r\n	<li>Day 15 - 17: Estrus detection and mating (it is advisable to mate the females with a suitable ram, under supervision and 48 hours after the administration of ECEGON&reg;. Mating will be repeated in approximately 60 hours. Artiicial insemination can also be performed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Superovulation: For superovulation purposes it is recommended to administer 4 to 5 mL (800 &ndash; 1000 I.U.) of ECEGON&reg;, at the moment of removing the intravaginal insert.</li>\r\n	<li>Artiicial insemination: With estrus detection: it is recommended to use ECEGON&reg; between 8 and 12 hours after detecting estrus.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="line-height:20.8px">Without estrus detection: if fresh semen is to be used (vaginal route) inseminate between 48 and 58 hours post administration of Ecegon&reg;. In the event of using frozen semen (laparoscopic procedure) insemination must be between 55 and 65 hours post administration of ECEGON&reg;.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Goats </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>For estrus synchronization and ovulation in anestrous does or in breeding seasons, the following program is recommended:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Day 0: Placement of intravaginal inserts.</li>\r\n		<li>Day 9: Administration of ECEGON&reg;, conjunctly with one dose of prostaglandin F2 alpha.</li>\r\n		<li>Day 11: Removal of device. D</li>\r\n		<li>ay 12 - 14: Estrus detection and mating or artiicial insemination.</li>\r\n		<li><strong>Dosage for goats:</strong>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Anestrus in adult does: 1 to 2 mL (200 &ndash; 400 I.U.).</li>\r\n			<li>Adult does in breeding season: 1 to 2 mL (200 &ndash; 400 I.U.).</li>\r\n			<li>Kids: 1 mL (200 I.U.).</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Artiicial insemination:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>With estrus detection:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Cervical: Inseminate 12 hours after detecting estrus.</li>\r\n			<li>Intrauterine: Inseminate 20 hours after detecting estrus.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		</li>\r\n		<li>Without estrus detection:\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Cervical: Inseminate between 31 and 48 hours post-administration of ECEGON&reg;.</li>\r\n			<li>Intrauterine: Inseminate 50- 60 hours post administration of the product.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Superovulation: For superovulation purposes, administer a single 4 to 5mL dose (800 to 1000 I.U.) of ECEGON&reg; conjunctly with one dose of prostaglandin F2 alpha.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Swine: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Induction of estrus and ovulation in primiparous and multiparous sows: Apply 3.5 to 5 mL (700-1000 I.U.) of ECEGON&reg; up to 24 hours post-weaning. Estrus will begin from day 4 to day 6 post-administration.</li>\r\n	<li>Induction of puberty in nulliparous sows (gilts): Apply 3.5 to 5 mL (700-1000 I.U.) of ECEGON&reg; to 90-100 kg b.w. gilts. Estrus will begin between days 3 to 5 post-administration.</li>\r\n	<li>Superovulation: Administer 5 to 7.5 mL (1000-1500 I.U) of ECEGON&reg;. The administration of human Chorionic Gonadotropin in intramuscular tissue at 72 hours is suggested for better estrus synchronization</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
