(5383, 395, 7, '<p>GONAXAL&reg; is an injectable solution of bureselin acetate 0.00042%, a synthetic analogue of hypothalamic gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH). Product intended for the reproductive system and reproduction management in female cattle and horses.</p>\r\n'),
(5384, 395, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Bureselin acetate 420 mcg, water for injection q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5385, 395, 1, '<p>GONAXAL&reg; is indicated for the treatment of reproductive disorders, especially those of ovarian origin, and for artiicial insemination programs, due to its effect on ovulation and for improving fertility rates. Anestrus, retarded ovulation, follicular atresia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cattle: </strong>Therapeutic uses: For the treatment of anestrus of ovarian origin, since it promotes follicular development and the subsequent ovulation. For the treatment of persistent ovarian cysts, since it promotes their luteinization.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Biotechnological uses:</strong> For estrus synchronization in artiicial insemination programs. For improving reproductive parameters.<strong> </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Horses: </strong>Therapeutic uses: prolonged or permanent estrus. Anestrus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Biotechnological uses: </strong>For the promotion of ovulation of mature follicles and to predict the best moment for mating or artiicial insemination. For increasing pregnancy rates.</p>\r\n'),
(5386, 395, 3, '<p>GONAXAL&reg; is preferably administered in deep intramuscular tissue, but alternative routes may be used, for example endovenously or in subcutaneous tissue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cattle: </strong>Treatment of anestrus of ovarian origin: Follicular cyst: Administer 5 mL of GONAXAL&reg; (equivalent to 21mcg of bureselin acetate). A gynecological examination is not needed to remove the cyst. A new examination must be performed between 10 to 15 days after the irst. The treatment can be repeated if a favorable response is not obtained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Anestrus:</strong> Administer 5 mL of GONAXAL&reg; (equivalent to 21mcg of buserelin acetate). If estrus is not observed within the end of 10 to 12 days post treatment, it is recommended to perform a new gynecological examination to detect the absence of functional ovarian structures and lack of uterine tone. In these cases, treatment must be repeated. Retarded ovulation: Administer 2.5 mL of GONAXAL&reg; within 6 hours of mating or A.I. In this case ovulation will occur within 24 hours after treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tocological conditions:</strong> Administer 5 mL of GONAXAL&reg; to cows that have already had dystocic parturitions, with placental retention, since these extend the parturition-pregnancy period due to the presence of follicular cysts. This treatment must be performed between 10 and 14 days post calving, especially in dairy cows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Horses: </strong>In mares it is generally used for:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ovarian cysts:</strong> Administer 10 mL of GONAXAL&reg;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Anestrus: </strong>Administer 5 mL of GONAXAL&reg; twice, at an interval of 24 hours. If this physiological condition persists for 10 days, repeat treatment at days 11 and 12.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ovulation induction: </strong>Administer 10 mL of GONAXAL&reg;. Application is recommended 6 hours before mating or A.I., administering the product in the morning and service in the afternoon. It is also recommended to repeat mating the following morning. If ovulation has not occurred as conirmed by gynecological examination, it is recommended to repeat the treatment.</p>\r\n'),
(5387, 395, 8, 'None.'),
(5388, 395, 6, 'Vials containing 50 mL.'),
(5389, 396, 7, '<p>Injectable vitamin complex for cattle, horses, sheep and swine, with a clear therapeutic action which acts regulating calcium and phosphorus metabolism. Thus, bone calciication is ensured, activating blood phosphatases in cartilage ossiication centers and causing better assimilation of these nutritional factors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BAGO AD3E stimulates growth, maintains epithelial cells normal status, improves coats, favors breeding and improves the general health status of the animals. Vitamins A, D3 and E are the so called liposoluble vitamins. Therefore, this formulation in an oil vehicle is the most suitable since stability and therapeutic action is improved.</p>\r\n'),
(5390, 396, 2, '<p>Vitamin A 500,000 I.U.; Vitamin D3 75,000 I.U.;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vitamin E 50 I.U.; excipients q.s.f. 1 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5391, 396, 1, '<p>For the prevention and treatment of rickets, osteomalacia and hypocalcaemia. Intended to increase conception and parturition rates, improve general body condition and fertility of breeding animals and favor weight gain in beef and feedlot cattle. Adjuvant of anti-infectious and antiparasitic treatments. Prevention of neonatal mortality and increase vitality in newborn calves. To be administered during pregnancy and lactation. Vitamin source during droughts or with poor quality feed.</p>\r\n'),
(5392, 396, 3, '<p>Cattle: Bulls 4-6 mL; Cows: 2-4 mL; Calves: 0.5-1 mL; Beef and feedlot cattle: 1-4 mL; Horses: Stallions: 3-6 ml; Mares: 3-5 mL; Foals: 1-2 mL. Sheep: Rams and ewes: 1-2 mL; Lambs: 0.25-0.50 mL. Swine: Boars and adult sows: 1-3 mL; Piglets: 0.25-0.5 mL;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Route of administration </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Subcutaneous or intramuscular tissue.</p>\r\n'),
(5393, 396, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5394, 396, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 100 and 250 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5395, 397, 7, '<p>Injectable mineral supplement for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5396, 397, 2, '<p>Copper (as edetate), 1.0 g; Zinc (as edetate), 4.0 g; ; Manganese (as edetate), 1.0 g; Selenium (as sodium selenite), 0.5 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5397, 397, 1, '<p>ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN is an injectable solution of microelements indicated for the prevention and control of oxidative stress in calves at weaning, at the beginning of immunization schemes and on entry into the feedlot; and any other situation that may cause the release of superoxide radicals, such as shipments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN is also indicated for the prevention and treatment of deiciencies of the microelements contained in this solution (copper, zinc, selenium y manganese). ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN microelements and ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT vitamins, integrate together or separately vital factors for the antioxidant defenses of the body.</p>\r\n'),
(5398, 397, 3, '<p>The recommended dose of ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN, is 1 mL per 50 kg of body weight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The interval between doses must not be less than 30 days. Young animals (calves) up to 200 kg: 1 mL per 50 kg of body weight. Animals in inal growth stages (steers and heifers): 4 mL per animal as total dose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Adult animals:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cows: 5 mL per animal as total dose.</li>\r\n	<li>Bulls: 6 mL per animal as total dose.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Administer in subcutaneous tissue with 12 x 18 gauge needles. It is recommended to create fetal hepatic reserves treating the cows with ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN during the last-third of pregnancy, preventing copper and zinc deiciencies in young live calves, since it is very dificult to administer drugs to this category.</p>\r\n'),
(5399, 397, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5400, 397, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 500 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kit containing 1 bottle of ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN x 500 mL and 1 bottle of ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT x 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5401, 398, 7, '<p>Injectable mineral injectable supplement for cattle.</p>\r\n'),
(5402, 398, 2, '<p>Vitamin A palmitate 3.5 g; Vitamin E acetate 5.0 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5403, 398, 1, '<p>ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT is an injectable solution of vitamins A and E intended to be used together or separately with ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN so that both products may act to prevent oxidative processes in animals facing stressful situations. For example: castrations, weaning, entry into the feedlot, extreme weather conditions (drought - loods). Vitamins, together with microelements, macroelements and the energy granted by the diet (forage and grains), constitute the daily requirements needed for animal life. Their contributions may vary from milligrams to kilograms, but they are important in the same way and any imbalance among them shall cause deiciencies that will affect the animals. ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT vitamins and ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN microelements are, together or separately, essential factors for the antioxidant defense of the body.</p>\r\n'),
(5404, 398, 3, '<p>Calves: 1 mL per each 50 kg of body weight, from the irst week of life until weaning. Steers: 4 mL, every 3 months from the beginning of the fattening period. Heifers: 4 mL every 3 months during inal growth stages and before mating. Cows: 5 mL, 1 to 2 months before mating and 1 to 2 months before calving. Bulls: 6 mL, 1 to 2 months before mating and during breeding. Administer in subcutaneous tissue with 12 x 18 gauge needles.</p>\r\n'),
(5405, 398, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5406, 398, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 500 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kit containing 1 bottle of ADAPTADOR&reg; MIN x 500 mL and 1 bottle of ADAPTADOR&reg; VIT x 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5407, 399, 7, '<p>Calcifier. Injectable solution for cattle, horses, sheep and swine. With energy and cardiotonic supplements</p>\r\n'),
(5408, 399, 2, '<p>Calcium boron gluconate 9.25 g; Calcium gluconate 2.25 g; Calcium saccharate 0.5 g; Magnesium hypophosphate 9 g; Magnesium chloride, 9 g; Caffeine 0.1 g mg; Glucose 12 g; Phenol 0.5 g. Water for injection q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5409, 399, 1, '<p>Hypocalcaemia. Hypomagnesaemia. Vitular Fever. Acetonaemia. Pre- and Post-partum paresis. Eclampsy. Transient Tetanus. Shipping diseases. Rickets. Osteomalacia. Parturient Paresis or Collapse Dosage and route administration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adult cattle and horses: 250-700 mL. Calves, foals, sheep and swine: 100-200 mL. Lambs and piglets: 5-20 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The application of half the dose endovenously and the other half in intramuscular tissue has proven to be very effective.</p>\r\n'),
(5410, 399, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5411, 399, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5412, 400, 7, '<p>SUPLENUT&reg; is an injectable solution of copper (Cu) and zinc (Zn) intended for correcting and preventing these mineral deiciencies manifested in cattle in many areas. Its special formulation enables to achieve and maintain the physiological reserve levels required to prevent deiciencies caused by the lack of these minerals in soils, drinking water and feeds</p>\r\n'),
(5413, 400, 2, '<p>Copper (as edetate), 1.5 g; zinc (as edetate), 5 g; excipients, q.s.f. 100 mL</p>\r\n'),
(5414, 400, 1, '<p>SUPLENUT&reg; is indicated for the prevention and treatment of Cu and Zn deiciencies, including, changes in coat pigmentation (achromotrichia), anemia, diarrheas, deformation of articular cartilage and spontaneous fractures in calves, loss of body condition and prevention of sudden death by cardiac arrest in adult animals</p>\r\n'),
(5415, 400, 3, '<p>Young animals: calves weighing up to 200 kg, 1 mL per 50 kg of body weight. Replacement animals: Steers and heifers, 4 mL per animal as a total single dose. Adult animals: Cows, 5 mL - Bulls, 6 mL &ndash; Total single dose. It is recommended to administer SUPLENUT&reg; to cows during the last trimester of pregnancy to create reserves in fetal liver, thus preventing Cu and Zn deiciencies in newborn calves, since treatment for this animal category is dificult. SUPLENUT&reg; is an injectable solution to be administered in subcutaneous tissue with 12 x 18 needles while keeping aseptic conditions in all injection equipment.</p>\r\n'),
(5416, 400, 9, '<p>Attention should be paid to the dose to be administered, since doses higher than the recommended may cause acute liver necrosis and hemolytic crisis.</p>\r\n'),
(5417, 400, 8, '<p>None.</p>\r\n'),
(5418, 400, 6, 'Bottles containing 500 mL.'),
(5419, 401, 7, '<p>Subcutaneous anabolic implant for cattle and sheep.</p>\r\n'),
(5420, 401, 1, '<p>To increase average weight gains and improve feed conversion in cattle (calves from birth and throughout growth and fattening period, feedlot heifers and steers) and sheep (lambs and wethers).</p>\r\n'),
(5421, 401, 2, '<p>Each implant contains 12 mg of Zeranol. Zeranol is a natural non-steroid anabolic which acts increasing protein synthesis and nitrogen retention, promoting muscle growth. The anabolic action lasts between 90 and 120 days post-implantation.</p>\r\n'),
(5422, 401, 3, '<p>Cattle: 3 implants per animal (equivalent to 36 mg of zeranol/animal).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sheep: 1 implant per animal (equivalent to 12 mg of zeranol/animal).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The implant site is in subcutaneous tissue, between the skin and cartilage on the back side of the ear and below its midline. Penetrate 2.5 cm and squeeze the trigger gently. Withdraw the device gently and verify by feeling that the pellet of the implant stays in place. BAGO-PELL&reg; can be applied from birth. It is recommended to reimplant every 90 -120 days.</p>\r\n'),
(5423, 401, 6, '<p>Display case with 14 cartridges containing 24 doses each (336 doses)</p>\r\n'),
(5424, 402, 7, '<p>Antidiarrheal, antiseptic, carminative, intestinal lora normalizer for horses, cattle, sheep, goats, swine, dogs and cats. Oral suspension.</p>\r\n'),
(5425, 402, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: Phthalyl sulfathiazole 2.5 g; Streptomycin sulphate 0.5 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5426, 402, 1, '<p>ESTREPTOCARBOCAFTIAZOL is indicated for polymicrobial diarrhea in calves, foals and piglets. Colibacillosis, enteritis and gastroenteritis of all species in general. Food-borne infections.</p>\r\n'),
(5427, 402, 3, '<p>For all species, 1 mL/kg of body weight orally. The dose should be mixed with feed, or directly administered.</p>\r\n'),
(5428, 402, 8, '<p>Withdrawal period for meat intended for human consumption or industrialization is 12 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Withdrawal period for milk intended for human consumption or industrialization is 72 hours.</p>\r\n'),
(5429, 402, 6, 'Bottles containing 500 mL and 1 L'),
(5430, 403, 7, '<p>Antiseptic, disinfectant and surface germicide.</p>\r\n'),
(5431, 403, 2, '<p>Each 100 mL contains: trimethylammonium bromide, 5 g; dimethyl benzyl alkyl ammonium chloride 10 g; excipients q.s.f. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5432, 403, 1, '<p>Disinfection of surgical instruments, operating ield, external lesions of animals and udders in dairy facilities, troughs; disinfection of facilities, machinery, tools and surfaces against inluenza A (H1N1) virus. Disinfection of materials, devices and genital area in Artiicial Insemination systems, removing virus, bacteria and protozoan that affect breeding.</p>\r\n'),
(5433, 403, 3, '<p>External pre-surgical disinfection: 1: 2,000 (1 mL in 2 L). Disinfection of surgical instruments: 1: 200 (5 mL in 1 L). External disinfection of animals and udders in dairy farms: 1: 2.000 (1 mL in 2 L). Disinfection of troughs: 1: 10.000 (1mL in 10 L). Disinfection of facilities, equipment, tools and surfaces against Inluenza A H1N1 virus: 1: 200 (5 mL in 1 L or 50 mL in 10 L). Disinfection of materials devices and genital areas in Artiicial Insemination systems: 1: 200 (5 mL in 1 L or 50 mL in 10 L).</p>\r\n'),
(5434, 403, 6, '<p>Bottles containing 500 mL and 5 L.</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `tbl_producto_contenido` (`id`, `producto_id`, `parte`, `text`) VALUES
(5435, 404, 7, '<p>Broad spectrum biodegradable disinfectant with multiple components that act as an oxidant of organic material, applicable on surfaces, equipment and in various facilities. Active against multiple infectious agents, including Gram positive and Gram negative bacteria (aerobic, anaerobic and spores), fungus (mold and yeast) and viruses.</p>\r\n'),
(5436, 404, 2, '<p>Every 100 g contains (w/w): Potassium peroxymonosulfate 54,45%; Sodium hexametaphosphate 21,05%; Potassium persulfate 1,36%; excipients, q.s.f. 100 g.</p>\r\n'),
(5437, 404, 1, '<p>For use on inert surfaces in establishments approved by SENASA. After applying wash off with abundant water. Bacterias: Actinobacillus pleuropneumoniae, Bordetella avium, B. bronchiseptica, Burkholderia mallei, Campylobacter pyloridis, Clostridium perfringens, Dermatophilus congolensis, Escherichia coli, Histophilus somni, Klebsiella pneumonia, Moraxella bovis, Mycobacterium bovis, Mycoplasma gallisepticum, M. mycoides, Pasteurella multocida, Proteus vulgaris, Pseudomona aeruginosa, Salmonella ent&eacute;rica, Serpulina hyodysenteriae, Staphylococcus aureus, S. epidermidis, Streptococcus equi, S. pyogenes, S. suis, Taylorella equigenitalis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fungus: Aspergillus fumigatus, Candida albicans, Fusarium moniliforme, Microsporum canis, Trichopyton spp. Virus: Bovine Adenovirus type 4, Canine Adenovirus, Avian Adenovirus, Feline Calicivirus, Porcine Circovirus, Canine Coronavirus, Feline Herpesvirus, Turkey Herpesvirus, Equine Herpesvirus type 1, Equine Papilomavirus, Canine Parvovirus, Porcine Parvovirus, PCPV (Pseudocowpox virus), Bovine Poliomavirus, Bovine Rotavirus, Chicken Infectious Anemia virus, Infectious Salmon Anemia virus, Equine Infectious Anemia virus, Equine Viral Arteritis virus, Avian Infectious Bronchitis virus, Bovine Viral Diarrea virus, Aujesky&rsquo;s Disease virus, Infectious Bursal Disease (Gumboro) virus, Marek&rsquo;s Disease virus, Newcastle&rsquo;s Disease virus, Duck Viral Enteritis virus, Vesicular stomatitis virus, Foot and Mouth Disease virus, Canine Infectious Hepatits virus, Avian Inluenza virus, Porcine Inluenza virus (type A H1N1), Equine Inluenza virus (type A), Avian Infectious Laryngotracheitis virus, Infectious Pancreatic Necrosis virus, Feline Panleukopenia virus, Canine Parainluenza virus, Feline Infectious Peritonitis virus, African Horse Sickness virus, African Swine Fever virus, Classical Swine Fever virus, Turkey Rhinotracheitis virus, Feline Rhinotracheitis virus, Bovine Infectious Rhinotracheitis virus, Equine Coital Exanthema virus (equine herpesvirus type 3), Canine Distemper virus, Egg Drop Syndrome virus (adenovirus), Porcine Reproductive and Respiratory Syndrome virus (PRRSV), Maedi-Visna virus.</p>\r\n'),
(5438, 404, 3, '<p>Preparation of 0,5-1,0% solution: for the amount of solution to prepare, add the corresponding amount (according to orientative table) and mix until dissolution is complete, until a clear red-orange solution forms.</p>\r\n\r\n<table align="center" border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:0px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Water</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center">Solution</td>\r\n			<td>Water</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center">Solution</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:0px">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>5L</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>10L</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>20L</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:0px">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>0.5%</td>\r\n						<td>1,0%</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>...</td>\r\n						<td>50g</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>50g</td>\r\n						<td>100g</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>100g</td>\r\n						<td>200g</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:0px">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>100L</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>500L</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>1000L</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width:0px">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>0,5%</td>\r\n						<td>1,0%</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>1Kg</td>\r\n						<td>2Kg</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>2,5Kg</td>\r\n						<td>5Kg</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>5Kg</td>\r\n						<td>10Kg</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Surfaces: Saturate surfaces with 1% solution, leave for 10 minutes. As a guideline, 1 L of solution must be used for every 3 m2. The product may be applied on: stainless steel, porcelain, plastic, polyurethane, polypropylene, tiles, linoleum, vinyl, cement, asphalt, wood, concrete, glass; on different types of facilities: avian farms, porcine farms, horse farms or racetracks, sheep farms, hatcheries, all breeding places, canine and feline boarding kennels, zoos, aquariums and ish farms, veterinary clinics, insemination rooms, laboratories. For example: loors, walls, roofs, farm chutes and pens, feeders and waterers, transportation vehicles, incubators, cages and examination tables.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Surgical instruments: Submerge completely in 1% solution for 10 minutes. Do not exceed indicated contact time. Closed Environments: Knapsack sprayer: pulverize 0,5% solution. Nebulizers or microdiffusers: pulverize 1% solution. Apply approximately 1 L of solution for every 10 m2 of surface. Ventilate adequately for three hours before reentering facility. Not it for use by aspersion, nebulisation or micro diffusion in slaughterhouses, cold chain storage facilities and processing plants.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tanks and Water Supply Networks: Empty and isolate the network. Fill the tank with 0,5% solution and leave for 10 minutes. Open the entrance of the network and leave the solution in the pipelines for 30 minutes before draining. Foot baths and Wheel baths: Saturate with a 1% solution. Replace every 4 days or when the solution contains large amounts of debris. Maximum duration of the solution after preparation: 7 days. Store in closed plastic or glass containers, at room temperature and away from direct light.</p>\r\n'),
(5445, 244, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario hem&aacute;tico inyectable para el control&nbsp;de Babesiosis o Piroplasmosis en el ganado bovino.&nbsp;Debido a su acci&oacute;n quimioter&aacute;pica es efectivo tambi&eacute;n&nbsp;contra Anaplasma marginale. Es una soluci&oacute;n acuosa,&nbsp;clara y est&eacute;ril de Dipropionato de Imidocarb al 12%,&nbsp;perteneciente a la clase Diamidinas y al grupo&nbsp;de las Cabanilidas con acci&oacute;n contra protozoarios&nbsp;y rickettsias.</p>\r\n'),
(5446, 244, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Dipropionato de Imidocarb, 12 g;&nbsp;agua para inyectables, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5447, 244, 1, '<p>Tratamiento y control de la Babesiosis causada&nbsp;por la Babesia spp en bovinos, as&iacute; como tambi&eacute;n&nbsp;de la Anaplasmosis causada por Anaplasma marginale&nbsp;en bovinos. Ambas enfermedades pueden darse solas&nbsp;o en forma asociada y se las conoce como complejoparasitario-rickettsial de la Tristeza Bovina, las cuales&nbsp;son transmitidas por vectores como las garrapatas y otros&nbsp;insectos hemat&oacute;fagos. Tambi&eacute;n indicado en el&nbsp;control&nbsp;de las reacciones cl&iacute;nicas provocadas por la inoculaci&oacute;n&nbsp;de las vacunas vivas de Babesia spp y&nbsp;Anaplasma spp,&nbsp;en los procesos de inmunizaci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5448, 244, 3, '<p>Las dosis difieren seg&uacute;n la enfermedad a controlar&nbsp;y si la v&iacute;a de administraci&oacute;n es intramuscular&nbsp;o subcut&aacute;nea.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>En el tratamiento de babesiosis (se debe confirmarpor an&aacute;lisis de laboratorio), administrar 1 &nbsp;mLde STAND UP por cada 100 kg de p.v., equivalente&nbsp;&nbsp;a 1,2 mg de Imidocarb/ kg de p.v.</li>\r\n	<li>En el&nbsp;tratamiento de anaplasmosis y de las&nbsp;&nbsp;infecciones mixtas (por Anaplasma y Babesia),&nbsp;administrar 2,5 mL de STAND UP por cada 100 kg&nbsp;de p.v., equivalente a 3 mg de I midocarb/ kg p.v.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>En la inmunizaci&oacute;n con vacunas vivas al ser el&nbsp;per&iacute;odo de incubaci&oacute;n de la babesiosis m&aacute;s corto(entre 9-15 d&iacute;as), los signos cl&iacute;nicos son los primeros&nbsp;en aparecer.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>La dosis recomendada para control de la babesiosis es&nbsp;de 1 mL por cada 100 kg de p.v., equivalente a 1,2 mg&nbsp;de Imidocarb/ kg p.v. S&oacute;lo administrar STAND UP, en&nbsp;caso de observar sintomatolog&iacute;a cl&iacute;nica.&nbsp;Algunas semanas despu&eacute;s (en tre los 35 y 42 d&iacute;as)&nbsp;podr&aacute;n aparecer signos de anaplasmosis.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>En caso de que el cuadro cl&iacute;nico sea severo,podr&aacute; ser usada una dosis de 2,5 mL cada 100 kg&nbsp;&nbsp;de p.v.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Como quimioprofil&aacute;ctico, STAND UP puedeser utilizado en las siguientes situaciones:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Cuando&nbsp;son&nbsp;introducidos&nbsp;animales&nbsp;susceptibles&nbsp;en&nbsp;&aacute;reas&nbsp;de&nbsp;incidencia&nbsp;de&nbsp;babesiosis.Administrar STAND &nbsp;UP al momento del ingreso&nbsp;o en los primeros 5 d&iacute;as de su llegada, a una dosis&nbsp;de 1 mL por cada 100 kg de&nbsp;p.v., equivalente a 1,2 mg&nbsp;de Imidocarb / kg p.v.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Cuando&nbsp;son&nbsp;introducidos&nbsp;animales&nbsp;susceptibles&nbsp;en&nbsp;&aacute;reas&nbsp;de&nbsp;incidencia&nbsp;de&nbsp;anaplasmosis.&nbsp;Administrar STAND UP a las primeras se&ntilde;ales&nbsp;de sintomatolog&iacute;a cl&iacute;nica de la enfermedad (entre 40&nbsp;a 90 d&iacute;as), a una dosis de 2,5 mL cada 100 kg de p.v.,&nbsp;o sea, 3,0 mg de I midocarb / kg p.v. Considerando&nbsp;que el per&iacute;odo de incubaci&oacute;n de la anaplasmosis&nbsp;es m&aacute;s prolongado, no se debe tratar antes de que&nbsp;aparezcan los primeros s&iacute;ntomas de la enfermedad,&nbsp;pues esto impedir&aacute; el desarrollo de la inmunidaddespu&eacute;s de la infestaci&oacute;n por las garrapatas&nbsp;&nbsp;y/o picaduras de insectos hemat&oacute;fagos.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n'),
(5449, 244, 8, '<p>Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y la faena para consumo&nbsp;deben transcurrir 90 d&iacute;as.&nbsp;Entre el &uacute;ltimo tratamiento y el orde&ntilde;e para consumo&nbsp;humano y/o industrializaci&oacute;n de la leche deben transcurrir&nbsp;10 d&iacute;as.</p>\r\n'),
(5450, 244, 6, '<p>Frascos por 20 mL y 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5451, 274, 7, '<p>Calcificante. Soluci&oacute;n inyectable para bovinos, equinos, ovinos y porcinos. Con refuerzo energ&eacute;tico y cardiot&oacute;nico.</p>\r\n'),
(5452, 274, 2, '<p>Borogluconato de Calcio, 9,25 g; Gluconato de Calcio, 2,25 g; Sacarato de Calcio, 0,5 g; Hipofosito de Magnesio, 1 g; Cloruro de magnesio, 9 g; Cafe&iacute;na, 0,1 g; Glucosa, 12 g; Fenol, 0,5 g; Agua para inyectables, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5453, 274, 1, '<p>Hipocalcemias. Hipomagnesemias. Fiebre Vitular. Acetonemia. Estados parapl&eacute;jicos del pre y post parto. Eclampsia. Tetanias. Enfermedades del transporte. Raquitismo. Osteomalacia. Colapso o Paresia Puerperal.</p>\r\n'),
(5454, 274, 3, '<p>Bovinos y Equinos adultos: 250-700 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Terneros, potrillos, ovinos y porcinos: 100 a 200 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Corderos y lechones: 5 a 20 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Es muy efectiva la administraci&oacute;n de mitad de la dosis por inyecci&oacute;n endovenosa y la otra mitad por inyecci&oacute;n intramuscular.</p>\r\n'),
(5455, 274, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(5456, 274, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5457, 273, 7, '<p>Complejo vitam&iacute;nico inyectable para bovinos, equinos, ovinos y porcinos, de manifiesta acci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica que interviene regulando el metabolismo del Calcio y el F&oacute;sforo. De esta manera se asegura la calcificaci&oacute;n de los huesos, activando las fosfatasas sangu&iacute;neas en los puntos de osificaci&oacute;n del cart&iacute;lago y provocando mejor asimilaci&oacute;n de dichos factores nutricionales. Estimula el crecimiento, mantiene el estado normal de los epitelios, mejora el pelaje, favorece la reproducci&oacute;n y mejora el estado general de los animales. Las vitaminas A, D3 y E son las llamadas vitaminas liposolubles. En consecuencia, su formulaci&oacute;n en veh&iacute;culo oleoso resulta la m&aacute;s adecuada, pues mejora su estabilidad y su acci&oacute;n terap&eacute;utica.</p>\r\n'),
(5458, 273, 2, '<p>Vitamina A, 500.000 U.I.; Vitamina D3, 75.000 U.I.; Vitamina E, 50 U.I.; excipientes, c.s.p. 1 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5459, 273, 1, '<p>Preventivo y curativo del raquitismo, osteomalacia e hipocalcemia. Para elevar el porcentaje de pre&ntilde;ez, mejorar el estado general de los reproductores y favorecer el engorde en la recr&iacute;a e invernada. Como adyuvante de tratamientos antiinfecciosos y antiparasitarios. Para ser administrado durante e inmediatamente despu&eacute;s de la gestaci&oacute;n. Como fuente vitam&iacute;nica en &eacute;pocas de sequ&iacute;a o alimentaci&oacute;n deficiente.</p>\r\n'),
(5460, 273, 3, '<p>Bovinos: Toros: 4-6 mL; Vacas: 2-4 mL; Terneros: 0,5-1 mL; Recr&iacute;a e invernada: 1-4 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equinos: Padrillos: 3-6 mL; Yeguas: 3-5 mL; Potrillos: 1-2 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: Carneros y ovejas: 1-2 mL; Corderos: 0,25-0,5 mL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Porcinos: Machos y hembras adultas: 1-3 mL; Lechones: 0,25 &ndash; 0,5 mL.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>V&iacute;a de administraci&oacute;n Subcut&aacute;nea o intramuscular.</p>\r\n'),
(5461, 273, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(5462, 273, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5463, 275, 7, '<p>Es una soluci&oacute;n inyectable de Cobre (Cu) y Zinc (Zn), para corregir y evitar las deficiencias de estos microelementos que se manifiestan en los bovinos en vastas zonas del pa&iacute;s. Su formulaci&oacute;n especial permite alcanzar los niveles fisiol&oacute;gicos y mantenerlos para evitar las deficiencias provocadas por las carencias en suelos, aguas de bebida y forrajes.</p>\r\n'),
(5464, 275, 2, '<p>Cobre (como Edetato), 1,5 g; Zinc (como Edetato), 5 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5465, 275, 1, '<p>Prevenci&oacute;n y tratamiento de las deficiencias de Cu y Zn, que incluyen fallas en la pigmentaci&oacute;n del pelo (acromotriquia), anemia, diarreas, deformaciones articulares, fracturas espont&aacute;neas en terneros, p&eacute;rdida de la condici&oacute;n corporal y prevenci&oacute;n de la muerte s&uacute;bita por falla card&iacute;aca en animales adultos.</p>\r\n'),
(5466, 275, 3, '<p>Animales j&oacute;venes: Terneros/as hasta 200 kg., 1 mL cada 50 kg de p.v. Animales en recr&iacute;a: Novillos y vaquillonas, 4 mL por animal como dosis &uacute;nica y total. Animales adultos: Vacas, 5 mL, toros, 6 mL, dosis &uacute;nica y total.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Se recomienda generar reserva hep&aacute;tica fetal administrando SUPLENUT&reg; a las vacas en el &uacute;ltimo tercio de la gestaci&oacute;n, evitando de esa forma las deiciencias de Cu y Zn en el ternero al pie de corta edad, al ser dif&iacute;cil el tratamiento en &eacute;sta categor&iacute;a.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aplicar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea con agujas 12/18, manteniendo buenas condiciones de asepsia en todo el instrumental.</p>\r\n'),
(5467, 275, 9, '<p>Prestar singular atenci&oacute;n a las dosis a administrar, ya que dosis superiores a las aconsejadas pueden llegar a provocar necrosis hep&aacute;ticas agudas y crisis hemol&iacute;ticas.</p>\r\n'),
(5468, 275, 8, '<p>No posee.</p>\r\n'),
(5469, 275, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5470, 276, 7, '<p>Antis&eacute;ptico, desinfectante y germicida de supericie.</p>\r\n'),
(5471, 276, 2, '<p>Cada 100 mL contiene: Trimetilacetilamonio bromuro, 5 g; Dimetilbencilalquilamonio Cloruro, 10 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5472, 276, 1, '<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n de instrumental quir&uacute;rgico, campo quir&uacute;rgico, lesiones externas de animales y ubres en el tambo, bebederos; instalaciones, m&aacute;quinas, utensilios y supericies contra el virus de influenza tipo A H1N1.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n de materiales, dispositivos y &aacute;reas genitales en sistem&aacute;s de Inseminaci&oacute;n Artiicial, eliminando virus, bacterias y protozoarios que afectan la reproducci&oacute;n.</p>\r\n'),
(5473, 276, 3, '<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n externa prequir&uacute;rgica: 1: 2.000 (1 mL en 2 L). Desinfecci&oacute;n de instrumental quir&uacute;rgico: 1: 200 (5 mL en 1 L) Desinfecci&oacute;n externa de animales y ubres en el tambo: 1: 2.000 (1 mL en 2 L).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n de bebederos: 1: 10.000 (1mL en 10 L) Desinfecci&oacute;n de instalaciones, m&aacute;quinas, utensilios y supericies contra el virus de influenza tipo A H1N1: 1: 200 (5 mL en 1 L o 50 mL en 10 L).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Desinfecci&oacute;n de materiales, dispositivos y &aacute;reas genitales en sistemas de Inseminaci&oacute;n Artiicial: 1: 200 (5 mL en 1 L o 50 mL en 10 L).</p>\r\n'),
(5474, 276, 6, '<p>Frascos por 500 mL y bidones por 5 L.</p>\r\n'),
(5475, 277, 7, '<p>Anab&oacute;lico, implante subcut&aacute;neo para bovinos y ovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(5476, 277, 2, '<p>Cada implante contiene: 12 mg de Zeranol.</p>\r\n'),
(5477, 277, 1, '<p>Para mantener el promedio de ganancia de peso y mejorar la conversi&oacute;n alimenticia en bovinos (terneros al pie de la madre, terneros de recr&iacute;a, novillitos, novillos, vaquillas para engorde y vacas descarte) y ovinos (corderos, borregos, capones y ovejas descarte).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El implante es compatible con otras actividades simult&aacute;neas (vacunaciones, desparasitaciones, etc.). No aumenta el consumo de alimentos, por lo cual no hay que incrementar el &aacute;rea de pastoreo. No retiene l&iacute;quidos, disminuyendo las mermas por oreo en la res.</p>\r\n'),
(5478, 277, 3, '<p>Bovinos: 3 implantes por animal (equivalente a 36 mg de zeranol/animal).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ovinos: 1 implante por animal (equivalente a 12 mg de zeranol/animal).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Para utilizar el producto en bovinos, colocar el cartucho en la pistola dosificadora, quitando previamente la faja de seguridad, la cual debe encontrarse intacta.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Para utilizar el producto en ovinos, desarmar el cartucho, extraer 2 implantes de cada compartimento, volver a armar el cartucho y colocarlo en la pistola dosificadora.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Para utilizar las 72 dosis ovinas, esta acci&oacute;n debe repetirse dos veces m&aacute;s, dejando siempre 1 s&oacute;lo implante en cada compartimento.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Perforar la piel con la aguja en forma subcut&aacute;nea, en el pliegue que hace la oreja con la cabeza, cerca del borde inferior, penetrar 2,5 cm y oprimir suavemente el gatillo colocando el implante entre la piel y el cart&iacute;lago.</p>\r\n'),
(5479, 277, 8, '<p>Bovinos: 65 d&iacute;as. Ovinos: 40 d&iacute;as</p>\r\n'),
(5480, 277, 6, '<p>Caja dispensadora conteniendo 14 cartuchos con 24 dosis cada uno (336 dosis en total)</p>\r\n'),
(5481, 241, 7, '<p>Antiparasitario interno y externo en soluci&oacute;n inyectable&nbsp;para bovinos y ovinos.</p>\r\n'),
(5482, 241, 2, '<p>Closantel (N-[5-cloro-4-[(4-clorofenil) cianometil ]-2-metilfenil]-2-hidroxi-3,5-diiodobenzamina), 10 g; excipientes, c.s.p. 100 mL.</p>\r\n'),
(5483, 241, 1, '<p>Para el control y tratamiento de parasitosis internas y externas en bovinos y ovinos. Ovinos: Par&aacute;sitos internos:&nbsp;Haemonchus spp, sobre todo cepas bencimidazol&nbsp;resistentes; Oesophagostomum spp; Bunostomum spp;&nbsp;Chabertia ovina; Fasciola hep&aacute;tica. Par&aacute;sitos externos:&nbsp;Piojos chupadores (Linognathus ovillu, L. pedalis); miasis&nbsp;(Cochliomyia hominivorax); gusano de nariz (Oestrus&nbsp;ovis). Bovinos: Par&aacute;sitos internos: Haemonchus spp;&nbsp;Oesophagostomum spp; Bunostomum spp; Fasciola&nbsp;hep&aacute;tica.Par&aacute;sitos externos: Piojos chupadores&nbsp;(Linognathus vituli; Haematopinus eurysternus); miasis&nbsp;(Cochliomyia hominivorax); Ura (Dermatobia hominis).</p>\r\n'),
(5484, 241, 3, '<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">\r\n	<caption>Tabla de dosificaci&oacute;n (Ovinos):</caption>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>TRATAMIENTO</td>\r\n			<td>ESPECTRO</td>\r\n			<td>DOSIS</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>A</td>\r\n			<td>Par&aacute;sitos internos con efecto prolongado durante 60 dias. Par&aacute;sitos ext. Oestrus Ovis</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL / 20 kg (5 mg/kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>B</td>\r\n			<td>Par&aacute;sitos internos con efecto prolongado durante 60 dias. Par&aacute;sitos externos (*)</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL / 10 kg (10 mg/kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>(*) Repetir cada 21 d&iacute;as con infestaciones de piojos chupadores.&nbsp;Administrar por v&iacute;a subcut&aacute;nea o intramuscular</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Kg p.v</td>\r\n			<td>Tratamiento A</td>\r\n			<td>Tratamiento B</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>10-20</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>20-30</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL</td>\r\n			<td>2 mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>30-40</td>\r\n			<td>2 mL</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;3mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>40-50</td>\r\n			<td>2 mL</td>\r\n			<td>4mL</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">\r\n	<caption>Tabla de disificaci&oacute;n (Bovinos)</caption>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tratamiento</td>\r\n			<td>Espectro</td>\r\n			<td>Dosis</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>A</td>\r\n			<td>Par&aacute;sitos internos con efecto prolongado durante 60 dias</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL / 20 kg (5 mg/kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>B</td>\r\n			<td>Par&aacute;sitos internos con efecto prolongado durante 60 dias. Par&aacute;sitos internos (*)</td>\r\n			<td>1 mL / 10 kg (10 mg/kg)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>(*)&nbsp;Repetir cada 21 d&iacute;as con infestaciones de piojos chupadores.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(*)&nbsp;Repetir cada 45 d&iacute;as con infestaciones de Ura.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Kg p.v</td>\r\n			<td>Tratamiento A</td>\r\n			<td>Tratamiento B</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>50</td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>5</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>100</td>\r\n			<td>10</td>\r\n			<td>10</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>200</td>\r\n			<td>15</td>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>300</td>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n			<td>30</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>400</td>\r\n			<td>20</td>\r\n			<td>40</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n'),
